Commentary: Tim Southee finds the edge straightaway. It is a length ball, around off. it shapes away a touch with some extra bounce. The ball takes the outside edge but falls short of the second slip.
On a length, around off. Oshada Fernando defends it out solidly.
BEATEN! Oshada Fernando now tries to feel for it. Southee dishes it on a length, around fourth stump, it shapes away a bit. Oshada Fernando leans in and tries to have a poke at it but misses.
Length and on off, defended.
Shorter, outside off. This one flies off the deck. Oshada Fernando steps outside the crease but makes the leave.
Back of a length, wide of off. Oshada Fernando makes a solid leave. A maiden to start with then for the Kiwi skipper.
Matt Henry starts with a jaffa. It is touch fuller, on off. It shapes away with the angle. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to play through the line but gets beaten on the outside edge.

An appeal for lbw but turned down! Tim Southee has a chat and takes the review. Matt Henry serves it on a length, on off. It nips back in off the deck. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to flick it away but misses. He gets pinged on his pads. Matt Henry makes a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The Ball Tracking later confirms that it is umpire's call on ball hitting the wickets. Dimuth Karunaratne remains at the crease.
This is much fuller, on off. It comes back in as well. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to flick it away but misses.
A length ball, around leg. Dimuth Karunaratne gets pinged high on his pads as he misses to work it on the leg side.

Once again a loud appeal but the umpire shows no interest! Matt Henry dishes a length ball, on off. It nips back in off the deck. Dimuth Karunaratne is caught inside his crease and takes a blow high on his pads. Once again the bounce comes into play to save him.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Tim Southee hurls a length ball, around off. It jags back in. Oshada Fernando takes a blow on his pads. Tim Southee makes an appeal but the umpire thinks it is going down leg.
This time Tim Southee dishes an outswinger, on fifth stump. Oshada Fernando lets it be.
It is a full ball, on off. Oshada Fernando gets his blade down in time and defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Excellent shot! Oshada Fernando and Sri Lanka are off the mark finally. This should ease down some nerves. Tim Southee fires in a full one, drifting down leg. Oshada Fernando hangs back and flicks it along the ground through mid-wicket. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence.
Sharp defense! It is a length ball, on off. Oshada Fernando gets behind the line and defends it out with full face of the blade.
On a length, on off. Oshada Fernando pushes it to cover and gets a single.
Matt Henry goes full, around off, swinging away. Oshada Fernando gets it to the right of point off the outer half. Devon Conway dives to that side and makes a sharp stop.
This is on a length, around off. This one flies off the deck. Oshada Fernando is pinged high on his pads.
FOUR! EDGY! Matt Henry dishes it full, in the channel, inviting the drive and Oshada Fernando falls for it. The ball takes a thick inside edge, skips the stumps and runs down to the fine leg fence.
Good-length, on off, shapes away a touch. Oshada Fernando tries to defend it but it goes to the slip cordon off the outside edge. It does not carry though as it is played with soft hands.
A length ball, drifting down leg. Oshada Fernando comes forward and tries to clip it away but misses.
Fuller, on leg. Oshada Fernando clips it to square leg for one.
Full length, on off. Oshada Fernando gets on his front foot and blocks it out awkwardly.
It is a short ball, on leg stump. Oshada Fernando gets inside the line and makes  a good leave.
Much fuller, on off. Oshada Fernando presses forward and pushes it to mid on.
It is full, tailing into the pads. Oshada Fernando eases it towards mid on.
Tim Southee goes full, on off. Oshada Fernando gets it to the leg side off the inner half.
A short one, wide of off. Oshada Fernando shuffles across and makes the leave.

Dimuth Karunaratne finally gets off the mark here. It is a length ball, on off. Dimuth Karunaratne taps it to cover off the bottom half of the blade. There is a bit of hesitation at first but eventually he gets to the other end.
Good length, on fifth stump. This one flies off the deck. Oshada Fernando makes a good leave.
Sharp running! It is full and on off. Oshada Fernando gets on his front foot and fends it to the off side. He is quick to get across. Good signs to build a partnership.
A length ball, on off, nips back in off the deck. Dimuth Karunaratne gets pinged on his pads but the umpire does not raise his finger.
Length, outside off. Blocked away.
Shorter this time, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne lets it be.
Tim Southee hurls a length ball, outside off, swinging away. Oshada Fernando does not go after it.

It is a short ball, on middle. Oshada Fernando swivels and pulls it hard behind square on the leg side. Matt Henry runs to his left in the deep and saves a certain boundary with an exceptional drive. They take two runs.
Tim Southee serves a length ball, on fourth stump. Oshada Fernando shuffles across and tries to block it away but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Tim Southee now goes wide of the crease and dishes a length ball, around off. It swings away sharply. Oshada Fernando now tries to drive it through the line but gets beaten.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Tim Southee draws the first blood. The skipper has set the tone here certainly. Oshada Fernando's gritty knock comes to an end in an unlucky manner though. He will be gutted with himself. Tim Southee goes full, sliding down leg side. Oshada Fernando tries to flick it away but gets a feather on it. Tom Blundell gets to his left and takes a sharp catch. An appeal in made for caught behind and the umpire raises his dreaded finger.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Tim Southee

Commentary: It is a length ball, outside off. It extracts some extra bounce off the surface. Kusal Mendis leaves it alone.
Matt Henry serves it on a length, on off. gets it to come back in, with some extra bounce. Dimuth Karunaratne takes a hit on his thigh pads.
This one is angling across, on a good length. Dimuth Karunaratne has no shot to offer.
Beaten! Matt Henry hurls in a full-length ball, on fourth stump. Dimuth Karunaratne steps forward and tries to drive it through the line but misses.
Swing and a miss! Good length, angling across, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne stays on his back foot and goes for the punch, gets no bat on ball though.
This one is on a length, attacking the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne clips it towards short leg.

Matt Henry once again asking the right questions here. An appeal is made for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. Tim Southee takes the review after consulting his players. Although, the review does not go their way as it confirms that the ball is pitching outside leg. New Zealand lose a review here. It is a length ball, on leg stump. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to flick it away but misses to wear it on his pads.
Tim Southee fires in a full one, on off. Kusal Mendis blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, outside off, left alone.

Kusal Mendis survives. He makes the most of the review here. It is a length ball, outside off, nips back in sharply. Kusal Mendis tries to defend it but misses. He gets pinged on his pads. Tim Southee appeals and the finger goes up. Mendis takes the review and the Ball Tracking confirms that the ball is going above the stumps.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, outside off. Kusal Mendis looks to chase it but misses.

Woah! So close! Dimuth Karunaratne almost gives away his wicket here. It is a length ball, on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne steps way outside his crease and tucks it to the leg side. Henry Nicholls is sharp to react, he gets to his right and gathers the ball, although he fails to score a direct-hit at the striker's end. Dimuth Karunaratne gets a lifeline here.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Fortunate boundary for Dimuth Karunaratne. It is a sharp bouncer, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the pull, but it flies off the top-edge and goes to third man for four runs.
Length and on off. Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to the off side for a single.
Good length, wide of off. Kusal Mendis looks to chase it but misses.
Fuller this time on off. Mendis gets behind the line and blocks solidly.
Fuller length outside off. Karunaratne prods and pushes it toward mid-off.
Blair Tickner comes 'round the wicket and angles it in, full and on off. Dimuth Karunaratne tucks it to the leg side.
BEATEN! Blair Tickner now angles in a length ball, but gets it to move away this time. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to hit it through the line but is no where near the ball.
Full and on off. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles and blocks it out.
FOUR! Nice placement. Blair Tickner fires it full, attacking the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket for four runs.

Blair Tickner now dishes a length ball, outside off and gets it to jag back in. Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders his arms at it and gets pinged on his pads. He can trust the bounce though on this surface.
A length ball, outside off. Kusal Mendis lets it be.
Outside off, left alone once again.
FOUR! Well played! It is overpitched, on fourth stump. Kusal Mendis opens the face late and steers it down to the third man fence.
On a length, in the channel. Kusal Mendis tries to block it but does so inside the line.
A length ball, on fourth stump. It flies off the deck. Tom Blundell gathers it above his head behind the sticks.
Good length, wide of off. Kusal Mendis lets it be.
Short and around off from round the wicket. Karunaratne lets it go .
On a good length and outside off. Left alone by Dimuth Karunaratne.
Back of a length angling in around off. Karunaratne shoulders arms on this one.
Touch fuller this time around off. Karunaratne tucks into the onside.
Good length ball around off. Karunaratne strides forward and defends.
Short ball angling down the leg. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it and lets it go through.
FOUR! On a good length angling down the leg. Mendis covers the line and gets an inside edge that runs down toward the fine leg region for a boundary.
FOUR MORE! Back of a length outside off. Mendis flays at it as it flies away over the slips and gully region and runs down toward the third man region for a boundary.
On a good length just outside off. Mendis defends it with soft hands toward the slip.
FOUR! Overpitched around off. Mendis strides forward and drives it nicely off the front foot through extra cover and mid-off for a third boundary in the over.
Back of a length angling in around the leg peg. Mendis tucks it toward deep backward square leg for a couple.
Good length ball angling in and nipping away after pitching. Mendis prods forward and gets beaten on the outside edge. A beauty to finish the over.
Back of a length outside off. Left alone by Karunaratne.
Good length ball angling in around off. Karunaratne watchfully lets it go through to the keeper.
On a good length around off. Karunaratne strides forward and gets a thick outside edge along the carpet toward the gully region for a single.
Back of a length takes off after pitching and nips away just outside off. Mendis pushes at it as the ball goes past beating the outside edge.
Fuller this time, and Mendis defends toward cover-point.
Short and angling down the leg. Mendis ducks under it and lets it go.
Fuller length coming in. Karunaratne works it past the short leg and toward the square leg for a single.
On a good length down the leg. Mendis helps himself toward fine leg and eases for a single.
Edged and Four! Full and outside off. Karunaratne goes hard for the drive and it flies over the gully region as the ball races toward the third-man fence for a boundary.
On a good length just outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne plays it with soft hands toward covers and crosses for a quick single.
FOUR! Full and outside off. Mendis pushes at it and gets it through the backward point region as it races to the fence for another boundary.
FOUR! CLASSIC! Full and overpitched on off. Mendis plays with a straight face of the bat and drives it beautifully down the ground toward the long on fence for four.
Back of a length around off. Karunaratne tucks it toward mid on.
Hard length just outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne covers the line and defends solidly.
Full and on the stumps. Dimuth Karunaratne drives it past the bowler and through the mid-on region. Kane Williamson gives the chase and saves one for his side.
Full and on off. Mendis drives along the carpet off the outside edge toward the man at the backward point.

FOUR! Easy pickings! A low full toss down the leg. Mendis gently chips it through the mid-wicket as it runs down toward the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary. 50-run stand up with this boundary as well.
A sharp bouncer! Short and angling into the batter. Mendis ducks out of it.
On a good length just outside off and angling in. Dimuth Karunaratne prods forward and defends.
Full and outside off, driven to covers.
On a good length and just outside off. Karunaratne outside edges along the turf toward the third slip.
Bowls it a tad fuller this time around off. Karunaratne prods and defends.
On a good length and angling across, Left alone by Dimuth Karunaratne.
Full length on the pads. Karunaratne flicks it toward mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length delivery just outside off. Mendis watchfully lets it go.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off. Mendis cuts it nicely through the cover region for a cracking boundary.
Full and swings back in around off. Mendis goes for the drive and inside edges through the mid-wicket region for a couple.
FOUR MORE! Easy pickings! Short and angling down the leg. Mendis pulls from the bottom of the bat and helps it away toward the deep backward square leg region for another boundary.
Full and outside off, driven to short covers.
FOUR! BANG! Short and outside off. Mendis slashes hard and uppercuts it over the slips as it flies down to the third man region for a boundary. 14 coming off Wagner's first over.
On a good length just outside off, left alone.
Play and a miss! Full and outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne pushes at it for the drive and gets beaten on the drive.
On a good length and angling in. Karunaratne lobs it up toward the short mid-wicket region off the inside part of the bat.
Very full and on the stumps, driven toward mid-on.
Bowls it full and outside off this time. Left alone by Karunaratne.
Fuller length around off. Karunaratne inside edges it toward square leg for none.
Short and angling down the leg. Mendis takes it on and pulls it past the short fine leg for a single.
Dishes it full and down the leg. Karunaratne is unmoved as Blundell dives to his right and collects it.
On a good length nipping outside off. Karunaratne prods at it as the ball passes the outside edge.
Full on the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it nicely through the square leg region for a comfortable three.
Back of a length on the leg. Mendis tucks it toward the square leg.
Short and down the leg. Mendis pulls along the carpet to the man at a short fine leg.
Hard length angling in around off. Karunaratne prods forward and gets beaten on the inside, taking a thud on the pad.

Edged and Four! On a good length outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne prods forward and gets an outside edge along the carpet that goes through the gap between slip and the gully region down toward the third man for a boundary.
Full length, on middle and leg. Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket for three runs. Top-class running.
FOUR! Easy pickings. It is full, sliding down leg. Kusal Mendis clips it down to fine leg for four runs. Also, FIFTY is up for Kusal Mendis in no time here.
Length, on the pads, clipped to the leg side for one.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it.
FOUR! Short and down the leg. Mendis takes it on and pulls it hard toward the fine leg region. One bounce and into the ropes.
WIDE! Bowls it very short and down the leg. Wide signaled by the umpire.
Short again and Mendis pulls it nicely along the carpet toward the deep backward square leg region for an easy two.
FOUR! Into the gap! Wagner continues to bowl short and around the stump. Mendis takes it on and pulls it toward the long leg region for yet another boundary.
Back of a length around off. Mendis shuffles and defends it onto the pitch.
Short and just outside off. Mendis guides it uppishly toward the third man on a bounce for one.
On a good length around off. Karunaratne prods and defends toward covers.
FOUR! Full and down the leg. Mendis has picked up nicely and flicks it off the pads as the ball rockets toward the deep backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Very full and on the stumps. Mendis has flicked this through the mid-wicket region for a couple. The 100-run stand is up between Mendis and Karunaratne.
Short and outside off. Mendis goes for the uppercut and misses.
FOUR! Short again and gets stuck in the pitch. Mendis flays at it as it flies off the gap toward third man for a boundary.
Back of a length around the leg. Mendis tucks it toward mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off. Karunaratne pushes it toward mid-off and picks a quick single. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Southee comes from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Another sighter! Fuller, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne makes another leave.
FOUR! Exceptional shot. It is fuller, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne steps down and creams it past mid off for four runs. Dimuth Karunaratne has put his foot on the gas early in this session now.
It is pitched up, on off. Dimuth Karunaratne strokes it to mid off.
Good length, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders his arms at it.
Touch fuller, but way outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne lets it be.
Matt Henry hurls in a length ball, on off. Kusal Mendis blocks it into the deck.
Back of a length, in the channel. This one flies off the deck. Kusal Mendis tries to have a poke at it but misses.
JAFFA! Matt Henry goes full, on fourth stump. Kusal Mendis is caught inside the crease this time. He prods and tries to block it away but does so inside the line.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Kusal Mendis tries to flick it away but is a bit early into his shot.
Fuller and on off. Kusal Mendis eases it to cover and gets to the other end.
A dot to end a probing over from Henry. It is a length ball, angling across. Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone.

A loud appeal for caught behind! Tim Southee serves a length ball, around off. The ball nips away a touch with some extra bounce. Kusal Mendis fails to defend it away. The ball brushes the back leg and goes to the keeper.
BEATEN! A bit fuller this time, in the channel. Kusal Mendis gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and on off. Kusal Mendis pulls it to mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Full length, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne steps forward and knocks it down the park. It goes past mid on and races away to the fence. The stand moves to 116 runs.
It is full, down leg. Dimuth Karunaratne fails to flick it away.
Matt Henry gets this one to nips back in from outside off, on a length. Kusal Mendis gets pinged on his thigh pads as he is unable to flick it away.
Matt Henry angles it in, full and on off. It nips away off the deck to beat Kusal Mendis on the outside edge.
FOUR! Good shot. It is pitched up, on off. Kusal Mendis shuffles and hits it down to long on for a boundary.
Full, in-line with the stumps. Kusal Mendis blocks it on his front foot.
Henry serves it full and on off. Kusal Mendis leans in and pushes it firmly past mid off for three runs.
Matt Henry goes full again, on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne wrists it towards deep mid-wicket. The batters have enough time to come back for three runs.
Southee angles in a length ball, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne gets squared up but the ball sneaks past the outside edge. It goes into the slip cordon off his back leg.
Outside off, left alone.
Tim Southee goes a bit fuller, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles a long way across to make the leave.
Length ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Five dots on the trot. It is full, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne steps across and pushes it to mid off.

FOUR! This boundary will surely spoil the over for Tim Southee. It is full, angled in around off. Dimuth Karunaratne shimmies down the wicket and plays the on drive to perfection. It races past mid on and goes into the ropes.
A length ball, in the channel, shaping away. Kusal Mendis gets beaten as he tries to after it.
Good length, around off. Kusal Mendis gets it to gully off the outside edge. It does not carry.

A loud appealfor caught behind! Matt Henry serves it short, sliding down leg. Kusal Mendis swivels and goes for the pull shot. Tom Blundell moves to his left and takes a sharp catch above his head. Blundell is pretty confident that he has got hiis man here. Matt Henry appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Tim Southee takes the review. The UltraEdge though confirms that there is no bat involved. New Zealand have burned another review here.
Length, on the pads. Kusal Mendis flicks it though square leg for three runs.
Matt Henry now comes from 'round the wicket. It is a length ball, angled in on off. Dimuth Karunaratne gets it to the slip cordon off the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off. It nips back in. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles across and shoulders his arms at it. He taken a blow high on his pads.
Full length, on off. Mendis gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball goes to Michael Bracewell at third slip.
Length ball, on off. Mendis fends it out to point.
A length ball, on the pads. Mendis blocks it to the off side.
Much fuller, around off. Mendis blocks it out watchfully.
Length, wide of off. This one nips back in a long way. Kusal Mendis tries to flick it away but misses. He takes a blow high on his thigh pads.
Tim Southee goes full and on off. It flies off the deck. Kusal Mendis tries to block. He takes a hit on his pads.
Length, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles and flicks it past square leg for a single.
Length ball, in the channel. Kusal Mendis gets beaten on the outside edge as he fails to work it away.
Matt Henry spills this one down the leg side. Kusal Mendis is unable to put it away.
Full length, on leg, blocked out.
Matt Henry angles in a length ball, on off. It  shapes away sharply off the deck. Matt Henry has his hands on his head here. He cannot believe how has Kusal Mendis not nicked it behind.
Fuller, sliding down leg. Kusal Mendis clips it through mid-wicket for two runs. 150 is up for Sri Lanka. These two batters have picked things up from where they left off.
Short ball, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne pulls it to deep square leg for a single. That will be his FIFTY. Dimuth Karunaratne is certainly playing a captain's knock here.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter, outside off. Mendis punches it to point off his back foot.
Full length, on off. Kusal Mendis prods and blocks it out watchfully.

OUT! LBW! Tim Southee appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Elation for New Zealand, as Kusal Mendis walks without taking the review, so the celebrations continue. Tim Southee hurls in a length ball, outside off. The ball nips back in a long way. Kusal Mendis goes deep inside the crease and shoulders his arm at it. He offers no shot and takes a blow on his pads. The umpire agrees this time.  Tim Southee has picked up his second wicket now.
Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary: Fuller, tailing into the pads, Angelo Mathews tucks it to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
A sharp bumper, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne initially thinks about pulling it away but withdraws from his shot.
Short one, wide of off. Left alone by Dimuth Karunaratne.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Matt Henry is finally rewarded for his exceptional bowling so far in this innings. New Zealand are back in the game with both the set batters back in the dressing room. It is a full-length ball, outside off. It nips away a touch. Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the booming drive but only gets a thick outside edge. Tom Latham takes a sharp catch at second slip.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Matt Henry

Commentary: Fuller, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Good length, on fifth stump. Dinesh Chandimal lets it be.
Good length, on the pads. Angelo Mathews tucks it to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
A well-directed short ball, on off. Angelo Mathews sways away from the line.
Full length, just outside off. Angelo Mathews presses forward and blocks it out firmly.
Outside off, left alone.
Full length, just outside off. Angelo Mathews gets it to mid on off the inner half.
FOUR LEG BYES! It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Dinesh Chandimal fails to flick it away. The ball brushes his pads and runs down to the third man fence.
Full length, tailing into the pads. Dinesh Chandimal wears a blow on his pads as he fails to flick it away.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal gets beaten on the inside edge to get pinged high on his pads.
Full, on off, blocked out.
Length ball, on top of off. Dinesh Chandimal shuffles and eases it to mid on.
Length and on off, blocked out watchfully.
Full and nipping a tad bit outside off. Left alone by Mathews.
On a good length around the middle and off. Mathews defends off the backfoot.
Good length again around off. Mathews gets behind the line and defends onto the pitch.
Continues to bowl in the channel around off. Angelo Mathews drops it into the offside.
Fuller this time and Mathews pushes it toward mid-off.
Full again on off. Mathews prods and defends.
Good length ball outside off. Chandimal fends it toward the gully region.
Tad fuller this time and on off. Chandimal defends into the onside.
Good length ball nipping into the batter. Chandimal prods and inside edges toward the fine leg for a single to get off the mark.
On a good length and nipping away outside off. Angelo Mathews plays at it and gets beaten.
Back of a length just outside off, Mathews feels for it as the ball zips past the outside edge.
The length is a fraction fuller this time and the ball shapes away sharply to beat Mathews on the outside edge.
On a good length and nipping into the batter. Chandimal prods forward and gets an inside edge toward square leg for one.
On a length and Mathews defends it forward.
Back of a length on the leg peg, Mathews tucks it off the pad and toward deep square leg for a couple.
Length ball, around off, defended out.
Full on off. Mathews defends it off the front foot.
On a good length around off. Mathews tucks it toward mid-wicket.
Back of a length back around off. Chandimal jumps around and fends it forward.
Length, on leg, clipped to the leg side.
On a good length outside off. Chandimal guides it toward the gully region.
Back of a length on off. Chandimal defends it forward.
Hard length into the surface. Chandimal fends it away.
Dishes a full ball, almost a yorker length on off. Chandimal pushes it back toward the bowler.
Back of a length on off. Mathews bunts it back at Mitchell.
Pulls the length back a tad bit outside off. Mathews fends it toward covers.
On a good length around the middle and leg stump line. Mathews fends and gets a leading edge along the carpet toward the point.
Full and outside off. Mathews drives it straight toward mid-off.
Bouncer and outside off. Mathews sways away from it.
Back of a length outside off. Angelo Mathews watchfully lets it go.
On a good length angling into the batter. Chandimal taps it toward mid-wicket and crosses for a single.
Short of a length angling into the batter. Mathews awkwardly fends it off the splice of the blade. The bat is broken here for Angelo Mathews and he has called in for a new one.
Short and outside off. Mathews lets it go through.
Full and on the stumps. Nicely worked away to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Short of a length outside off. Left alone by Mathews.
Back of a length, and nips back into the batter. Angelo Mathews misses the tuck and takes a thud on the pad.
Full and outside off. Chandimal hits hard, and drives, and Southee makes a brilliant dive to his left and stops the boundary.
Length ball angling into the off and middle. Chandimal pushes it towards silly mid-on. They waned a single but decided against it.
Full on off, driven to covers.
On a good length around off. Chandimal defends it forward.
Goes short this time and Chandimal takes it on and pulls it toward deep square leg region and falls in front of the fielder.
Good length on the middle and leg. Mathews turns it toward square leg for a single to end the over.
Back of a length angling down the leg. Left alone by Mathews.
Back of a length again on the stump line. Mathews fends it uppishly off the pad toward mid-wicket for one.
Good length ball on off. Chandimal defends it forward.
Hard length outside off. Chandimal dabs it into the offside for one.
SIX! BANG! Short and angling into the batter. Angelo Mathews pulls and helps it over the fine leg region for a maximum.
Back of a length and Mathews tucks it off the pad toward fine leg for a leg bye.
On a good length on off, Mathews presses forward and defends.
FOUR! Up and Over! Short and outside off. Angelo Mathews guides it uppishly over the slip and toward the third man region for a boundary.
Back of a length on the pads, tucked away to square leg for one.
Full and on off. Chandimal drives it to mid-off.
Short and outside off. Chandimal pulls it in front of the wicket and toward the deep mid-wicket fence for a couple.
Good length on off. Chandimal presses forward and defends.
On a good length and on-off, Mathews defends off the front foot.
Full and on the leg peg. Mathews clips it off the pad toward the mid-wicket region for a couple.
Back of a length angling in. Mathews plays across and takes a thud on the pad.
On a good length outside off, punched into covers.
FOUR! Angelo Mathews is getting into his groove. It is a short ball, on off. Angelo Mathews pulls it down to wide of long on for a cracking boundary.
Back of a length on the leg stump, tucked into the onside.
On a good length and nipping back into the batter. Chandimal prods forward and wears on the rib cage.
Short and outside off. Chandimal punches it to the point.
Full and outside off. Chandimal drives hard and mistimes it toward Southee at mid-off.
Full and angling on the pads. Chandimal clips this uppishly toward deep mid-wicket for one.
Bowls a good length ball that nips back and hits Mathews high on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Full and on the legs. Mathews works it nicely through the mid-wicket region as it races into the fence for four.
On a good length and nips a tad away. Chandimal goes for the drive and gets beaten.
Back of a length outside off. Chandimal punches off the backfoot through extra covers for an easy three.
Short and pulled away along the carpet toward deep square leg for one.
Back of a length down the leg. Chandimal tucks it off the pad towards fine leg for one.

Bowls it full and on the middle and off stump line. Mathews plays across the line and gets wrapped in front. The Kiwis appeal and the umpire is unmoved. Southee has gone upstairs for the review. There is a little spike on the bat and NZ have burnt all their reviews.
Back of a length, going down leg. Left alone.
On a good length around off. Chandimal defends off the front foot.
Full and outside off, driven to covers.
Back of a length around off. Chandimal fends it toward mid-on.
On a good length outside off. Left alone.
Edged and short of first slip. Bowls it full and outside off. Chandimal drives and edges it on a bounce to Bracewell at first slip.
Full and on the middle and leg. Chandimal works it toward short mid-wicket.
LEG BYE! Full and down the leg. Mathews clips it off the pad toward fine leg for a leg bye.
Back of a length outside off. Chandimal punches it toward mid-off.
FOUR! Up and Over! Short and outside off. Chandimal hangs back and plays it uppishly toward the third man region for a boundary.
FOUR MORE! Overpitched outside off. Chandimal drives it uppishly past the bowler and through mid-off as it runs down to the long-off fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Take that! Three in a row! Full and outside off. Chandimal plays it late and drives it nicely through the cover region for a boundary.
Back of a length, and nips into the batter. Chandimal fends as it deflects off the thigh pad and lobs to the keeper. And That's time for Tea.
On a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, outside off. Angelo Mathews drives it into covers.
Length, on the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it through square leg for a single.
Wagner comes 'round the wicket and angles in a full-length delivery, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal makes a sharp leave.
Much fuller, wide of off, coming in late. Dinesh Chandimal has no shot to offer.
Neil Wagner hurls in a good-length delivery, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal shoulders his arms at it.
Tim Southee starts with a length ball, in the channel, its nips away a touch. Angelo Mathews tries to have a poke at but gets beaten.
FOUR! Lovely shot. It is full, angled into the pads. Angelo Mathews lifts his back leg and flicks it through the gap at mid-wicket for four runs.
Full, on off, Angelo Mathews fends it to covers.
An outswinger, full and around off. Angelo Mathews pushes it gently towards mid off.
Tim Southee goes full and on off. Angelo Mathews dabs it out.
It drifts in, on a length, around off. The nips away a touch. Angelo Mathews gets squared up and gets it to the slip cordon off the outside edge.
Good length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller, angled in, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal shuffles and blocks it out.
Fraction short, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal sways back a bit and cuts it hard towards backward point.
FOUR! Incredible shot. It is a short ball, wide of off. Dinesh Chandimal rides the bounce this time and cuts it past gully. It races away.
Dinesh Chandimal drives this full one to mid off.
Outside off. Dinesh Chandimal lets it be. It has been a good comeback by Neil Wagner after an expensive start in the morning.
Length and on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it with full face.
It is full, around off. Angelo Mathews eases it back to the bowler.
Much fuller, in the channel. Angelo Mathews blocks it on his front foot.
Tim Southee hurls in a length ball, in the channel. Angelo Mathews tries to have a poke at it but misses.
Length, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Fraction short, wide of off. Angelo Mathews prods and shoulders his arms at it.
FOUR! Crunched! It is pitched up, wide of off. Dinesh Chandimal lunges and drives it through covers for four runs.
Outside off, Dinesh Chandimal lets it be.
Another dot now, as Dinesh Chandimal leaves this length ball which is served outside off.
Full, angled into the pads. Dinesh Chandimal clips it behind square on the leg side. Two taken.
A sharp bumper, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Dinesh Chandimal gets the second boundary of the over. Short, wide of off. Dinesh Chandimal rides the bounce and hammers it through covers for a fine boundary.
Short and just outside off. Mathews ducks under it.
Fuller this time and on off. Mathews defends it forward.
Short again, and Mathews ducks underneath this one.
On a good length around off. Mathews gets behind and bunts back at the bowler.
Full on off. Mathews prods and defends toward the onside.
Full and on off. Mathews presses forward and blocks it.
Short and around the leg peg. Chandimal pulls it to deep backward square leg for one.
Short again and on the leg stump. Mathews ducks under it.
Continues to bowl short and this time outside off. Angelo Mathews sways away from this one.
Short and half pulls it toward the square leg.
FOUR! Bumper outside off. Angelo Mathews makes room and uppercuts it over the point region as the ball rolls into the fence for four runs.
Short again and down the leg. Mathews ducks under it.

OUT! EDGED and TAKEN! Full and outside off. Chandimal reaches out for it and gets a thick edge through to Latham at the second slip who grabs it with ease. Southee breaks the stand and gets his third. Chandimal departs for a well made 39.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Tim Southee

Commentary: Short of a length outside off. de Silva rides on top and guides it through the gap wide of point for a couple.
On a good length outside off. de Silva fends it toward the gully region.
Full, on off. de Silva has driven it back to the bowler.
Good length on off. de Silva defends it forward.
Back of a length outside off. Left alone by de Silva.
FOUR! Short and on the leg stump line. Mathews gets into the position and pulls it past the backward square leg as it rolls into the fence for four.
Short and angling outside off. Left alone by Mathews.
Another short ball, on off, Mathews ducks under it.
Short again, outside off. Mathews pulls it toward mid-on.
Short and down the leg. Mathews helps it toward deep backward square leg for one.
FOUR! Short again and de Silva pulls it to the long leg region for a boundary to end the over.
Back of a length, nipping back into the batter. Mathews hangs back and wears on the pad.
Full and outside off. Angelo Mathews drives it toward mid-off for one.
FOUR! Full and on the middle and leg. de Silva clips it nicely through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Back of a length, nips back into the batter. de Silva looks to work it away but gets hit on the pad.
Much fuller this time, on off. de Silva prods and defends.
On a good length and nipping in just outside off. de Silva shoulders arms on this.
Blair Tickner starts with a full one, around off. It nips away off the deck. Angelo Mathews fends it to covers.

BEATEN! Ohhs and ahhs from the fielders behind the sticks. Blair Tickner angles in a length ball, in the channel. It jags away after hitting the deck. Angelo Mathews tries to smack it through the line but misses it completely.
Fuller, angled into the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket and crosses.
Blair Tickner bends his back hard this time and dishes a short ball, on top of off. Dhananjaya de Silva stays inside the crease and taps it to point.
A yorker-length delivery, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets it to mid on off the bottom half of the blade.
It is fuller, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets it to point off the outer half.
Matt Henry goes full, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews tries to tickle it fine but misses.
Much fuller, on off. Angelo Mathews presses forward and defends it back to the bowler.
It is full, tailing into the pads. Angelo Mathews tries to flick it away but ends up play all over it. He gets pinged on his pads. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone by Angelo Mathews.
JUST SHORT! It is a short ball, on top of off. It climbs on the batter. Angelo Mathews gets his bat high to block it away. It lobs off the outer half but lands just in front of gully.
Fuller and on off, blocked out.
Blair Tickner now dishes a length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Dhananjaya de Silva prods to defend it out but the ball goes past the outside edge.
It is full, on leg. Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it through mid-wicket. Devon Conway gives it a long chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Outside off, left alone.
It is fuller, on off. Angelo Mathews gets it towards mid on. They take one as there is a misfield.

A short ball, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva rides the bounce and pulls it towards deep square leg. Dhananjaya de Silva plays an uncontrolled shot but is lucky to see it fall in no man's land. The batters take a single.
Fuller, straying on the pads. Dhananjaya de Silva clips it through mid-wicket for a brace.
On a length, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva fends it to the off side.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Dhananjaya de Silva hops and nudges it to square leg for one.

Cheers from the crowd! Angelo Mathews soaks himself in applause as he racks up 7000 runs in his Test career. It is full and on off. Angelo Mathews tucks it to mid on. There is a misfiled and the batters take a couple.

OUT! CAUGHT! Matt Henry finds the breakthrough and gets his second wicket. Angelo Mathews holes out after achieving his milestone. Herny fires it full, in the channel and gets it to jag away off the deck. Angelo Mathews presses forward and tries to block it away. Although, he only manages to get a thick outside edge. It flies towards first slip and Daryl Mitchell stationed there makes no mistake.
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Matt Henry

Commentary: Length and on off, defended out solidly.
Full length, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva dabs it to point.
Blair Tickner dishes a length ball, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva shuffles to block it away, but it hits the bottom half of the blade and bounces past the stumps.
Short one, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
It is angled in, full and on off. Niroshan Dickwella eases it back to the bowler.
A length ball, that comes back in from outside off. Niroshan Dickwella gets an inside edge on his pads. They cross for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva pulls it to mid on off the toe-end. It almost carries.
On a good length angling around off. Dickwella gets behind and defends.
FOUR! Full and outside off. Niroshan Dickwella drives this uppishly through the backward point region for a boundary.
Back of a length angling outside off. Left alone by Dickwella.
Fuller length this time outside off. Dickwella lets it go through to the keeper.
Short of length ball on off, Dickwella rises on his toes and fends it down.
Hard length around off. Dickwella defends off the backfoot.
Full on the leg peg. de Silva clips toward mid-on.
Back of a length on off. de Silva gets behind the line and defends.
Good length outside off. de Silva dabs it toward the gully region.
Full on off, driven back toward the bowler.
Full again and driven towards mid-off.
On a good length outside off, de Silva dabs it toward point.
Michael Bracewell starts off with a low full toss on off. Niroshan Dickwella gets down to paddle but bunts it into the onside.
Dickwella takes it on the full and paddles again toward the short fine leg region for a couple.
Tossed up on off. Niroshan Dickwella prods and defends.

OUT! LBW! Michael Bracewell picks up a wicket in his very first over. Just what the doctor ordered for New Zealand. It is tossed up, full and on middle. Niroshan Dickwella gets low and goes for the sweep. He misses to get rapped on the pads. There is an appeal and the finger goes up. Niroshan Dickwella takes the review but the Ball Tracking shows three reds. Sri Lanka lose a review and a wicket as well.
Howout: lbw b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Tossed up outside off, driven to covers.
Full and outside off, Kasun Rajitha pushes it toward point.
Shortish around off. de Silva shimmies down and bunts it toward mid-on.
Short again and outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva swats it toward mid-on.
On a good length around off. de Silva turns it toward the square leg off the inside part of the blade.
On a good length and outside off. Left alone by Rajitha.
Full and outside off. Kasun Rajitha goes for the drive and missses.
Back of a length just outside off, Kasun Rajitha shoulders arms on this one.
Full on off. de Silva shuffles and sweeps it nicely toward fine leg region for a couple.
FOUR! Full and outside off. de Silva lofts it inside out over the covers as the ball trickles away a couple of bounces into the ropes.
Full on off. de Silva prods and defends.
Full again on the stumps. de Silva plays the reverse sweep through the short third for another two.
de Silva shimmies down and takes it on the full to edge it through the short third region for a single.
Full on off. Rajitha prods and defends.
Full length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva dabs it to point for a single.
Back of a length, in the channel. Kasun Rajitha lets it be.
Blair Tickner bends his back hard now and serves a short ball, on off. Kasun Rajitha sways away.
A length ball, around off, nipping away. Kasun Rajitha tries to go hunting after it but get beaten on the outside edge.
Woah! Blair Tickner angles in a length ball, on off. It nips away a touch. Kasun Rajitha goes back and tries to block it away but misses.
Shorter, wide of off. Kasun Rajitha leaves it alone for the keeper. A maiden now for Blair Tickner.
Full length, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva gets it to mid on off the inner half.
Good-length ball, angling across with some extra bounce. Dhananjaya de Silva tries to cut it away.
Outside off, left alone.
Full length, angled across, outside off. DDS leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length, wide of off. Dhananjaya de Silva lets it be.
A length ball, wide outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva throws the kitchen sink at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Up and over! Blair Tickner dishes a full one, on off. Kasun Rajitha lofts it over the bowler's head for four runs.

Blair Tickner thinks he got a wicket here but Kasun Rajitha saves himself with a great review here. It is full, tailing into the pads. Kasun Rajitha gets pinged on his pads. There is an appeal and the finger goes up. The Ball Tracking though confirms that the ball is missing the wickets.
Fuller, on off, blocked out.
Full length, on off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it out solidly.
On off, pushed to cover.
SIX! All the way! Blair Tickner serves a short ball, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva waits for it and launches it over the backward point fence.
FOUR! Kasun Rajitha gets his second boundary. It is full, angling across, wide of off. Kasun Rajitha throws the kitchen at it. The ball flies down to third man for four runs.

Fuller, on off. Kasun Rajitha gets under it and hits it high in the air. The ball goes to the right of mid off. Tim Southee tries to get under it but could not spot the ball in the end. They take one.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva makes some room and slashes hard it. The ball goes through to the keeper.
FOUR! Exceptional shot! 299 now up for the visitors. It is a full-length ball, just outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and creams it past mid off for a fine boundary.
Length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva makes a leave.
Shorter, on off. Kasun Rajitha goes back and blocks it to the off side.
Fuller, on off. Kasun Rajitha drives it to the left of mid off.
It is tossed up, full and outside off. Kasun Rajitha tries to hit it through the line. The ball goes down to third man off the outside edge. They take two.
FOUR! What a shot! It is floated and full, outside off. Kasun Rajitha uses his feet and drives it through the gap at covers. The ball races away to the fence.
Goes full, on off, blocked out on the front foot.
It is much fuller and quicker, on middle and leg. Kasun Rajitha defends it out watchfully.

FOUR! Dhananjaya de Silva and Sri Lanka are underway on Day 2! Blair Tickner starts with a full delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva leans forward and drives it back past the bowler for the first boundary of the day.
On a length around off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and keeps it out.
Good-length delivery outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva hangs back and fends this one towards the second slip.

Back of a length on off by Blair Tickner, Dhananjaya de Silva stays on the back foot and punches it to cover. Calls his partner for a single and Kasun Rajitha obliges. Michael Bracewell hits at the striker's end but Rajitha was safely in. The ball deflects off the stumps towards mid-wicket and batters sneak in an extra run.
Good-length around off, Dhananjaya de Silva works this one to cover and takes a single.
FOUR! Full and drifting at the pads, Kasun Rajitha clips this one off his toes towards the deep backward square leg region for a boundary. A good first over for Sri Lanka.
Starts with a good-length delivery outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva shoulders arms and lets it go.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Tim Southee strikes in his first over and removes Dhananjaya de Silva! Bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to go through the off side and punches at the delivery away from the body. Gets an outside edge that flies behind the wicket and Tom Blundell dives to his right and takes a good tumbling catch. An early wicket on Day 2 for New Zealand.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Tim Southee

Commentary: Touch fuller and angling in on middle and leg, Prabath Jayasuriya goes for the clip but misses and wears it on the front pad.
On a good length in the channel outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Beauty! Good-length delivery around off, nips away after pitching, Prabath Jayasuriya hangs his bat out to defend but does not connect.
Full and at the stumps, Prabath Jayasuriya clips this one from the crease to square leg for a single.
Back of a length outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya dabs this one along the ground to gully.
Banged in short and at the batter, Prabath Jayasuriya takes his eyes off the ball and awkwardly fends it to silly mid off.
Goes back of a length again and on leg, Prabath Jayasuriya tucks this one to the left of the keeper and takes a single.
Short of a length on off, Kasun Rajitha sways away and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Another bumper on off by Blair Tickner, Kasun Rajitha backs away and leaves the ball alone.
Length delivery on off, Kasun Rajitha clears his front leg to go down the ground but gets an inside edge back onto his pads.

Shortish delivery aimed at the batter, Prabath Jayasuriya looks to help this one fine but gets cramped for room. Gets it off his gloves and the ball flies to the left of the keeper. Tom Blundell shuffles to his left and gets fingertips on it.. The ball though rolls down to fine leg and batters cross for a couple of runs.
Fuller in the channel outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya shoulders arms and lets it go.
Goes short again and on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya ducks underneath and leaves the ball alone.
Fuller and on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya gets behind the line and clips it to mid-wicket for a dot.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Prabath Jayasuriya nudges this one towards square leg and collects a single.
Full and outside off, Kasun Rajitha reaches out to the delivery and drives it to cover for a run.
Back of a length around off, Kasun Rajitha stays leg side of the ball and pushes this one a bit uppishly towards backward point.
Lands this one full and outside off, Kasun Rajitha goes for the drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fullish delivery on leg, Kasun Rajitha clips this one off his toes to fine leg for a single.
Good-length on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya works this one past short leg and takes a single.
Banged in short around off, Kasun Rajitha sways away and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
WIDE! Another bumper on middle, Kasun Rajitha lets it go. The ball sails over the batter's head and the umpire signals a wide.
Good-length delivery outside off, Kasun Rajitha shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
Full and angling at the pads, Prabath Jayasuriya clips this one wide of mid on and takes a single.
Keeps this one on a good-length around off, Kasun Rajitha guides this one on the off side but does not manage to beat backward point.
Goes full and on off, Kasun Rajitha pushes this one to mid on for a dot.
Back of a length and slanting down the leg side, Kasun Rajitha shoulders arms.
On a good length and outside off, Kasun Rajitha does not reach out to the delivery and lets it go.
Full and shaping away outside off, Kasun Rajitha leans forward and leaves the ball alone.
Starts with a full delivery just outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya steers this one past backward point and collects a couple of runs.

A tough chance goes down! Full and on off, Prabath Jayasuriya drives it to uppishly but to the left of the bowler. Matt Henry fails to hang onto it in his follow-through. The ball rolls towards long off and batters run three.
Full and swinging away outside off, Kasun Rajitha goes for the drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! Matt Henry continues to go full and bowls this one on middle, Kasun Rajitha looks to work this one on the leg side but closes the bat face early. The ball bounces after hitting the seam and catches the leading edge of Rajitha's bat. The ball lobs towards extra cover where Kane Williamson runs around from mid off and completes a good catch. Matt Henry has his third wicket of the innings now.
Howout: c Kane Williamson b Matt Henry

Commentary: Full and angling across outside off, Lahiru Kumara leaves the ball alone.
Full and in the channel outside off, Lahiru Kumara shoulders arms and lets it go.
Short of a length on middle by Tim Southee, Prabath Jayasuriya fends this one from the upper part of the bat towards backward point.
Full and outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya gets on the front foot and goes for the drive but misses.
Good-length delivery outside off, a hint of away movement, Prabath Jayasuriya looks to drive it on the up but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Banged in short and on off, Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under it and lets it go.
On a length around off, Prabath Jayasuriya gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Full and outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya goes for a big booming drive but connects with thin air. First maiden over of the day by Tim Southee.
Back of a length and angling in on off, Lahiru Kumara shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
Full and on middle from 'round the wicket, Lahiru Kumara defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length on off, Lahiru Kumara gets behind the line and keeps it out.
Switches to over the wicket and bangs it in short on middle, Lahiru Kumara ducks underneath and lets it go.
FOUR! Full and around off, Lahiru Kumara picks the length early and drills this one wide of mid on. Opens his account with a boundary.
Shortens his length and bowls it at the batter from 'round the wicket, Lahiru Kumara backs away and dabs it to gully.
Short of a length and shaping away outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya hangs out to his bat to defend but does not connect.
On a good length in the channel outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya looks to defend this one from the crease but misses.
Length delivery and swinging away outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya leaves the ball alone.
Goes full again and around off, the ball nips away after pitching, Prabath Jayasuriya goes for the drive but misses.
Keeps it full and outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya leans forward for the drive but does not connect.
Full and angled in on off, Prabath Jayasuriya drives this one towards extra cover and retains the strike with a single.
Back of a length and shaping away outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya pokes at his bat at the delivery but does not get any bat on it.
Another back-of-a-length delivery around off, Prabath Jayasuriya shapes to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Banged in short and at the batter, Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under the delivery and lets it go.
Short of a length on middle and leg, Prabath Jayasuriya fends this one on the bounce to short leg.
Another play and a miss! Good-length delivery, going away outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya hangs back to defend but gets beaten again
Back of a length outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya does not reach out to the delivery and lets it go. A maiden by Matt Henry.
Full and angling in on off, Lahiru Kumara stays leg side of the ball and pushes it to cover.
Full and outside off from 'round the wicket, Lahiru Kumara clears his front leg and swings his bat at it but connects with thin air.
Continues to go full and outside off, Lahiru Kumara leaves the ball alone.
Full and angling in at the pads, Lahiru Kumara watchfully blocks this one out.
Another full delivery on middle, Lahiru Kumara defends it back to the bowler.
Switches to over the wicket and bowls it full and angling across on off, Lahiru Kumara drives it firmly but finds mid off.
Full and at the stumps, Prabath Jayasuriya looks to defend but wears this one on the front pad.
Full and swinging away outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya does not reach out to the delivery and lets it go.
Good-length delivery and swinging in on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya gets behind the line and keeps it out.
A loud appeal but turned down! Full and at the pads, Prabath Jayasuriya goes for the clip but misses and gets hit on the front pad. New Zealand go up in appeal but the umpire's finger stays down.
Full and on middle, Prabath Jayasuriya defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Back of a length and shaping away outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya pushes at the delivery away from his body and pays the price. The ball catches the outside edge and flies behind the wicket. Tom Blundell dives quickly to his right and completes a good catch. Sri Lanka are now 9 down and Matt Henry has his fourth wicket of the innings.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary: Banged in short but down the leg side, Lahiru Kumara ducks under it and lets it go.
Back of a length on middle, Lahiru Kumara hangs out his bat to defend but gets it from the outer part of the bat. The ball goes through the slip cordon and batters run two in the process.
Length delivery outside off, Lahiru Kumara tries to defend this one but gets beaten.
Another bumper on leg by Tim Southee, Lahiru Kumara gets out of the way and leaves the ball alone.
Fuller and around off, Lahiru Kumara clears his front leg to go down the ground. Gets it from the upper of the bat towards mid on for a single.
Full and swinging in on leg, Asitha Fernando gets across to work it on the leg side but misses.
Full and angling in on off from 'round the wicket, Lahiru Kumara looks to defend but gets an inside edge back onto his pads.
Good-length delivery outside off, Lahiru Kumara tries to push this one on the off side but misses.
Sharp bumper! Banged in short and at the batter, Lahiru Kumara safely ducks under it and lets it go through to the keeper.
Fuller and outside off by Matt Henry, Lahiru Kumara swings his bat at it but connects with thin air.
Short of a length and slanting in on middle, Lahiru Kumara takes his eyes off the ball and awkwardly ducks under it.

FOUR! Short and at the batter, Lahiru Kumara gets into a tangle but still manages to time the pull shot. Gets it behind square on the leg side and the fast outfield does the rest. Devon Conway does put in a dive but the ball trickles into the fence off his left boot.
Full and around off, Asitha Fernando gets behind the line and defends it on the off side for a single.
On a good-length and angling across outside off, Lahiru Kumara does not push at the delivery and lets it go.
It is a length ball, angling across. Lahiru Kumara does not go after it. This one stays a bit low as well.
Much fuller, on off. Lahiru Kumara eases it to covers and crosses.
Full and swinging away outside off, Asitha Fernando gets forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Just over! On a good length and outside off by Tim Southee, Asitha Fernando keeps his bat hanging outside off and gets a thickish outside edge. The ball flies over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length on leg, Lahiru Kumara looks to get on top of the bounce but wears it on the thigh pad.
Length delivery outside off, Lahiru Kumara swings his bat at the delivery but connects with thin air.
Full and at the pads by Matt Henry, Lahiru Kumara clips this one towards deep square leg and takes a single. 350 comes up for Sri Lanka.
Full and around off, nips back in after pitching, Asitha Fernando gets behind the line to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball hits him high on the thigh pad.
Full and on off, Asitha Fernando works this one past short leg and collects a single.
Banged in short and at the batter, Lahiru Kumara ducks underneath the delivery.
Full and on leg, Asitha Fernando watchfully keeps this one out on the leg side.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Fernando ducks under it.
FOUR! EDGY! It is a full ball, outside off. Asitha Fernando throws his bat at it. The ball takes the outside edge and flies down to third man for four runs.

OUT! LBW! Tim Southee has five in the innings! Bowls this one full and on middle and leg, Asitha Fernando shuffles across again to access the leg side but does not connect. The ball catches him in front of the stumps, New Zealand go up in appeal and the umpire raises the dreaded finger. Asitha Fernando has a word with his partner and sends it upstairs. The UltraEdge shows no bat and it is three reds on Ball Tracking. The onfield decision stands and that brings an end to Sri Lanka's innings.
Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary: Kasun Rajitha comes 'round the wicket and gets some swing straightaway. It is full, angled in on off. Tom Latham clips it to the leg side.
FOUR! Top placement! Tom Latham and New Zealand are off the mark here. Kasun Rajitha goes full, on middle and leg. Tom Latham leans into it and knocks it down to long on for four runs.
Good length, outside off. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Kasun Rajitha fires it full, tailing into the pads. Tom Latham flicks it along the ground, through the gap at mid-wicket. The batters take three runs. Too easy for Tom Latham
Kasun Rajitha angles in a length ball, outside off. Devon Conway is drawn into the shot but the ball just straightens a touch. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller, on the pads. Devon Conway clips it through square leg for a single. So, 8 runs off the first over. A solid start for the hosts by the look of it.
Good length, outside off, with a bit of swing. Devon Conway leaves it for the keeper.
Asitha Fernando angles it across, on a length, Devon Conway trusts the bounce and shoulders his arms at it.
This is a bit fuller, lands on off and swings away off the deck. Devon Conway gets beaten on the outside edge.
Too full, sliding down leg. Devon Conway clips it to deep square leg and collects three runs with ease.
A length ball, in the channel. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
It is fuller, although swinging down leg. Latham fails to clip it away.
This one catches Conway by surprise. It is a length ball, around off. It flies off the deck. Devon Conway defends it awkwardly off the top half of the bat.
Length, on off, defended.
Much fuller, outside off. Devon Conway lets it be.
Four dots in a row! Kasun Rajitha serves it full, outside off. Devon Conway tries to drive it away but gets an inside edge on it. The ball rolls towards square leg.
Much fuller, on off. Conway steps forward and gets it to mid-wicket off the inside edge.
Good length, wide of off. Devon Conway makes a solid leave. A maiden now for Kasun Rajitha.
Length, sliding down leg. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Outside off. Tom Latham makes a leave.
Fuller, angled across, wide of off. Tom Latham keeps his bat to himself.

A loud appeal for lbw! Asitha Fernando pleads in fact, but the umpire isn't convinced. Coming to the delivery, It is a length ball, around leg and nips away a touch. Tom Latham tries to flick it away but ends up playing all around it. He is pinged right in front of the stumps. Dimuth Karunaratne takes the review. The Ball Tracking though confirms that the ball is pitching outside leg. Sri Lanka lose a review, quite early in their innings.
Length, outside off, left alone.
On a length, on fourth stump. Tom Latham leaves it alone for the keeper.
Devon Conway shuffles and shoulders his arms to this good-length ball.
Outside off, left alone once again.
It is fuller, on middle and leg. Devon Conway nudges it to mid-wicket.
Easy leave! Back of a length, wide of off. Devon Conway watches it sail past him.
It is tad fuller this but continues to attack outside off. Devon Conway showing no intent to play away from his body.
Angles in a length ball, on off. Devon Conway defends it watchfully. Another maiden for Kasun Rajitha.
It is full, on leg. Tom Latham fails to flick it away. This is the last over before Lunch.
Asitha Fernando hurls in a full-length ball, on fourth stump. Tom Latham prods and tries to push it to the off side. The ball takes an inside edge on to his pads.
Fuller, wide outside off, swinging further away. Tom Latham lets it be.
A length ball, on off. It is angled across. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
Outside off, shaping further away on a length. Tom Latham makes an easy leave.
Good length, on top of off. Tom Latham fends it to covers and scampers across for a quick single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
It is full, way closer to the tramline outside off. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
It is a bit fuller, outside off. Not close enough to bother Latham here.
FOUR! Beautiful shot. It is pitched up, on fifth stump. Tom Latham leans in and drives it through covers for a fine boundary.
Full one on off. Tom Latham bunts it to the off side and takes a single.
Full again, angles it in, around off. Devon Conway blocks it out solidly.
Length ball, outside off. It nips back in a touch. Devon Conway makes a sharp leave.
Asitha Fernando dishes it full, on leg. Tom Latham gets his foot across and tucks it to square leg.
Fernando fires it full, down leg. Devon Conway fails to glance it away.
A bit full, angled across, on a length. Devon Conway lets it be.
It is full, around fifth stump. Devon Conway tries to have a feel for it away from his body. The ball goes to square leg off he inside edge and they cross.
FOUR LEG BYES! A length ball, on leg, swining down leg. It brushes Latham's pad and runs down to the fina leg fence.
Outside off. Tom Latham makes a wise leave here.
Kasun Rajitha dishes a length ball, in the channel. Devon Conway pushes it gently to covers and crosses.
Fuller, on the pads, Tom Latham clips it to square leg for another single.
Good length, on sixth stump. Left alone.
Kasun Rajitha angles in a length ball, at 133 clicks. The ball hits the deck and shapes away a touch. Devon Conway gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to hit it through the line.
Outside off, left alone.
Full, angling down leg. Devon Conway fails to clip it away.
Asitha Fernando spills this one down the leg side. Tom Latham is unable to attack it.
Much fuller, outside off. Tom Latham leaves it alone for the keeper.
Another easy leave for Latham as this is sprayed way outside off.
A sharp bumper, on middle. Tom Latham ducks under it without any hesitation.
Length, on off, tapped out.
Asitha Fernando fires it full, into the pads. Tom Latham stays back and clips it through the gap at square leg. They take a couple.
Kasun Rajitha goes very full and on off. Devon Conway defends it away watchfully.
Fuller, in the channel. Devon Conway steps across and blocks it out solidly.
Good length, wide of off. Conway lets it be.
Length, on off. Conway blocks it with full face.
Fifth dot on the trot! It is angled in, on a length, around off. Devon Conway presses forward and defends it quite solidly.
Fuller, attacking the stump. Devon Conway jams it back towards the bowler.
Devon Conway leaves this length ball, wide outside off.
Much fuller, outside off. Tom Latham shuffles across and makes the leave.
It is pitched up, in the channel. Tom Latham leans in it and drives it firmly through the gap at covers. They take three before the fielder cuts it out.
Fuller, outside off, nips in a bit late. Devon Conway watches it sail past him and into the keeper's mitts.
Shortsih, wide of off. Conway shoulders his arms at it.
Good length, outside off. It climbs off the deck. Devon Conway lets it be.
Outside off, Latham makes an easy leave.
Lahiru Kumara hurls in a length ball, around middle. It is angled across. The ball gets some extra bounce off the deck. Tom Latham stays inside the crease and leaves it alone.
Length and on off, blocked away to safety.

It is a length ball, that lands around middle and nips in a touch. Tom Latham takes a blow high on his pads, as he fails to flick it away. Lahiru Kumara makes an appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
FOUR! Into the gap! It is full, wide of off, angled across. Tom Latham opens the face and steers it down to third man for four runs.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller, outside off, nipping in late. Devon Conway is happy with a sighter.
It is a short ball, on off. Devon Conway goes for the pull shot. The ball takes the top-edge and flies to deep square leg. It lands safely. One taken.
Full length, outside off, seaming further away. Tom Latham shoulders his arms this time.
Good length, wide of off. Tom Latham makes another leave.
It is a length ball, outside off. Tom Latham leans in and tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Touch fuller, on fifth stump, nips back in late. Tom Latham makes an easy leave.
Short one, outside off, at 138 clicks. Devon Conway leaves it alone.
This one swings further away from outside off. Devon Conway makes a good leave.
This time it is full, on off. Devon Conway defends it off the bottom half.
FOUR! EDGY! Back of a length, wide of off. Devon Conway rocks back and cuts it hard. The ball takes the top-edge and runs down to third man for four runs.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, around off. Devon Conway drives it into covers. The fielder there makes a half-stop. One taken.
It is fuller, on off. Devon Conway gets it to backward point off the outer half.
On a length, wide of off, swinging in late. Conway lets it be.
Outside off, Conway leaves it alone.
Asitha Fernando hurls in a length ball, wide of off. Devon Conway has not shown any intent to play away from his body.
Fuller, outside off. Conway offers no shot here.

A huge appeal but the umpire says nothing! Asitha Fernando angles in a length ball, into the pads. Devon Conway misses his flick to take a blow on his pads. This is clearly going down leg. Dimuth Karunaratne does not take the review here.
Shortish, wide of off. Left alone.
This one lands outside off and shapes further away. Tom Latham watches it sail past him.
Length and on off, tapped to point.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on fifth stump. Tom Latham makes a solid leave.
Back of a length, on off. Tom Latham dabs it back to the bowler.
Good length, around off. This one flies off the deck. Devon Conway trusts the bounce and makes a sharp leave.
On off, blocked out.
Length ball, angled in around off. Devon Conway gets it to the slip cordon off his gloves.
Good running! It is pitched up, outside off. Devon Conway leans in and drives it through covers. They take three before the fielder cuts it out.
Full, on off, Latham defends it out with full face.
Much fuller, around off. Tom Latham remains solid in his defense.
FOUR! Smartly played! Back of a length, outside off. Devon Conway rocks back and rides the bounce. He smashes it over backward point for four runs.
It is full this time, around off. Devon Conway tries to defend it away from his body. The ball takes the inside edge and runs down to fine leg. Two taken.
Length, around off, blocked out to the off side.
On a good length, outside off. Left alone.
It is fuller, in the channel. Conway gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half. One taken. 50 up for the hosts as well.
Lahiru Kumara angles in a length ball, outside off. It nips away off the deck. Tom Latham tries to defend it but does so inside the line.
Full and on off. Conway presses forward and blocks it into the deck.
Good length, in the channel. Conway trusts the bounce and makes the leave.
Devon Conway stays back to this length ball and pushes it to covers.
Fuller, on off. Conway blocks it into the surface.
Tad full, wide of off. Devon Conway leaves it alone.
It is fuller, wide of off. Devon Conway drives it gently towards covers.
On a good length outside off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham shoulders arms.
Good-length delivery on off, Tom Latham gets behind the line and solidly defends it down the wicket.
Short of a length and shaping away outside off, Tom Latham leaves the ball alone.
Another short delivery aimed at the batter, at 140 kph, Tom Latham works this one down to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length on middle, Devon Conway hangs back and pushes this one in front of mid on for a run.
Fuller and slanting in on off, Tom Latham watchfully lets it go.
Starts with a full delivery on middle, Devon Conway gets forward and defends it on the leg side.
Floated, full on middle and leg, Devon Conway defends it down the wicket.
Full and turning away on off, Devon Conway gets on the front foot and keeps this one out.
Short and on off, Devon Conway goes back and whips it to mid-wicket.
Short and quicker around off, Devon Conway punches this one along the ground to extra cover.
Flighted, full on off, Devon Conway leans forward and blocks this one out.
Shortish delivery on off from over the wicket, Tom Latham stands tall and dabs it to backward point.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Tom Latham looks to tuck this one on the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good-length delivery angling across outside off, Tom Latham lets it go.
Another good-length delivery at the stumps, Tom Latham gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler
Banged in short and on middle, Tom Latham rides on top of the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Devon Conway drops this one on the leg side and calls his partner for a quick single.
Tossed up, full on middle, Devon Conway steps out and drives it down to long on for a run.
Full and around off, Tom Latham gets forward and blocks it out.
Angled in full on off, Tom Latham solidly gets behind this delivery.
Flighted, full just outside off, Tom Latham shimmies down the track and defends it to cover.
Keeps it full on off, Tom Latham gets forward and blocks it out on the off side.
Short and flatter on off, Tom Latham goes back in his crease and punches it down to long on. Retains the strike with a single.
Full and around off by Kasun Rajitha, Tom Latham drives it along the ground to mid on.
Short and outside off, Tom Latham cuts hard off the back foot but finds backward point.
On a good length on leg, Tom Latham looks to turn this one on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Length delivery on off, Tom Latham leans forward and keeps this one out.
Touch fuller and outside off, Tom Latham shoulders arms.
Full and angling across around off, Tom Latham watchfully lets it go through to the keeper.
Short and flatter on leg, Devon Conway clips this one wide of deep square leg and collects three runs.
Goes full and around off, Tom Latham gets forward and keeps this one out.
Sees the batter advance and bowls it short, Tom Latham solidly defends this one on the off side.
Short and on middle and leg, Tom Latham punches it off the back foot to long on for a run.
Short and outside off, Devon Conway lets it go.
Tossed up, full on off, Devon Conway defends it down the wicket.
Back of a length on off, Tom Latham stands tall and defends this down the wicket.
Shortish delivery on middle, Tom Latham nudges this one towards square leg and takes a single.
Fuller and outside off, Devon Conway gets forward and drives it wide of mid off for a single.

FOUR! Pulled away by Tom Latham! Banged in short and at the batter, Tom Latham swivels in his crease and pulls it along the ground to fine leg. Lahiru Kumara stationed there does not bend quickly and concedes a boundary.
Sharp bumper! Short and on middle, Tom Latham looks to pull this one but changes his mind at the last moment and lets it go through to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Tom Latham leaves the ball alone.
Tossed up, full on middle and leg, Devon Conway defends it down the wicket.
Fuller and around off, Devon Conway leans forward and keeps this one out.
Short and on off, Devon Conway works this one off the back foot to mid-wicket.
Short and quicker on middle, Devon Conway goes back and punches it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full outside off, Devon Conway drives it hard towards extra cover. Chamika Karunaratne makes a good half-stop and keeps it to one.
Flighted, full outside off, Tom Latham goes for the sweep but fails to connect.
Starts with a full delivery on leg, Devon Conway clips this one but fails to get it past mid on.
Full and angling in on off, Devon Conway gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
On a good length around off by Asitha Fernando, Devon Conway solidly keeps this one out.

OUT! LBW! Asitha Fernando comes back into the attack and removes Devon Conway! Bowls this one full and around off, the ball nips back in after pitching and beats Conway on the inside edge. The ball strikes him on the back leg, Sri Lanka go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Conway has a word with his partner and goes for the review. The UltraEdge shows no bat and it is the umpire's call on Ball Tracking. The onfield decision stands and Conway has to make his way back. A much-needed breakthrough for Sri Lanka.
Howout: lbw b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: On a length and shaping away outside off, Kane Williamson lets it be.
Full and seaming away outside off, Kane Williamson leans forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and on middle, Tom Latham stays on the back foot and works it wide of leg slip.
Flighted, full on middle, Tom Latham knocks it down to long on for a run.
Short and on middle from 'round the wicket, Kane Williamson goes back and nudges it to square leg. Opens his account with a single.
Short and flatter on off, Tom Latham dabs this one past point for a single.
Short and angled away on off, Kane Williamson gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Short on middle and leg, Kane Williamson stays back and tucks it on the bounce to short leg.
Full and angling in on middle, at 138.8 kph, Tom Latham drives it firmly to mid on.
Back of a length but down the leg side, Tom Latham gets his gloves out of the way and leaves the ball alone.
Full and on middle and leg, Tom Latham drives it straight to mid on.
Back of a length and shaping away outside off, Tom Latham watchfully lets it go.
Fuller this time and outside off, Tom Latham drives but finds backward point with his shot.
Sharp delivery! Short of a length and angled in at the batter, Tom Latham gets out of the way and lets it go. Niroshan Dickwella dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Back of a length and shaping in on off, Kane Williamson hangs back and pushes it to cover.
On a good length and outside off, Kane Williamson leaves the ball alone.
Continues to go back of a length on off, Kane Williamson gets on top of the bounce and keeps this one out.
Good-length delivery in the channel outside off, the ball nips away after pitching and beats Kane Williamson as he tried to defend.
Back of a length and angling back into the batter, the ball jags back in sharply after pitching and hits Williamson high on the pads.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lahiru Kumara gets the big fish! Kept bowling back of a length prior to this delivery and bowls this one full and outside off, Kane Williamson is tempted by the length and goes for the drive through covers. Does not manage to keep his shot along the ground and hits it straight to short cover where Dimuth Karunaratne takes a good low catch. This is a massive wicket for Sri Lanka. That will be TEA on Day 2!
Howout: c Dimuth Karunaratne b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary: Asitha Fernando angles in a full one, on off. Tom Latham flicks it towards mid on for a single.
Asitha Fernando now offers some width by serving a length ball, wide of off. Henry Nicholls lets it be.
Length ball, around off, defended out.
A length ball, on fifth stump. Henry Nicholls shuffles and clips it towards mid-wicket for a single. He gets off the mark here.
Tom Latham flicks this length ball to mid-wicket off his pads and collects a single.
