A dot to end the over! A huge and a loud appeal for lbw as well. It is full, tailing back into the pads. Henry Nicholls tries to flick it across the line but misses. He gets pinged on his pads. Altough, it is going down the leg side.
Short one, wide of off. Left alone by Latham.
Back of a length once again, outside off. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
Tom Latham shoulders his arms to this short ball, outside off, that nips in a touch late.
Confident leave! Lahiru Kumara hurls in a length ball, outside off. It nips in late. Latham though trusts the bounce here and sees the ball fly above the sticks.
Outside off, left alone once again.
Lahiru Kumara dishes a length ball, that lands outside off and jags back in off the deck. Tom Latham offers no shot and wears a blow high on his thigh pads.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Henry Nicholls tucks it through mid-wicket for one.
Asitha Fernando goes full, around middle. Tom Latham miscues his drive towards mid on. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
Outide off, left alone.
Length, wide of off. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
Tom Latham shuffles, covers his stumps nicely and leaves this length ball, wide outside off.
Four dots on the trot to end the over! Asitha Fernando dishes a length ball, on off. It nips is sharply with some extra bounce. Tom Latham gets pinged above the flap of his pads.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lahiru Kumara gets his second wicket now. Sri Lanka are delighted to see the back of Henry Nicholls here, as he walks back without troubling the score much. Lahiru Kumara dishes a short ball, on the bodyline. Henry Nicholls swivels and goes for the pull shot. He does not time it well as the ball flies off the top-edge. It goes high in the air towards the leg side. Kasun Rajitha calls for it and takes a sharp catch coming in from mid on.
Howout: c Kasun Rajitha b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary: Length and on off, blocked out.

Lahiru Kumara bowling with fire here. It is a good-length ball, angled in around fifth stump. Daryl Mitchell is drawn into playing the shot but for the original line as he gets beaten on the outside edge by the away swing.
Good length, outside off, nips back in a long way. Daryl Mitchell makes a confident leave. The ball sails over the stumps.
Length ball, around leg. Daryl Mitchell clips it to the leg side.
A bit fuller, outside off. Daryl Mitchell steps across and tries to push it away but wears it on his pads. A stifled appeal for lbw but the umpire shows no interest.
Length, outside off. Latham lets it be.
Full, coming in with the angle, on off. Latham defends it out watchfully.
Short one, on off. Latham pulls it to deep mid-wicket for two runs.
A length ball, just outside off. Latham lets it be.
Asitha Fernando goes full this time, outside off. It nips in a touch late. Latham covers his sticks and lets it through to the keeper.

This is close! Asitha Fernando cannot believe it. It is a length ball, that jags back in sharply off the deck from outside off. Tom Latham trusts the bounce and shoulders his arms at it. Although, he is fortunate enough to see the ball go over the stumps here. It wasn't far away from turning into a fourth wicket. Sri Lanka are clearly on top.
Full and on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and pushes it along the ground to mid on.
Full and angling in around off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and drives it straight to mid off.
Banged in short on off by Lahiru Kumara, Daryl Mitchell drops his wrists and lets the ball go.
Goes full again and on off, Daryl Mitchell solidly keeps this one out.
Back of a length and angling down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell nudges this one down to fine leg for a run.
Bumper outside off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham shapes to pull but does not go through with the shot and leaves the ball alone.
Starts with a beauty! On a good-length angling in on off, the ball nips away after pitching and beats Daryl Mitchell on the outside edge.
Fuller and at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell defends it back to the bowler.
Full and swinging away outside off, Daryl Mitchell does not reach out to the delivery and lets it be.
Another peach by Kasun Rajitha! Good-length in the channel outside off, the angle draws Daryl Mitchell into the shot. The ball shapes away and beats the batter on the outside edge.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down! Full and going away around off, Daryl Mitchell steps out and looks to get to the pitch of the delivery. Does not account for the away movement and the ball catches him on the front pad. Sri Lanka go up in unison but the umpire is unmoved. Dimuth Karunaratne opts for a review and UltraEdge shows no bat. Although, the Ball Tracking shows that it is umpire's call on ball hitting the wickets. Daryl Mitchell survives.
Fuller on leg, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and blocks this one out.
FOUR! Fullish delivery outside off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham goes for the drive but gets a thickish outside edge. The ball flies through the vacant third slip area for a boundary.
Good-length in the channel outside off, Tom Latham leaves the ball alone.
On a good length angling in around off, Tom Latham shoulders arms.

A huge shout for LBW but turned down! Lahiru Kumara continues to bowl on a good length and around off, the ball jabs back in sharply after pitching. Tom Latham covers the off stump and offers no shot. The ball catches him high on the back leg and the umpire's finger stays down. It looked high in real-time.
Fullish delivery outside off, Tom Latham squeezes this one to mid off for a dot.
FOUR! Back of a length and outside off, Tom Latham gets on top of the bounce and steers it past backward point for a boundary.
On a good length around off, Daryl Mitchell gets forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Luckily for him, he does not reach out to the delivery.
FOUR! Full and swinging away outside off, Daryl Mitchell goes for the drive away from his body but gets an outside edge that rolls past gully for a boundary.

A loud appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved! Full and shaping away in the channel outside off, Daryl Mitchell tries to defend this one from the crease but plays down the wrong line. Niroshan Dickwella pouches it safely and goes up in appeal but the umpire's finger stays down. Dimuth Karunaratne has a word with the bowler and decides not to review. The replays confirm that the ball had come off Mitchell's pads.
On a good length on off, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and keeps it out on the off side.
Fuller in length on off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and defends it down the wicket.
Bowls it on a length outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves the ball alone.
Starts with a loosener, full but swinging down the leg side, Tom Latham leaves it alone. Niroshan Dickwella dives quickly to his right and makes a good stop.
Full and swinging in on middle, Tom Latham accounts for the inward movement and blocks this one out.
FIFTY for Tom Latham! On a length at the pads, Tom Latham works this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single. This has been a resolute knock by Latham with wickets falling at the other end.
SIX! Daryl Mitchell goes huge! Full and shaping away outside off, Daryl Mitchell frees his arms and thumps this one well over long on for the first maximum of the New Zealand innings.
On a good length outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves the ball alone.
Good-length delivery angling in on middle, Daryl Mitchell solidly blocks this one out.

Kasun Rajitha continues his attack from 'round the wicket. It is a length ball, angled in around fourth stump. It nips away off the deck. Tom Latham gets beaten as he tries to defend inside the line here.
Full length, angled into the pads. Tom Latham clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, outside off, shaping further away. Daryl Mitchell steps across and shoulders his arms at it.
Length, wide of off. Daryl Mitchell lets it be.

Kasun Rajitha hurls in a full-length ball, around off. It nips away sharply. Daryl Mitchell presses forward to block it away but it only catches the outside edge. Although, as he plays it with soft hands the ball lands short of the man at second slip. The batters sneak a single as there is a misfield in slips. 100 is up for the hosts with this single.
Full length, on off. Tom Latham pushes it gently towards covers for a quick single.
It is full, slanting across, outside off. Tom Latham shuffles and clips it towards mid-wicket for one.
Angelo Mathews pitches it up, on off. Daryl Mitchell gets under it and lofts it over mid off. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it out.
A length ball, angled across, wide of off. Tom Latham comes a long way across and gets beaten on the outside edge here.
Full length, on off. Latham taps it to cover and takes a single.
Length and on off, blocked out.
Good running! It is a much fuller, on leg. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket. The call is for two and they get two comfortably. This partnership is building really well for the Kiwis.
On a length, outside off, it holds its line. Tom Latham does not bother to chase it.
Kasun Rajitha pulls his length back a touch, on fifth stump. Tom Latham shuffles and blocks it out solidly.
Much fuller, outside off. Tom Latham presses forward and pushes it gently towards mid off. One taken.
Outside off. Left alone.
It is very full, on fourth stump, shaping away. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and bunts it to the off side.
Fuller, around middle. Daryl Mitchell tucks it to mid-wicket and crosses.
Full length, just outside off. Daryl Mitchell prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Very full, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell gets it to the leg side off the inner half. The batters take a couple.
Angelo Mathews serves it full, wide of off, swinging away. Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
A bit short, outside off. Daryl Mitchell hangs back and taps it to point.
Full length, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
A single to end the over! Good length, around off. Tom Latham pushes it down the ground for one.
Prabath Jayasuriya starts with a full one, outside off. Tom Latham prods and blocks it into the deck.
Tom Latham uses his feet and dabs it into the surface.
Floated and full, outside off. Tom Latham drives it through the gap at covers for three runs.
Full and on leg. Daryl Mitchell flicks it down to long on for one.
Another single now as Tom Latham knocks his full one towards long on.
Floated and full, on middle. Daryl Mitchell gets low and sweeps it down to fine leg. It is a long chase for the fielder. The batters take three.
Starts with a back-of-a-length delivery on off, Daryl Mitchell gets across and works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller around off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and defends it down the wicket.
On a length on off, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and defends this one towards mid on.
Short of a length on middle, Daryl Mitchell goes for the pull but gets an inside edge. The ball rolls off his pads towards square leg for a single.
Back of a length outside off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham shoulders arms.
FOUR! Cut away by Tom Latham! Asitha Fernando bowls this one short and outside off, Tom Latham gets on his toes and rides on top of the bounce. Cuts this one through covers and collects a boundary.

Short and flatter on leg, Daryl Mitchell turns this one past short leg and takes a single. Chamika Karunaratne picks up the ball and hits at the non-striker's end. The ball deflects off the stumps towards long off which allows batters to run two runs more.
Short and on off, Tom Latham goes back and pushes it wide of extra cover for a single.
Tossed up, full around off, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and blocks this one out.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell goes for the sweep but gets a bottom edge back onto his pads.
Slower and short on leg, Daryl Mitchell goes back and keeps it out on the leg side.
Floated and full, on leg. It grips and turns down leg. Daryl Mitchell tries to block it on his front foot but misses.
Flighted, full on off, Tom Latham defends it down the wicket.
Short and outside off, Tom Latham goes back in his crease and cuts it to deep backward point for a run.
A stifled appeal for LBW but turned down! Tossed up, full and on leg, Daryl Mitchell gets inside the line and paddles this one off his gloves towards short fine leg for a single.
Floated full on off, Tom Latham uses his feet and drives it back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Tom Latham steps out and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Tossed up, full on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and blocks this one out.

OUT! TIMBER! Asitha Fernando comes up with a brutal delivery and gets rid of Tom Latham! Nails the yorker on off from 'round the wicket and catches the batter by surprise. Tom Latham fails to get his bat down in time to dig this one out and pays the price. Sees his woodwork disturbed and Sri Lanka are delighted so they so should be. New Zealand are now 4 down trailing by 221 runs.
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Short of a length outside off, Tom Blundell hangs back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
On a good length in the channel outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms.
Length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets to the pitch of the delivery and blocks it out.
Goes back of a length outside off, Daryl Mitchell stays back and keeps it out on the off side.
Bumper by Asitha Fernando, aimed at the batter, Daryl Mitchell ducks under the delivery and lets it go.
On a good length angling in around off, Tom Blundell covers his off stump and watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Touch fuller and going away outside off, Tom Blundell opts not to offer a shot.
Back of a length outside off, a hint of inward movement, Tom Blundell gets his gloves out of the way and leaves the ball alone.
Shortish delivery and slanting in on middle, Tom Blundell stays on the back foot and defends it down the wicket.
Goes full this time and outside off, Tom Blundell gets tempted by the width and goes for the drive away from his body. Luckily for him, he does not edge this one.
Shortens his length and bowls it on off, Tom Blundell gets behind the line and keeps this one out on the off side.
A length ball, wide of off. It nips away off the deck. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone for the keeper.
It is fuller in length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leans in and drives it into covers.
FOUR! A much-needed boundary for New Zealand. It is a good-length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell rocks back and punches it over backward point for four runs.
It is a length ball, wide of off. It stays a bit low off the deck. Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
Asitha Fernando angles in a length ball, on fifth stump and gets it to shape away sharply. Daryl Mitchell gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leans in and checks his drives towards extra covers.
Lahiru Kumara goes full, around off. It nips back in. Tom Blundell hangs his blade away from his body. The ball takes the inside edge and goes down to square leg. One taken.
Length ball, comes back in sharply from outside off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it back to the bowler.
Full, tailing into the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards mid on.
Lahiru Kumara now dishes a sharp bouncer, outside off. This one is way above the batter's head. Wide called.
Good length, wide outside off. It nips back in with some extra bounce. Daryl Mitchell makes a solid leave.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Daryl Mitchell ducks under this one.
LEG BYE! It is full, sliding down leg. Daryl Mitchell fails to clip it away. The ball brushes his pads and goes down to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Length, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell gets a single now as he tucks this through mid-wicket.
Length, wide of off. Tom Blundell prods and shoulders his arms at it.
A length ball, that jags back in from around off. Tom Blundell takes a blow on his pads but clearly going down leg.
It is fuller, on middle and leg. Tom Blundell gets it to through square leg off the inside edge. The batters take two runs.
Good-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. It climbs on to the batter. Tom Blundell tries to have a feel for it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Too full, outside off. Tom Blundell dabs it out to point.
A short ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell does not go hunting here.
Length ball, nipping back in from outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and blocks it back to the bowler.
Length, wide of off. Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
Fuller, angled into the pads. Daryl Mitchell clips it to mid-wicket, could not get it through the gap though.
Daryl Mitchell flicks this length ball off his pads towards square leg. One taken.
BEATEN! A length ball, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell pushes the blade through the line but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Kasun Rajitha starts with a beauty! It is angled in, on a length, around off. It nips away with some extra bounce. Daryl Mitchell gets beaten as he tries to block it inside the line.
Fuller, on leg. Daryl Mitchell clips it to the leg side for a single.
BEATEN! It is a good-length ball, around off. It jags away off the deck. Tom Blundell tries to have a poke at it but misses.
Length and on off, shaping away. Tom Blundell shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Four dots in a row to end the over! It is a short one, outside off. Blundell shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.
Sharp bounce! Short of a length outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets on his toes to work it through the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length outside off, Daryl Mitchell does not reach out to the delivery and leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell hangs back and works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length around off, nips back in after pitching, Tom Blundell shapes to defend but the ball sneaks past the inside edge.
Full and swinging in on off, Tom Blundell accounts for the inward movement and drives it back past the bowler. The batters run three before Angelo Mathews cuts it off.
Short of a length and angling in outside off, Daryl Mitchell opts not to offer a shot and lets it go.
Length delivery shaping away outside off, Tom Blundell defends this one under his eyes on the off side.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Kasun Rajitha gets into the act now! Bowls this one back of a length and shaping away outside off, Tom Blundell hangs out his bat to defend and pays the price. The ball seams away after pitching and catches the outside edge of his bat. Niroshan Dickwella behind the wicket makes no mistake to hand Rajitha his first wicket of the game. Half the side back in the hut for New Zealand with still 204 runs behind.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Kasun Rajitha

Commentary: Serves this one full and swinging away outside off from 'round the wicket, Michael Bracewell shoulders arms and lets it go.
Full and angling in around off, Michael Bracewell solidly keeps this one out.
Full and just outside off, Michael Bracewell leaves the ball alone this time.
Length delivery at the pads, Michael Bracewell tucks this one off his hips towards square leg. Gets off the mark with a single.
Starts with a length delivery outside off, Michael Bracewell opts not to offer a shot.
Short of a length and around off, Michael Bracewell goes for the pull but does not connect. Wears the ball on his body and it rolls behind the wicket to Niroshan Dickwella.
Continues to go back of a length on off, Michael Bracewell shoulders arms.
Touch fuller and outside off, the ball nips back in after pitching, Michael Bracewell covers his off stump and lets it go.
Keeps it on a length outside off, Michael Bracewell continues to leave balls outside his off stump.
Full and shaping in on off, Michael Bracewell takes a stride forward and leaves the ball alone.
Short of a length around off, Daryl Mitchell watchfully shoulders arms.
Fuller in length and moving away outside off, Daryl Mitchell accounts for the away movement and lets it be.
Angles this one full and around off, the ball moves away after pitching. Daryl Mitchell gets forward and leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length on off by Kasun Rajitha, Daryl Mitchell stands tall and taps it towards point.
Beauty! Bowls this one on a good length and shaping away on off, Daryl Mitchell does not reach out to the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on off, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and defends it from the outer part of the bat on the off side.
FOUR! Full and slanting in just outside off from 'round the wicket, Michael Bracewell picks the length early and presents a straight bat. Drives it back past the bowler and collects a boundary.
Goes full again and around off, Michael Bracewell leans forward and clips this one wide of mid on. The batters run three before Prabath Jayasuriya cuts it off.
On a good length on middle, Daryl Mitchell looks to access the leg side but closes the bat face early. Gets a leading edge that goes wide of backward point for a couple of runs.
Short of a length in the channel outside off, Daryl Mitchell stays on the back foot and dabs it to backward point.
Good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets his bat out of the way in the nick of time.
Another delivery on a good length, going away, Daryl Mitchell shapes to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Final over of the day coming up.
Full and angling across outside off, Michael Bracewell takes a good stride forward and defends it to mid off.
Full and outside off by Kasun Rajitha, Michael Bracewell opts not to offer a shot and lets it go.
Keeps it full and around off, Michael Bracewell gets on the front foot and defends it down the wicket.
Banged in short on off, Michael Bracewell swivels in his crease and goes for the pull but wears it on his shoulder. The ball goes on the bounce towards the slip cordon.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down! Kasun Rajitha foxes the batter with a full delivery and swings this one in on leg, Michael Bracewell misjudges the line and length of the delivery and shapes to leave. The ball catches him on the front pad and Sri Lanka go up in appeal. The umpire is unmoved and Dimuth Karunaratne opts not to go for the review. The replays confirm that the ball was pitching outside leg.

Full and swinging in on middle, Michael Bracewell accounts for the inward movement and drives it towards mid on. A half-stop there allows the batters to cross for a single. That will be STUMPS on Day 2!
Asitha Fernando starts with a full-length, on leg, swinging further down leg. A loosener to begin this on moving day. Michael Bracewell fails to glance it around the corner.
Asitha Fernando fires it full, on leg, it nips in off the deck. Michael Bracewell tries to flick it away but takes a blow on his pads. A stifled appeal for lbw, but it is clearly going down leg.
Asitha Fernando goes full once again, sliding down leg. Asitha Fernando struggling to find his line against the left-hander.
First run for the hosts! It is a full-length ball, angling across, around off. Michael Bracewell gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half. They cross for a single.
It is very full, wide outside off. It shapes further away. Daryl Mitchell leans in but does not go through with his shot.
Length and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it solidly off his front foot. A good start by Asitha Fernando with the ball.
Kasun Rajitha serves it full, wide outside off. This one stays low after hitting the deck. Michael Bracewell lets it be.
Much fuller and straighter, on leg. Michael Bracewell blocks it with full face.
Michael Bracewell gets on his front foot and defends this length ball back to the bowler.
Four dots on the trot! It is a length ball, around off, angling across. Michael Bracewell hangs his blade away from his body and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Make that 5! It is pitched up, on fifth stump. Michael Bracewell pushes it gently towards mid off.
So, Kasun Rajitha starts with a maiden here. Fuller, outside off, swinging away a touch. Michael Bracewell defends it watchfully on his front foot.
Good length, around the hips. Daryl Mitchell shuffles a bit and flicks it behind square on the leg side for one.
A dot now! Much fuller, on off. Michael Bracewell miscues it to covers.
Good length, on off. Michael Bracewell gets behind and bunts it back to the bowler.
Asitha Fernando dishes a full one, on fourth stump. Michael Bracewell gets it back to the bowler off the inner half. Some ohhs and ahhs can be heard now.
It is a short ball, on middle. Michael Bracewell goes for the pull shot, but it flies off the outer half. It lands safely at mid-wicket and they take a single.
Fuller, down the leg side. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone. Another tidy over from Asitha Fernando comes to an end.

A full-length ball, outside off. Michael Bracewell leans in and drives it to covers. The ball takes an awkward bounce in front of the cover fielder and evades him. Angelo Mathews has to give it a chase. The batters take three. An uneven bounce now costs some run here.
Fuller, on off, defended out solidly.
Kasun Rajitha goes full, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell tucks it to the right of mid on and takes a single.
Michael Bracewell now rotates the strike as he flicks this length ball off his pads. A single to mid-wicket.
Length, wide of off. Left alone.

It is a length ball, much straighter on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell gets it down to fine leg off the inside edge. The batters take two runs. This is exceptional running from the batters. Lahiru Kumara quite slow in the deep, the second run was never there.
Asitha Fernando comes 'round the wicket and goes full, wide of off. It nips in late off the deck. Michael Bracewell has no shot to offer.
Good-length ball, outside off. It climbs onto the batter. Michael Bracewell tries to have a feel for it and gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Michael Bracewell finds the gap well this time. It is a length ball, in the channel, with some extra bounce. Michael Bracewell leans in a bit and steers it through the gap behind point. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence.
Shorter, on off. Michael Bracewell blocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone. Michael Bracewell now getting his eye-in here.
A dot to end the over! A length ball, outside off, nips away. Michael Bracewell shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.
A bit shortish, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell lets it through to the keeper.
Kasun Rajitha goes full, outside off, shaping away. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone once again.
Another leave this time by Daryl Mitchell as this is served on a length, wide of off though.
Full length, outside off. This one holds its line. Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
Kasun Rajitha now angles in a full-length ball, on fourth stumps. It jags away sharply. Daryl Mitchell does not fall into the trap.
It is a length ball, in the channel again. Daryl Mitchell prods and makes the leave. A maiden now for Rajitha.
Full length, outside off. Michael Bracewell taps it out to the off side.
Length and on leg. Michael Bracewell tucks it to square leg for a single.
Asitha Fernando dishes a length ball, wide of off. Daryl Mitchell does not chase it.
Fuller, outside off, shaping further away. Daryl Mitchell showing his patience in the middle, as he makes another leave.
Outside off once again, too wide to even bother Daryl Mitchell.

Four dots in a row to end the over! Daryl Mitchell gets forward and tries to defend it away but does so way inside the line. It is a length ball, outside off, which jags away as well. Sri Lanka bowlers are made to work hard this morning.
Kasun Rajitha bends his back hard and dishes a short one, on off. Michael Bracewell pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length, outside off, shaping away. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.

There is some noise here! Kasun Rajitha puts in a loud appeal for caught behind. The umpire is unmoved and Dimuth Karunaratne takes the review. Coming to the ball, it is a length ball, angled in around off. The ball nips away off the deck. Daryl Mitchell tries to block it away on his front foot but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge, brushes the back leg and goes to the keeper. The UltraEdge later confirms as well that no bat is involved. Sri Lanka lose a review here.
Kasun Rajitha asking the right questions here. It is a length ball, that nips away off the deck. Daryl Mitchell shuffles and tries to block it away but gets beaten.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is a full-length delivery, outside off. It nips away a touch. Daryl Mitchell shimmies down the wicket and smacks it down the ground. The ball goes past mid off and races away.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly.
Floated and full, outside off. Michael Bracewell gets forward and blocks it into the deck.
A bit short, wide of off. Michael Bracewell goes back and blocks it to the left of the bowler.
On off, Michael Bracewell blocks it into the deck.
Fuller, around off. Michael Bracewell gets behind and defends it with full face.
Flatter, on leg. Michael Bracewell tucks it into mid-wicket.
Prabath Jayasuriya starts his spell on Day 3 with a maiden. Floats it up, on middle and leg. Michael Bracewell goes back and flicks it into the leg side.
Kasun Rajitha dishes a full-length ball, outside off. It nips away sharply. Daryl Mitchell comes outside the crease and tries to block it away but misses. He gets pinged on his back pad.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off. Daryl Mitchell eases it to extra cover.
On a length, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell tries to block it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.
It is full, on fourth stump. Daryl Mitchell steps across and blocks it solidly.

This time Daryl Mitchell stays inside the crease. A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone. A good cat and mouse game going on between Daryl Mitchell and Kasun Rajitha in this over.
Full and on off. Michael Bracewell knocks it down to long on for a single.
Loopy ball, full, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it on his front foot.
Fuller and on middle. Daryl Mitchell sweeps it down to fine leg for a single.
It is full and on off. Michael Bracewell flicks it to deep square leg. The batters take two comfortably.
Flatter and outside off. Michael Bracewell shuffles and clips it to the leg side.
A dot to end the over! Goes full, on fifth stump. Michael Bracewell gets behind the line and does the needed.
Lahiru Kumara starts with a length ball, wide of off. This one nips back in sharply, although a bit too late, as Daryl Mitchell decides the make the leave without any hesitation.
Length and on off, defended out.
Outside off, left alone.

Incredible knock! Daryl Mitchell has kept his team alive in this inning. It is full, outside off. Daryl Mitchell comes long way outside the crease and gets it towards mid on off the inner half. He scampers across for a quick single and racks up his eighth Test half-century. Daryl Mitchell raises his bat and soaks in the applause here. What a moment for him.
Back of a length, on off. Michael Bracewell decides to ride the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg. They take a single.
Fuller, on off. Daryl Mitchell knocks it to mid off and yells - NO, making it very clear to Michael Bracewell to stay inside the crease. Lahiru Kumara gives away just two runs here.
Fuller, on off, blocked out.

It is flatter, outside off. Michael Bracewell shuffles and shoulders his arms at it. The ball turns in a touch and hits him on his pads. Prabath Jayasuriya and the company make an appeal for lbw. The umpire is unmoved though. Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the review after having a chat with his players. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking later confirms that the impact it outside the line and the ball is missing the wickets. Sri Lanka have no reviews left here.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Who needs reviews, says Prabath Jayasuriya. He gets rid of Michael Bracewell on the very next delivery after losing a review. Prabath Jayasuriya tosses it up, outside off. Michael Bracewell goes back and tries to defend it inside the line though. The ball takes a faint edge and Niroshan Dickwella does the rest behind the sticks. A terrible mistake by Michael Bracewell here. He goes back to a delivery to which he should've played on the front foot here. Just the opening Sri Lanka were after. Can they build on it?
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: It is full, coming in with the arm, on middle. Tim Southee defends it watchfully.
Tossed up, outside off. Tim Southee bunts it to covers and gets off the mark with a single.
A dot to end a successful over. It is full and on off. Prabath Jayasuriya presses forward and blocks it out.
Banged in short and around off by Lahiru Kumara, Tim Southee ducks under the delivery and lets it go.
On a good length on off, Tim Southee hangs back and goes for the drive. Gets an inside edge back onto his pads. The ball rolls off his pads in front of cover and batters cross for a single.
Full and angling in on middle, Daryl Mitchell drives it firmly to the bowler. Lahiru Kumara picks up the ball in his follow-through and has a shy at the striker's end but does not hit.
Full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell frees his arms and swings his bat to go down the ground but gets an inside edge back onto his front pad.
Keeps it full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell leans forward and leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length on middle, Daryl Mitchell gets inside the line and tucks this one towards the fine leg region for a couple of runs.
Flighted, full on middle and leg, Tim Southee works it to mid-wicket.
Goes full and on middle, Tim Southee defends it down the wicket.
Full and angling in on leg, Tim Southee blocks this one out on the off side.
Fired in full and around off, Tim Southee dabs this one towards backward point.
FOUR! Fraction short and on leg, Tim Southee picks the length early and goes back in his crease. Pulls this one through mid-wicket for a boundary.

SIX! This is even better! Goes short again and on leg, Tim Southee does not miss out as he pulls this one off the back foot. Gets plenty of bat on it and clears the deep mid-wicket fence for his first maximum.

SIX! Daryl Mitchell gets into the act now! Back of a length around off by Lahiru Kumara, Daryl Mitchell gets into a good position and swings his bat at it. Thumps this one towards the long on fence for a maximum.
Keeps it full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms and lets it go.
Fullish delivery on off, Daryl Mitchell drives it along the ground to mid off for a dot.
Full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives this one firmly towards backward point. Dinesh Chandimal there dives to his left and keeps it to one.
On a good length at the stumps, Tim Southee makes room and clears his front leg. Looks to go over mid on but gets it from the upper part of the bat. The ball rolls to mid on for a run.
Length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell leans forward and drives this one wide of mid off for a single. Angelo Mathews runs to his left and makes a good diving stop.
Tossed up on middle, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and blocks this one out.
Fuller and around off, Daryl Mitchell paddles this one to fine leg for a single.
Bowls this one full and on leg, Tim Southee goes for a mighty heave and gets it towards deep backward square leg for a run.
Floated, full on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted, full on middle, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Tim Southee defends it down the wicket.
Starts with a full delivery shaping away outside off, Daryl Mitchell does not chase the delivery as he tried to defend.
Fullish delivery angling in on middle, Daryl Mitchell digs this one out back to the bowler.
FOUR! BANG! Lahiru Kumara bowls this one on a length around off, Daryl Mitchell picks the length early and clears his front leg. Drills this one back over the bowler's head for a boundary.
WIDE! Banged in short at the batter, Daryl Mitchell ducks and lets it go. The ball sails over the batter's head and the umpire signals a wide.
Fuller and shaping in on off, Daryl Mitchell leans forward and drives it down to long off for a single.
Length delivery around off, Tim Southee goes deep in his crease to go down the ground. Does not get this from the middle part of the bat but enough to clear mid on. Two runs taken.
Serves it full and swinging away outside off, Tim Southee swings his bat at it once again but connects with thin air.
Starts with a shortish delivery on leg, Daryl Mitchell shuffles across and leaves the ball alone.
On a good length and going away outside off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and shoulders arms.
Length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets to the pitch of the delivery and taps it in front of cover for a single.
Goes full this time and outside off, a hint of away movement, Tim Southee makes room to go through the off side but does not connect.
Length delivery on middle, Tim Southee swipes across the line without much timing towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
WIDE! Another bumper sails over the batter's head. Daryl Mitchell ducks and lets it be.
Short of a length on off, Daryl Mitchell hangs back and dabs it to backward point. Retains the strike with a single.
Bowls this one full and moving away outside off, Daryl Mitchell covers hi off stump and leaves the ball alone.
Another full delivery shaping away outside off, Daryl Mitchell takes a stride forward and does not offer a shot.
Keeps it full and on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell gets forward to defend but gets an inside edge that rolls in front of square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Kasun Rajitha bowls this one on a length and outside off, Tim Southee allows the ball to come to him and guides this past backward point for a boundary.

FOUR! Pitches this one full and outside off, Tim Southee goes for a big heave across the line but gets a thickish outside edge that flies down to third man. Dinesh Chandimal runs around and puts in a valiant effort but does not manage to prevent the boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stunning catch by Lahiru Kumara! Kasun Rajitha bowls this one on a length and on middle and leg, Tim Southee clips this one from the crease. Had no intention of keeping his shot along the ground and pays the price. Lahiru Kumara at deep square leg runs to his right and flings himself to complete a brilliant catch. Sri Lanka will be relieved to see the back of Tim Southee as runs were starting to flow for New Zealand.
Howout: c Lahiru Kumara b Kasun Rajitha

Commentary: On a good length on leg, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and keeps it out.
Short and outside off, Daryl Mitchell cuts his one along the ground to deep point and settles for a single.
Banged in short and on middle, Matt Henry sways away and lets it go through to the keeper.
Touch fuller and shaping away outside off, Matt Henry throws his hands at the ball but does not connect.
Length delivery sliding down the leg side, Matt Henry goes for the clip but misses.
Good-length delivery on middle, Matt Henry gets across to work it on the leg side but closes the bat face early. Gets a leading edge that falls in front of point and batters cross for a single.

A stifled appeal for caught behind but turned down! Bowls this one full but down the leg side, Matt Henry tries to help it fine but misses. Niroshan Dickwella thought he heard a noise and went up in appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Full and outside off by Kasun Rajitha, Matt Henry goes for the drive but gets beaten.
Fuller and on leg, Matt Henry tries to clip this one off his toes but fails to connect.
On a length on middle, Matt Henry looks to drive this one down the ground but gets an inside edge that rolls in front of fine leg. A couple of runs taken.
Full and in the channel outside off, Matt Henry watchfully blocks this one towards backward point.
Keeps it full and moving away outside off, Matt Henry goes for the drive away from his body and gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell opts not to offer a shot and lets it go.
Keeps it on a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms once again.
Goes full and on off, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and works it towards deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Asitha Fernando bowls this one full and around off, Matt Henry lets his hands flow and drives it on the up. Gets it through covers and picks up a boundary.
Fullish delivery angling in on leg, Matt Henry gets beaten on the inside edge as he looked to access the leg side.
Good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Matt Henry swings his bat at it but fails to connect.
Length delivery, sliding down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell clips this one to deep square leg for a run.
On a length around off, Matt Henry hangs back to defend but gets an inside edge back onto his front pad.
Goes full and swinging away outside off, Matt Henry swipes across the line but finds square leg.
Shortens his length and bowls it on off, Matt Henry backs away and lets it be.
Full and on middle and leg, Matt Henry accounts for the away movement and plays it to mid on.
FOUR BYES! Full and slanting down the leg side, Matt Henry goes for the clip but misses. Niroshan Dickwella behind the wicket dives to his left but to no avail. Four more runs for New Zealand.
On a length on middle by Asitha Fernando, Daryl Mitchell waits for it and places this one in the vacant mid-wicket region. Comes back easily for the second run.
Length delivery in the channel outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets on the front foot and keeps this one out.

FOUR! Full and drifting onto the pads, Daryl Mitchell does not miss out as he gets a fine tickle on it and beats Niroshan Dickwella to his left. The ball races away to the fence and New Zealand now trail by 100 runs.
Full and on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell knocks this one down to long on for a run.
Short of a length but down the leg side, Matt Henry gets his gloves out of the way and lets it go through to the keeper.
Back of a length on leg, the ball nips back in after pitching, Matt Henry tries to clip this one but does not get any bat on it.
Good-length delivery on middle by Kasun Rajitha, Daryl Mitchell allows the ball to come to him and taps this one in the vacant mid-wicket region for a brace.
Goes full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends this one to the right of the bowler. Kasun Rajitha fumbles in his follow-through and concedes a single.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Short and outside off, sits up nicely for the batter, Matt Henry stands tall and punches this one hard and past backward point for a boundary.
Banged in short around off by Kasun Rajitha, Matt Henry rolls his wrists and pulls it along the ground but fails to get it past square leg.
Continues to go short and on off, Matt Henry sways away and leaves the ball alone.
Switches to 'round the wicket and bowls a short delivery at the batter, Matt Henry moves to the off side to help this one fine but connects with thin air.
Full and slanting in on leg, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and pushes it down to long on for a run.
Back of a length and angling in on middle, Matt Henry fends this one from the crease towards point.
Goes short this time and outside off, Matt Henry opts to leave the ball alone.
On a good length and on middle and leg, Matt Henry gets behind the line and keeps this one out.
Another bumper on middle by Lahiru Kumara, Matt Henry sways away and lets it go through to the keeper.

Bowls this one full and angling in on leg, Matt Henry gets into the shot early and ends up chipping this one uppishly towards mid on. Luckily for him, the ball falls way short of Dinesh Chandimal there.
Kasun Rajitha serves a length ball, on leg stump. Daryl Mitchell blocks it watchfully on his front foot.
A short ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell stands tall to defend it back to the bowler.
It is full, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it through the gap at mid-wicket for two runs.

A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! Sri Lanka do not have any reviews left, so they cannot question the umpires decision here. A length ball, that lands outside off and nips in off the deck. Daryl Mitchell prods and tries to defend it away but gets pinged high on his pads here. Kasun Rajitha pleads rather than making an appeal here but the umpire does not raise his finger.
Fuller, on middle. Daryl Mitchell knocks it down to long on for a single. New Zealand now trail by 88 runs.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly.
Lahiru Kumara starts with an inswinger, full and on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it out under his eyes here.
A length ball, that nips in a touch outside off. Daryl Mitchell steps across and offers full face of the bat.
It is on a length, wide of off. The ball jags back in sharply. Daryl Mitchell though trusts the bounce on this occasion and shoulders his arms at it.
Shorter, on the body. Daryl Mitchell pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
A dot now! Lahiru Kumara dishes a length ball, outside off. It comes back in. Matt Henry uses the depth of his crease to defend it out.
A well-directed short ball, around off. Matt Henry sways away from the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Daryl Mitchell greets the spinner into the attack with a boundary here. Prabath Jayasuriya under pressure straightaway. It is a full toss, on off. Daryl Mitchell premeditates the reverse sweep, and runs it down to third man for four runs. Daryl Mitchell into the 90s.
Full and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it on his front foot.
Darted on the pads, Daryl Mitchell clips it to the leg side.
Floated and full, on middle. Daryl Mitchell paddles it down to fine leg and collects a brace.
It is full, on middle and leg, coming in with the arm. Daryl Mitchell goes back and blocks it into the deck.
Daryl Mitchell uses his feet this time, gets to the pitch of the ball and knocks it down to long off for a single. Clever batting by Mitchell, he retains the strike here.
Lahiru Kumara fires in an inswinger, full and on off, at 140 clicks. Daryl Mitchell works it towards mid on and crosses.
Lahiru Kumara comes 'round the wicket and serves a short ball, way down the leg side. Matt Henry thinks about riding the bounce here but fails to put it away.
It is a length ball, on the body. Matt Henry shuffles and heaves it across the line to deep square leg. One taken.
Daryl Mitchell now rotates the strike as he pulls this short one behind square on the leg side. He moves to 97.
Lahiru Kumara dishes a short ball, down leg. Matt Henry fails to pull it away.
Matt Henry sees off the over successfully. Lahiru Kumara finally sneaks in a full-length delivery, but down leg. Matt Henry shuffles way inside and tries to clip it away, but misses it.
Floated and full, outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets forward and blocks it out.
Full and on off, blocked on the front foot.
Much fuller, coming in with the arm. Daryl Mitchell remains solid in his defense.
Prabath Jayasuriya fires it full, on leg. Daryl Mitchell tucks it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
A full toss, on off. Matt Henry pushes it back to the bowler.
A bit flat, on off. Matt Henry defends it out on his front foot. So just a single off the over.
A length ball, sliding down the leg side. Daryl Mitchell fails to put it away.
Lahiru Kumara dishes it full, outside off. It nips in a touch. Daryl Mitchell steps outside to block but gets an inside edge on his pads.

CENTURY FOR MITCHELL! What an innings, an extraordinary one. Everyone in the ground is on its feet. Daryl Mitchell rocks back to this short ball and cuts it past point. The batters take two runs. Daryl Mitchell jumps and punches in the air. Daryl Mitchell has certainly anchored the innings for his side here.
Fuller, on off. Daryl Mitchell pushes it out for one.
A sharp bouncer on middle. Matt Henry tries to hook it away but gets no where near the ball.
Lahiru Kumara fires in a yorker-length delivery, in the blockhole. Matt Henry gets his blade down in time to deal with it. New Zealand now trail by 73 runs.
Floated and full, outside off. Daryl Mitchell drives it down to long off for one.
FOUR! Matt Henry now joins the party. He also gets the 50-run stand in fine fashion. It is full and on off. Matt Henry dances down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for four runs.

FOUR! Consecutive boundaries. Prabath Jayasuriya overcompensates this time and goes short, outside off. Matt Henry frees his arm and cuts it hard through point. The ball races away and the cheers get even louder.
Fuller, in-line with the stumps. Matt Henry defends it on his front foot.
Looped up, around off. Matt Henry pushes it to the off side.
Tosses it up, full, on middle and leg. Matt Henry presses forward and blocks it into the deck.
An inswinger, full and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it on his front foot.
Full-length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell steps across and taps it to the off side.
Good-length delivery, in the channel. It climbs on the batter. Daryl Mitchell shuffles across but does not go through with his shot here.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Daryl Mitchell's long lasting innings finally comes to an end. Lahiru Kumara is absolutely pumped up. Lahiru Kumara fires in a full-length ball, angles it in on fourth stump. The ball nips away off the deck, just enough to finally catch the outside edge of Daryl Mitchell's blade. Niroshan Dickwella dives to his right and takes a sharp catch here.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary: Neil Wagner gets off the mark instantly. It is a length ball, angling across, outside off. Neil Wagner punches it off his back foot through covers for a single.
A sharp bouncer, on leg. Matt Henry goes chasing but gets no bat on it.
Full and on off. Neil Wagner blocks it off the inner half.
Neil Wagner steps outside the crease and defends this full one back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off. Neil Wagner tucks it to short leg.
Tosses it up, full and on off. Neil Wagner comes down the track, readjusts and blocks it out to the leg side.
Full and on off, blocked to the off side.
Dhananjaya de Silva goes full, attacking the stumps. Neil Wagner goes back to defend.
Back of a length, sliding down leg. Matt Henry tries to hook it away but misses.
A sharp bumper, on off this time. Matt Henry sways away.
Fuller, on the pads, Matt Henry flicks it to deep square leg. Dhananjaya de Silva does enough in the deep to save the boundary. Two taken.
A good-length ball, on off. Matt Henry shuffles and tries to heave it across the line. He misses and takes a blow on his elbow. This must be painful.
Length ball, on top of off. Matt Henry shuffles across and blocks it watchfully.

LEG BYE! Lahiru Kumara appeals for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. It is a full-length ball, around leg. It comes back in to hit Matt Henry on the pads. The ball rolls out to the off side. They cross for a leg bye. It is certainly pitching outside leg.
Fuller and on off. Matt Henry sweeps it to deep square leg and collects a brace.
On off, blocked out on the front foot.
On the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket.
A single now as this is played down to long on.
Full and on off. Neil Wagner defends it away watchfully.
Dhananjaya de Silva tosses it up, full and on middle, it is coming in with the arm. Neil Wagner prods and tries to defend it on his front foot. He gets an inside edge on his pads.
Fuller, on off, Matt Henry defends it out solidly.
It is a full again, on leg. Matt Henry nudges it to the leg side.
Good length, in the channel. Matt Henry shuffles and pushes it to point for a single.

Good fielding! It is a short ball, on off. Neil Wagner rides the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg. Neil Wagner finds the gap as well, although Prabath Jayasuriya puts in a valiant effort in the deep. He pulls the ball back mid-air and saves two runs here. Also with that 300 is up for New Zealand.
Full length, outside off. Neil Wagner drives it into covers. He connects well but could not find the gap.
SIX! BANG! Neil Wagner is having some fun with the bat here. It is a short ball, on off. Neil Wagner swivels, pulls it hard and flat over the square leg fence for a biggie.

SIX! Matt Henry gets into the act now! Dhananjaya de Silva floats this one full around leg from 'round the wicket, Matt Henry shimmies down the track and slogs it well over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
SIX! Back-to-back sixes! Tosses this one full on leg, Matt Henry clears his front leg and heaves this one towards cow corner for yet another maximum.

FOUR! Shortens his length and bowls it on middle, Matt Henry moves to the leg side and cuts it hard towards extra cover. A fumble there helps Henry's cause and he picks up a boundary. New Zealand now trail by 32 runs.
Goes full and at the stumps, Matt Henry hoicks across the line to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short and on middle, Neil Wagner steps out to go on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Short and on off, Neil Wagner solidly defends this one down the wicket.

FOUR! Slower and into the wicket on leg by Asitha Fernando, Matt Henry gets inside the line and waits for the ball to arrive. Goes for the pull but gets if off his gloves and wide of the keeper for a boundary.
Short and at the batter from 'round the wicket, Matt Henry goes for the pull again but does not connect this time.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Matt Henry whips this one off the back foot to deep backward square leg for a single.

SIX! Sri Lanka are losing the plot here! Asitha Fernando continues to go short and bowls it at the batter, Neil Wagner takes on the short ball and attempts a pull shot. Gets a top edge that travels well over fine leg for a maximum.
Short again and on middle, Neil Wagner looks to pull this one hard on the leg side but connects with thin air.
Switches to 'round the wicket and bowls it on a length on middle, Neil Wagner hangs back and works it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! FIFTY for Matt Henry! Kasun Rajitha bowls it short and outside off, Matt Henry slashes hard at the delivery and gets a thickish outside edge that goes over the slip cordon for a boundary. Brings up his 4th Test fifty.
FOUR! Kasun Rajitha bowls it on a length and sliding down the leg side, Matt Henry stays inside the line and gets a fine tickle on it. Gets it well wide of fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Matt Henry is scoring runs for fun here. It is a good-length ball, outside off. Matt Henry slaps it hard, over mid off for four runs.
SIX! BANG! 350 up for New Zealand. Matt Henry is not stopping here. It is full, on off. Matt Henry gets under it and tonks it over the bowler's head for a biggie. New Zealand now trail by 2 runs.

FOUR! A loopy delivery, full outside off, Matt Henry waits for it and drills this one on the off side. Gets it right in the gap between deep backward point and deep cover for yet another boundary. Remarkably, New Zealand now lead by 2 runs.
Goes pace up this time and bowls it on middle, Matt Henry heaves this one wide of long on for a couple of runs. What an over in the context of the game.
On a length and angling in on middle, Neil Wagner blocks this one out off the back foot.
Tad short and around off, Neil Wagner guides this one past backward point and takes a single.
Bowls this into the wicket and at the batter, Matt Henry goes for the pull but gets cramped for room and fails to get it away.
Full and swinging in on leg, Matt Henry looks to go down the ground but gets beaten on the inside edge.

OUT! TIMBER! Asitha Fernando nails the yorker at the stumps, a hint of tail back into the batter, Matt Henry clears his front leg and swings his bat at it. Misses it altogether and sees his woodwork rattled. Asitha Fernando is delighted and so he should be. End of a stunning innings by Matt Henry.
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Keeps it full and around off, Blair Tickner gets his bat down in time and squeezes it to deep backward point for a single.
On a good length and shaping away outside off, Blair Tickner does not go chasing the delivery and lets it go.
Full and sliding down the leg side, Blair Tickner goes for the clip but does not connect.
Good-length delivery outside off, Blair Tickner shapes to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and drifting at the pads, Blair Tickner clips it to deep square leg for a single.
SIX! Kasun Rajitha bowls this one slower and full outside off, Neil Wagner picks the change of pace and gets into a good position. Heaves this one towards the mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
Fullish delivery on off, Neil Wagner knocks it down to long off and retains the strike with a single.
Angled in full and at the stumps from 'round the wicket, Neil Wagner shapes to scoop this one but toe-ends it to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! The runs continue to flow for New Zealand! Asitha Fernando misses his length and bowls a low full toss outside off, Neil Wagner does not miss out though as he drives this one along the ground on the off side. Places it to the right of deep cover for a boundary.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Bowls this one back of a length and on middle, Neil Wagner swivels his crease to whip this one on the leg side but gets a top edge. The ball carries all the way to deep backward square leg where Dhananjaya de Silva runs forward and takes a good catch. Asitha Fernando has his fourth wicket and that brings an end to New Zealand's innings.
Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Starts with a full delivery swinging away outside off, Oshada Fernando gets forward and leaves the ball alone.
On a good length and shaping way outside off, Oshada Fernando pokes at the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good-length on off, Oshada Fernando hangs back and keeps it out on the off side.
Lands it full and outside off, Oshada Fernando takes a stride forward to defend but gets beaten by the away movement.
Fuller and going away around off, Oshada Fernando gets lured into the drive but the away movement takes the ball away from him.
On a length on middle, Oshada Fernando gets behind the line and keeps it out.
Matt Henry right on the money straightaway! Serves it full and swinging in around off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets forward to defend but gets beaten.
Fuller in length on off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets on the front foot and blocks this one out.
Banged in short and on middle by Matt Henry, Dimuth Karunaratne awkwardly ducks under the delivery and lets it go.
Full and around off, Dimuth Karunaratne takes a big stride forward and defends it down the wicket.
Goes full and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks this one out on the leg side.

A shout for LBW but turned down! On a good length on off by Matt Henry, Dimuth Karunaratne opts not to offer a shot and shoulders arms. The ball catches him high on the pads and New Zealand go up in unison. The umpire is unmoved and Tim Southee decides not to review.
Oshada Fernando and Sri Lanka are underway! Full and sliding onto the pads, Oshada Fernando clips ths one towards square leg and opens his account with a single.
Length delivery angling in around off, Dimuth Karunaratne covers the off stump and lets it be.
Fuller and swinging in on off, Dimuth Karunaratne presents a straight bat to go down the ground but gets beaten by the inward movement.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne leaves the ball alone.

Good-length delivery but swinging in on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the clip but does not get any bat on it. The ball goes off his thigh pad and Tom Blundell dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Full and slanting in on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks this one along the ground and through mid-wicket. The batters run three before the ball is cut off.
On a good length and angling across outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders arms and lets it go.
Fuller this time and in the channel outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne covers his off stump and leaves the ball alone.
Fuller around off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets forward to defend but gets an inside edge back onto his front pad.
Banged in short on middle by Matt Henry, Dimuth Karunaratne swivels in his crease and pulls it down to fine leg for a run.
Good-length delivery on off, the ball rears up after pitching but Oshada Fernando fends this one on the off side.

An appeal for LBW but turned down! Matt Henry bowls this one on a good length on off, the ball nips away after pitching and beats Oshada Fernando on the outside edge. The ball strikes him on the back leg and was going over the stumps.
Fuller again and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne opts not to offer a shot.
Full and swinging in on off, Dimuth Karunaratne falls over a bit but still manages to work it past square leg for a brace.
Keeps it full and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne is happy to let this one go.
Serves it on a good length around off, the ball nips away after pitching, Dimuth Karunaratne hangs back to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lands it on a length in the channel outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne accounts for the inward movement and shoulders arms.
Length delivery on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks this one off his hips to deep square leg for a single.
Bowls it on a length on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne gets behind the line and pushes it to mid on.
Brave leave! Good-length delivery around off, Dimuth Karunaratne covers the off stump and lets it go.
On a good length on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the clip but misses and gets hit in an awkward position.
Fuller this time and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne takes a stride forward and pushes it to mid on.
Full again and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne works this one towards point off the front foot and takes a single.
Bowls it full and on off, Oshada Fernando drives this one firmly but finds mid on. That will be TEA on Day 3!
Starts with a full delivery around off, Dimuth Karunaratne takes a stride forward to defend but gets it from the inner part of the bat. The ball rolls towards square leg for a single.
On a good length and shaping away outside off, Oshada Fernando hangs back and shoulders arms.
Goes full this time on off, Oshada Fernando gets on the front foot and drives it firmly to mid on.
Keeps it full and around off, Oshada Fernando drives it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Good-length delivery angling in on middle, Oshada Fernando gets across and defends it down the wicket.
Length delivery outside off, Oshada Fernando punches this one nicely on the off side but finds backward point.
Back of a length and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne gets inside the line and pulls it down to fine leg for a single.
Goes back of a length again and on off, Oshada Fernando gets cramped for room and can only defend this one on the off side.
Length delivery and angling in on off, Oshada Fernando pushes this one off the back foot to point and takes a single.
Serves it full and around off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets on the front foot and blocks it out on the off side.
On a good length and angling across outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders arms and let it go.
Keeps it on a length on off, Dimuth Karunaratne watchfully leaves the ball alone.
On a good length around off, the ball nips away after pitching, Oshada Fernando hangs out his bat to defend and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and going away outside off, Oshada Fernando gets lured on the front foot but luckily for him, he does not edge this one as he tried to defend.
FOUR! Bowls this one full and outside off, Oshada Fernando gets on the front foot an drives it wide of mid off to collect his first boundary.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it on a length on middle, Oshada Fernando solidly defends this one down the wicket.
FOUR! Banged in short and on middle by Tim Southee, Oshada Fernando stands tall and pulls it through square leg for the second boundary of the over. Sri Lanka now lead by 2 runs.
Length delivery, slanting in on leg, Oshada Fernando clips this one nicely to mid-wicket.
Good-length just outside off stump, the ball nips back in, Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
FOUR! Fraction short and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne gets the width he needs and does not miss out. Cuts it past point and picks up a boundary.
Switches to 'round the wicket and bowls it on a length around off, Dimuth Karunaratne covers his off stump and lets the ball through to the keeper.
Full and darted in on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne takes a stride forward and flicks it to mid-wicket.

Back of a length on off by Matt Henry, Dimuth Karunaratne hangs back to punch it through the off side but gets an inside edge that rolls towards silly mid off. He calls his partner for a quick single and Oshada Fernando obliges. .
Shortish delivery on middle, Oshada Fernando stays on the back foot and keeps this one out down the wicket.
Good length, outside off. Dimuth Karunaratne watches it sail past him.
It is angled in, outside off. It is wide enough to even bother Dimuth Karunaratne here.
Full this time, angled in around off. Dimuth Karunaratne gets it through covers off the leading edge. One taken.
LEG BYE! Tim Southee fires it full, down leg. Oshada Fernando fails to flick it away. The ball rolls out to square leg off his pads and they cross for a leg bye.
Tim Southee goes full, angled in, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne shuffles and tries to flick it away. He is a bit early into his shot. The ball goes to the off side off the leading edge.
Dimuth Karunaratne takes a couple of steps down the wicket to this full delivery and flicks it behind square on the leg side. One taken.
Blair Tickner starts from 'round the wicket. It is a loosener, down the leg side. Dimuth Karunaratne is unable to tickle it fine.
Blair Tickner bends his back hard and serves a short one, on middle. It flies off the deck. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it.
A sharp bouncer, once again, on leg. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it wisely.

OUT! CAUGHT! Magnificent catch by Henry Nicholls at gully! Dimuth Karunaratne grunts in agony. Blair Tickner draws the first blood here. He has an instant impact after coming into the attack. Blair Tickner angles it in, full and around off. It nips away off the deck. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to go for the booming drive, without any foot movement and only manages to find a thick outside edge. The ball flies at a rate of knots to the right of gully. Henry Nicholls there dives to his right and takes a blinder.
Howout: c Henry Nicholls b Blair Tickner

Commentary: On a length, outside off, left alone.
Fuller, on off. Kusal Mendis prods and drives it firmly towards mid off. Blair Tickner starts his spell with a wicket-maiden.
It is a length ball, that jags back in from outside off. Oshada Fernando blocks it with full face.
BEATEN! Matt Henry serves a length ball, in the channel, shaping away. Oshada Fernando hangs his blade away from his body. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Length, on off. Oshada Fernando blocks it out solidly.
It is full, outside off. Oshada Fernando drives it through the gap at covers. The batters come back for the second one.
Length and on off, defended out.
It is a short ball, on off. Oshada Fernando swivels and pulls it to square leg. One taken. Sri Lanka now lead by 13 runs.
It is fuller, angles in, around off. Oshada Fernando gets an inside edge on his pads.
FOUR! Wonderful shot. It is a good-length ball, outside off. Oshada Fernando waits for it and steers it past backward point for a cracking boundary.
Blair Tickner now dishes a length ball, on off. Oshada Fernando blocks it out watchfully.
Two dots in a row! Blair Tickner dishes it full, outside off. Oshada Fernando prods and tries to drive it away. He gets an inside edge on his pads.
Back of a length, on the body. Oshada Fernando pulls it awkwardly to deep mid-wicket. One taken.
Good length, outside off. This one nips back in sharply. Kusal Mendis is caught by surprise here. He hops inside the crease and somehow manages to block it out.
Full length, on off. Oshada Fernando gets forward and pushes it to mid on.

Matt Henry makes appeals and the umpire goes up in no time. Oshada Fernando though is not satisfied and he takes the review here. Coming to the delivery, it is a length ball, that lands outside off and jags back in. Oshada Fernando tries to defend it on his front foot. The ball beats the inside edge and raps him on the pads. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking though shows that the ball is flying over the wickets. The on-field decision has to be overturned here.
On a length, on fifth stump. It shapes away. Oshada Fernando shuffles and leaves it alone.
Full length, on the pads, Oshada Fernando flicks it to square leg for a single.
Kusal Mendis taps this full ball to covers and scampers across for a quick single.
It is full, angled into the pads. Oshada Fernando clips it to mid-wicket. Tim Southee keeps it down to one.
Full and around off by Blair Tickner, Oshada Fernando gets forward and turns this one to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length outside off, Kusal Mendis shoulders arms and lets it go.
Keeps it on a length in the channel outside off, Kusal Mendis stays on the back foot and defends it towards point.
Continues to bowl on a good length outside off, Kusal Mendis defends this one from the outer part of the bat to gully.
Goes touch fuller this time and outside off, Kusal Mendis does not reach out to the delivery.
Back of a length and outside off, Kusal Mendis opts not to offer a shot. A probing over by Blair Tickner.
Bowls this one back of a length and angling in on middle, Oshada Fernando solidly gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Keeps it on a good length around off, Oshada Fernando plants his front foot across and keeps this one out.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it back of a length on off, Oshada Fernando hangs back and dabs it to backward point.
Length delivery at the stumps by Matt Henry, Oshada Fernando shuffles across and works it through the vacant square leg region for a run.
Shortish delivery outside off, Kusal Mendis gets into a good position and cuts this one hard but finds backward point.
Touch fuller and outside off, Kusal Mendis is happy to let this one go through to the keeper.
Bowls this one a good length around off, the ball nips back in after pitching, Oshada Fernando gets behind the line and keeps it out on the leg side.
Banged in short and on off, Oshada Fernando rolls his wrists and pulls this one along the ground. Gets it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Smart batting by Oshada Fernando! Blair Tickner continues to go short and angling in around off, Oshada Fernando gets a bit cramped for room but still manages to ramp this one over the slip cordon for a boundary.
On a good length just outside off, Oshada Fernando drives it firmly to backward point.
Bowls this one full and on middle and leg, Oshada Fernando presents a straight bat and pushes it to mid on.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! One shot too many for Oshada Fernando! Blair Tickner bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Oshada Fernando tries to repeat the shot that fetched him a boundary earlier in the over. But, this ball is not that short and fails to ramp this one. Gets a feather on it and Tom Blundell behind the wicket makes no mistake. Blair Tickner has his second wicket and both openers are now back in the hut for Sri Lanka.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Blair Tickner

Commentary: Short of a length on off by Matt Henry, Kusal Mendis gets on his toes and punches this one wide of backward point and collects a couple of runs.
Beauty! Serves this one on a good length in the channel outside off, the ball moves away after pitching and beats Kusal Mendis on the outside edge.
Length delivery around off, Kusal Mendis gets squared up and defends it to towards gully.
A well-directed bumper by Matt Henry, bowls it at the batter, Kusal Mendis ducks and lets it go.
Back of a length on middle, Kusal Mendis stays on the back foot and turns this one towards square leg for a single. 50 comes up for Sri Lanka and the lead is now 32 runs.
Bowls it fuller and outside off, Angelo Mathews gets across to defend but gets it from the outer part of the bat towards point.

Ouch, that must have hurt! Blair Tickner bowls it on a good length on middle, the ball jags back in sharply, Kusal Mendis tries to get behind the line but gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball catches him on the thigh and he looks in a bit of pain.
Fullish delivery sliding at the pads, Kusal Mendis clips this one off his toes to deep square leg for a single.
Another full delivery at the pads, Angelo Mathews flicks this one on the leg side but does not manage to beat square leg.
On a good length on off, Angelo Mathews stays back and defends it down the wicket.
Length delivery on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews works this one from the crease to deep mid-wicket. Gets off the mark with a single.
Good-length angling in on off, Kusal Mendis gets hurried as he tried to defend this one. Gets an inside edge that rolls to fine leg for a run.
Starts with a length delivery outside off, Kusal Mendis watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Bowls it full and around off, the ball straightens after pitching and beats Kusal Mendis on the outside edge as he tried to defend.
Keeps it full and on off, Kusal Mendis solidly gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Continues to go full and outside off, Kusal Mendis is happy to let this one go through to the keeper.
Full and moving away outside off, Kusal Mendis shapes to leave but keeps his bat hanging. The ball rolls off the toe end of his bat towards the slip cordon.
Nicely bowled! Pitches this one full and swinging away around off, Kusal Mendis leans forward to defend but plays down the wrong line. A maiden by Tim Southee.
Neil Wagner fires in a full one, on off stump. Angelo Mathews uses the depth of his crease to defend it out.
Much fuller, wide of off. Angelo Mathews leans in and drives it towards extra covers. One taken.
This time it is a length ball, angled across, on off. Mendis dabs it to point.
It is pitched up, outside off. Kusal Mendis bunts it to covers.
This is sprayed well outside off, on a length. Kusal Mendis does not go after it.
Neil Wagner now hurls in a length ball, on top of off. Kusal Mendis stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Tim Southee serves it on a length, in the channel. Angelo Mathews gets it to point off the outer half.
A length ball, around off. Angelo Mathews goes back and punches it through the gap at point. They take two runs.
Full length, on fifth stump. Angelo Mathews gets behind the line and defends it out.
A length ball, on fifth stump. It flies off the deck. Angelo Mathews is way across and makes a late decision to leave it.
Angelo Mathews gets this full ball towards mid on. Matt Henry dives to his left and makes a half-stop. The batters take a single.
BEATEN! Tim Southee angles in a length ball, around off. It nips away sharply off the deck. Kusal Mendis comes across, he tries to defend it. The ball though beats the outside edge.
FOUR! Exceptional shot. It is full, angled across, wide of off. Angelo Mathews leans in and creams it through covers for four runs.
Much fuller, outside off. Angelo Mathews strokes it to mid off.
Much straighter, on a length, attacking the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it to deep square leg and crosses.

Just over! Oh wait, Devon Conway gets a hand on it, but it does not stick. Neil Wagner almost creates an opportunity out of nowhere. It is full, angled across, outside off. Kusal Mendis goes for the booming drive. The ball catches the outside edge and flies towards point. Devon Conway leaps, stretches his right-hand out but it spills out. The batters take a couple.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly.
Fuller, on off. Mendis pushes it out to safety.
Tim Southee hurls in a length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Angelo Mathews thinks about going after it but withdraws from his shot.
On off, blocked out.
A length ball, around off. Angelo Mathews defends it back to the bowler on his front foot.
It is a slower one, full and outside off. Angelo Mathews gets it to square leg off the inside edge. One taken.
A length ball, nipping in from outside off. Mendis stays back and blocks it out.
Tim Southee serves it on a good length, wide of off. Kusal Mendis lets it be. A probing over from Tim Southee comes to an end.
It is full and on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it towards mid on.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under it wisely. Is the short stuff back from Wagner?
No, not yet! It is a good-length ball, angled across. Angelo Mathews punches it to point off his back foot. Three dots in a row now.
Neil Wagner goes full, on the pads. Angelo Mathews tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, on off. Mendis blocks it out watchfully.
Neil Wagner dishes a length ball, around off. Kusal Mendis stays back and defends it out.
Bowls it on a good length and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms and lets it go.
Fuller this time and around off, Angelo Mathews leans forward and defends it on the off side.
Keeps it full and on off, Angelo Mathews drives it firmly to mid on for a dot.
Lands it on a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews is happy to let this one go through to the keeper.
Serves it fuller and on off, Angelo Mathews gets across and clips it wide of mid on for a single.
Length delivery around off, Kusal Mendis dabs this one off the back foot to point for a dot.
Back of a length on middle by Blair Tickner, Angelo Mathews works this one off hips towards fine leg for a single. .
Lands it full and outside off, Kusal Mendis frees his arms and drives it straight to cover.
On a good length and outside off, Kusal Mendis hangs back and guides it to backward point.
Length delivery outside off, Kusal Mendis shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
Goes with length again but outside off, Kusal Mendis does not bother to play this one.
Back of a length around off, the ball jags back in sharply and Kusal Mendis can only defend this one down the wicket.
Starts with a back-of-a-length delivery around off, Angelo Mathews stays on the back foot and punches it to short cover.
Bowls it on a length outside off, the ball keeps a bit low but Angelo Mathews still manages to keep this one out.
Full and angling in on off, Angelo Mathews gets forward and defends it down the wicket.
Continues to go full and just outside off, Angelo Mathews takes a good stride forward and drives it firmly to mid off.
On a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews reaches out to the delivery and pushes it to short cover.
Short of a length and on middle by Daryl Mitchell, Angelo Mathews goes back in his crease and tucks this one down to fine leg for a run.
Serves it full and around off, Angelo Mathews presents a straight bat and drives it back to the bowler. Blair Tickner gets down quickly and makes a good stop to his right.
On a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews punches this one to cover for a dot.
Goes fuller and on off, Angelo Mathews gets into a good positon and leans into the drive. Gets it to the left of mid on and collects three runs.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Kusal Mendis stands tall and plays this one under his eyes. Cuts it past point for a boundary.
Good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Kusal Mendis hangs his bat out to defend but gets beaten.
Fuller this time and at the stumps, Kusal Mendis solidly defends this one down the wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Angelo Mathews shuffles and nudges it to the leg side.
A length ball, around off. Angelo Mathews punches it to cover. Michael Bracewell makes a sharp shot and scores a direct-hit at the non-striker's end. Kusal Mendis is safely inside the crease though.
On a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews punches it to point.
