Shorter, outside off. Angelo Mathews taps it to the man at covers.
A length ball, wide of off, shaping further away. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
A maiden for Daryl Mitchell now! It is a length ball, on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it out watchfully.
Blair Tickner serves it on a length, outside off. This one jags back in with some extra bounce. Kusal Mendis watches it sail past him.
It is full, angled into the pads. Kusal Mendis tucks it to mid-wicket.

EDGED! It is a full-length ball, around off. It nips away off the deck. Kusal Mendis gets on his front foot to block it away. The ball catches the outside edge but it rolls down to the slip cordon, instead of carrying.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly.
Short ball, on off. Kusal Mendis pulls i along the ground to deep mid-wicket. They get a single.
A bit short, on the body. Angelo Mathews pulls it to the right of short fine. Henry Nicholls dives to that side and makes a sharp stop.
Back of a length, outside off. Kusal Mendis pushes it gently towards point for a single.
Much fuller, around off. Angelo Mathews steps forward and defends it to the cover region.
Short on off. Angelo Mathews stays inside the crease and blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, attacking the pads. Angelo Mathews nudges it to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Angelo Mathews gets it to deep square leg off the inside edge. One taken.
WIDE! A sharp bouncer, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under this one. The umpire signals a wide due to height here.
It is full, on off. Angelo Mathews gets it to point off the leading edge. One taken.
A length ball, that comes back in from outside off. Kusal Mendis clips it to the on side.
Good length, in the channel. It flies off the deck. Kusal Mendis lets it through to the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Blair Tickner gets third wicket of the innings. He can do no wrong in this session with the ball in hand. Fortunes have changed tremendously here for Blair Tickner. He is the same bowler who went for 103 runs in the first innings and remained wicketless then. Blair Tickner dishes a good-length ball, outside off. The ball flies off the deck. Kusal Mendis rocks back and throws his bat at it, as he looks to cut it away. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards second slip. Michael Bracewell there takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Michael Bracewell b Blair Tickner

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Prabath Jayasuriya blocks it out.
Back of a length, wide of off. Prabath Jayasuriya is happy with a sighter this time. A successful over from Blair Tickner comes to an end.
Good length, outside off. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
Much fuller, on fifth stump. Angelo Mathews blocks it on his front foot.
On a length, wide of off. Angelo Mathews has no shot to offer.
Tim Southee dishes a full one this time, around off. Angelo Mathews steps down and defends it.
Full length, on fourth stump. Angelo Mathews dabs it out to safety.
It is fuller, on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it watchfully to mid off.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under it wisely.

A loud appeal for caught behind! The umpire is unmoved. It is a short ball, outside off. Prabath Jayasuriya hangs back and tries to cut it away. There is a loud appeal from behind the sticks. Tim Southee is convinced and he takes the review. The replays confirms that there is day light between bat and ball here. Waste of a review here for New Zealand.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, on off. Prabath Jayasuriya guides it past gully. They take two runs.
Blair Tickner bends his back hard and serves a sharp bumper, on off. Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under this one.
Length, wide of off. This one stays low off the deck. Prabath Jayasuriya leaves it alone.
Good length, outside off, moving away. Angelo Mathews shoulders his arms at it.
Much fuller, on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Angelo Mathews shuffles and defends it solidly.
Tim Southee dishes a length delivery, around off. It gets some extra bounce as well. Angelo Mathews blocks it out.
Full, on middle and leg. Angelo Mathews clips it to mid-wicket.
Tim Southee goes full again, straying on the pads. Angelo Mathews nudges it to the leg side. A maiden now for Tim Southee.
Matt Henry starts with a length ball, that comes back in from outside off. Prabath Jayasuriya flicks it to the leg side.
An inswinger, full and on off. Prabath Jayasuriya defends it solidly on his front foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under this one.
Length ball, on the pads. Prabath Jayasuriya clips it to short leg.
Five dots on the trot! Good length, around off. Prabath Jayasuriya taps it out to the off side.
Matt Henry comes 'round the wicket for the final delivery of the day. A length ball, on off. Prabath Jayasuriya defends it to silly point. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Starts with a good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Keeps it on a good length but outside off, Angelo Mathews is happy to let this one go.
Persists with the same line, a bit too outside off and on a good length, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms.
Touch fuller this time and outside off, Angelo Mathews opts not to offer a shot.
Bowls this one on a good length and in the channel outside off, a hint of away movement, Angelo Mathews covers his off stump and lets it be.
A maiden to start Day 4! Length delivery just outside off, the ball nips back in a touch, Angelo Mathews accounts for the movement and shoulders arms.
Starts with a full delivery just outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya gets forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Keeps it full and straight at the stumps, Prabath Jayasuriya solidly defends this one down the wicket.
Beauty! On a good length angling in around off, the ball moves away after pitching and beats Prabath Jayasuriya as he tried to defend from the crease.
Back of a length on off by Matt Henry, Prabath Jayasuriya gets on top of the bounce and fends this one towards the slip cordon.
Goes fuller this time and on off, Prabath Jayasuriya gets forward and drives it on the up without much foot movement. Does not manage to beat Kane Williamson at mid off.
Matt Henry starts with a maiden as well! Angles this one in on a length and on leg, Prabath Jayasuriya gets beaten on the flick and gets rapped on the pads.

FOUR! Angelo Mathews and Sri Lanka are underway on Day 4! Tim Southee bowls this one on a length outside off, Angelo Mathews picks the length early and punches this one down the ground with an angled bat. Gets it past mid off and the fast outfield does the rest.
Goes full around off, Angelo Mathews gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Fuller again and outside off, Angelo Mathews gets lured into the drive to an away going delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Banged in short on off by Tim Southee, Angelo Mathews ducks and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
On a good length and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews does not chase this delivery and lets it be.
Keeps it on a good length on off, Angelo Mathews gets on his toes and does get squared up a bit. But still manages to dab this one towards point. Retains the strike with a single
Matt Henry continues to beat the bat, bowls this on a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews hangs out his bat to defend and luckily for him, he does not edge it.
Angled in fuller and on off, Angelo Mathews clips this one nicely to mid on.
A sharp bumper at the batter by Matt Henry, Angelo Mathews ducks underneath the delivery and leaves the ball alone.
Full again and nipping back in around off, Angelo Mathews plants his foot forward to defend but gets an inside edge back onto his pads.
Back of a length outside off, the ball moves away after pitching, Angelo Mathews does go reaching out to the delivery but does not get any bat on it.
Goes full this time and at the stumps, Angelo Mathews brings his wrists into play and clips this one through mid-wicket. The batters run three before Scott Kuggeleijn cuts it off.
Bowls it full just outside off, Angelo Mathews solidly gets behind the line and defends it on the off side.
Length delivery and shaping in around off, Angelo Mathews reads it well and shoulders arms.
Short of a length and outside off by Tim Southee, Angelo Mathews sways away and lets the ball go through to the keeper.

Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on a length and outside off, Angelo Mathews gets on the front foot to defend but goes at the ball with hard hands. Gets a thickish outside edge that goes a bit uppishly towards point.
Good-length delivery outside off, Angelo Mathews is happy to let this one go.
Keeps it full and outside off, Angelo Mathews does not get tempted by the length and leaves the ball alone.
Starts with a good-length delivery around off, Prabath Jayasuriya stands tall and punches this one through covers and collects a couple of runs.
Back of a length but angling down the leg side, Prabath Jayasuriya looks to help this one fine on the leg side but misses.
Lands it full and just outside off from over the wicket, Prabath Jayasuriya goes searching for the ball and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full again and on off, Prabath Jayasuriya drives it firmly down the ground where Tim Southee at mid off makes a good diving stop to his right.
Full and at the stumps, Prabath Jayasuriya gets behind the line and keeps it out on the leg side.
Shortens his length and directs it at the batter, Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under and lets it go.
Banged in short and on middle by Tim Southee, Angelo Mathews loses his balance but still manages to safely duck under the delivery.
Lands it full this time and around off, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms.
Continues to go full and outside off, Angelo Mathews opts not to offer a shot again.
Bends his back and bowls it short on off, Angelo Mathews sways away and sees the ball go through to the keeper.
Bowls it full in the channel outside off, Angelo Mathews takes a stride forward and blocks it out on the off side.
Full again and around off, Angelo Mathews solidly defends it down the wicket. Another maiden by Tim Southee.
Keeps it full and on off, Prabath Jayasuriya drives it firmly towards mid off.
On a length on off by Blair Tickner, Prabath Jayasuriya plants his foot forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and sliding down the leg side, Prabath Jayasuriya tries to tuck this towards fine leg but fails to connect.
Lands it full and just outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya gets forward and drives it through covers for a brace.
Banged in short and on off, Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under and lets it go.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Blair Tickner bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Prabath Jayasuriya stays on the back foot and pokes at the delivery away from his body. The ball catches the outside edge and Tom Blundell behind the wicket does the rest. Jayasuriya has a long chat with Angelo Mathews regarding the review but opts not to review and makes his way back. Blair Tickner adds another one to his wickets tally.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Blair Tickner

Commentary: Short of a length and going away outside off, Angelo Mathews hangs back and dabs this one towards backward point.
Short again and on off, Angelo Mathews pulls this one down to fine leg and takes a single.
Bowls it on a good length just outside off, Dinesh Chandimal watchfully defends this one back to the bowler.
Angles this one in at the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal plants his foot across and keeps it out towards mid on.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal shoulders arms.
Fuller again and around off, Dinesh Chandimal gets forward to access the off side but gets it from the inner part of the bat. The ball rolls towards square leg and batters cross for a single. .
Goes full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal takes a stride forward and pushes it a bit uppishly towards cover.
Full and just outside the off stump, Dinesh Chandimal gets on the front foot and defends it down the wicket.
On a length and shaping away outside off, Dinesh Chandimal keeps his bat hanging out to defend and gets beaten on the outside edge.

Goes searching for swing and ends up bowling it too full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leans into the drive and goes through covers. The batters run three before Devon Conway cuts it off. 100 comes up for Sri Lanka and the lead is now 82 runs.
On a good length and outside off, the ball rises after pitching, Angelo Mathews chases at the delivery and gets beaten.
Fuller this time and swinging away outside off, Angelo Mathews allows the ball to swing and drives it along the ground to mid off.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal opts not to offer a shot.
Back of a length around off, Dinesh Chandimal goes back and keeps it out on the off side.
Continues to bowl it in the channel outside off and on a good length, Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and blocks this one out on the leg side.
Goes back of a length on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes this one off the back foot to mid on.
On a good length and on off by Matt Henry, the ball keeps low but Dinesh Chandimal still manages to get his bat down in time and works it to fine leg for a run.
Lands it full around off, Angelo Mathews watchfully pushes it back to the bowler.
Keeps it on a good length around off, Dinesh Chandimal stays back and blocks it out on the off side.
Goes short this time and on off, Dinesh Chandimal gets on his toes and defends it down the wicket.
Back of a length on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes this one off the back foot towards cover.
Serves it full and around off, Dinesh Chandimal takes a good stride forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Bowls a full toss outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it firmly but finds mid off.
Shortish delivery on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal swivels in his crease and goes for the pull. Gets it off his gloves down to fine leg for a run.
Bowls it on a good length and shaping away outside off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes this one to cover for a dot.
Goes full this time and on off, at 130.6 kph, Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and defends it on the off side.
Continues to go full and around off, Dinesh Chandimal gets on the front foot to defend but gets it from the outer part of the bat towards backward point.
Full and sliding at the pads, Dinesh Chandimal does not miss out this time as he clips this one through the vacant mid-wicket region for a couple of runs.
Angled in full and on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal accounts for the inward movement and flicks it towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs more.
Back of a length outside off by Matt Henry, Dinesh Chandimal stays back and punches it to cover for a dot.
Back of a length on off, Angelo Mathews stays on the back foot and tucks it down to fine leg for a single.
Bowls it on a good length and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal misses the flick and gets hit high on the pads.
Shortish delivery outside off, Dinesh Chandimal gets on top of the bounce and pushes it to cover.
On a good length around off, the ball rears up after pitching, Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out on the off side.

In the air but just wide! Blair Tickner goes full this time and at the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal pushes at the delivery without much foot movement. Luckily for him, he plays it to the right of Blair Tickner and collects a single as the ball rolls towards mid on.
Keeps it on a good length and just outside off, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms and lets it go.

BYE! Not a dropped catch then. Matt Henry bends his back hard and serves a short one, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal tries to hook it away but misses. The ball goes over the head and swings a touch to the left of the keeper. Tom Blundell gets to hands on it but it does not stick. The batters cross and it is given as byes.
Length, on off, defended.
Short ball, on off. Angelo Mathews sways away from the line.
Matt Henry serves it full, on off. Angelo Mathews gets it to covers off the outer half.
Shorter, on leg. Angelo Mathews clips it to mid-wicket off his pads. They cross for one.
Dinesh Chandimal caught in two minds here. It is a short ball, outside off. It takes off the deck though. Dinesh Chandimal hops and gets it to point awkwardly.
Length, on the pads, tucked to the leg side for one.
Another single now as Dinesh Chandimal now clips this one towards square leg.
Good length, in the channel. Angelo Mathews shoulders his arms at it.
Back of a length, on top of off. Angelo Mathews hops inside the crease and blocks this one watchfully.
On a length, around off. Angelo Mathews remains solid in his defense.
A dot to end the over! Blair Tickner bends his back hard and dishes a sharp bumper, on middle. Angelo Mathews does not even care looking at it and ducks under it.
Good length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal tucks it towards mid on. Matt Henry is getting some bounce here.
A length ball, on off. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to the left of the bowler. Matt Henry dives to his left and parries it to extra cover.
This one is angled in, on a length, on fourth stump. Dinesh Chandimal defends it out solidly.
Back of a length, on off. Dinesh Chandimal sways away from the line this time. Not riding on the short stuff here.

FOUR! Right on cue. Dinesh Chandimal decides to ride the bounce this time. Back of a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal hops and upper cuts it over backward point. A couple of bounces over the rope.
Fuller, on fifth stump. Dinesh Chandimal strides in and defends it out.
Back of a length, in the channel. Angelo Mathews shuffles and makes a late leave.
It is much fuller, on middle and leg. Angelo Mathews clips it towards mid-wicket.
Good length, wide of off. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
Full length, in the channel. Angelo Mathews prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone without any trouble.
A maiden for Tim Southee! It is a full ball, on off, nips away a touch. Angelo Mathews defends it with full face.
Michael Bracewell starts with a full one, on off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Dinesh Chandimal now uses his feet to this full one, and clips it to short mid-wicket.
Darted on the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal lunges and blocks it into the deck.
Full, on leg. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to square leg and crosses.
Floated and full, outside off. Angelo Mathews strides in and defends it off the bottom half.
Tim Southee hurls in a length ball, that comes back in from outside off. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and defends.
FOUR! Powerfully hit. Back of a length, on off. Dinesh Chandimal gets on top of it and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
A sharp bouncer this time, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
It is full, tailing into the pads. Dinesh Chandimal clips it to mid-wicket and gets a single.
It is a full-length ball, on off. Angelo Mathews pats it back to the bowler.
Much fuller this time, wide outside off, shaping further away. Angelo Mathews shoulders his arms at it. A good end to the over. Sri Lanka now lead by 104 runs.
Floated, full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal gets to the pitch of it and flicks it down to long on for a single.
A bit quicker, and full, on off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to the left of the bowler.
FOUR! Angelo Mathews now getting into the act. It is a full delivery. Angelo Mathews gets low and sweeps this to deep mid-wicket from outside off. It races into the fence.
A single now as this is pushed to the off side.
Full and on off, blocked solidly.
Tossed up, on off. Dinesh Chandimal tucks it to short mid-wicket. 5 runs off the over.
Tim Southee goes full and on off. Angelo Mathews drives it nonchalantly towards mid off. Blair Tickner is quick to get to his right and make a stop.
Good length, outside off. Angelo Mathews makes the leave.

FOUR! Nicely played. Back of a length, on the body. Angelo Mathews heaves it across the line and places it really well to pierce the gap in the deep beind square on the leg side. The ball sneaks into the boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Almost carries! It is a full-length ball, outside off. Angelo Mathews drives it back to the bowler but off the inner half. Tim Southee collects it on a bounce.
A wild swing and a miss! Back of a length, wide outside off, shaping further away. Angelo Mathews goes after it, but misses it completely.
Fuller, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it on his front foot.
Dinesh Chandimal charges down the wicket and flicks this full ball to wide long on for a single.
Slightly short, outside off. Angelo Mathews punches it through point off the back foot. The call is for two and get it.
A single now as this is full one is knocked down to long on.
Floated and full, around off. Dinesh Chandimal uses his feet and tucks it to mid-wicket for one. He racks up 5000 runs in his Test career.
On the pads, flicked to square leg for one. Runs are coming quite easily now for Sri Lanka. The lead moves to 120 runs.
Good length, outside off. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone for the keeper.
Much fuller, but still very wide to bother Angelo Mathews as he makes yet another leave.
Shorter, too wide. Angelo Mathews cuts it to deep point but only for one as there is protection in the deep.
A dot now! Third one of the over. A length ball, wide of off. Dinesh Chandimal shuffles across and makes a good leave.

Woah! Dinesh Chandimal gets pinged on his gloves! It is a length ball, on off. It flies off the deck and catches Dinesh Chandimal by surprise here. He goes back and tries to defend it but takes a blow on his finger.
An inswinger, full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal shuffles and defends it watchfully.
Good length, on leg stump. Angelo Mathews flicks it behind square on the leg side off his hips. One taken.
Lands short! Daryl Mitchell comes 'round the wicket and goes short, on off. Dinesh Chandimal miscues his pull shot and fortunately it lands short of Michael Bracewell at square leg.
Short and on off. Angelo Mathews pulls it hard to square leg.

BYE! Daryl Mitchell hits the deck hard. It flies takes off, but down leg. Angelo Mathews gets inside the line and tries to pull it away. He misses and so does the keeper. They cross and collect a bye.
Shorter, way down leg. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
A sharp bouncer, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under this one.
It is full, outside off. Angelo Mathews prods and blocks it into the deck.
Floats it up, outside off. Angelo Mathews flicks it through mid on for one now.
Pushed through quicker, wide of off. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it towards point for a single.
Looped up, on off. Angelo Mathews flicks it past mid on for one. The stand moves to 50.
Fuller, outside off, turning in. Dinesh Chandimal shuffles and tucks it to short leg.
Dinesh Chandimal lunges forward to this full ball and defends it off the inner half.

FOUR! EDGY! Angelo Mathews gets his fifty. It is a short ball, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews heaves across the line. The ball takes the top edge and flies down to fine leg for a boundary. Angelo Mathews raises his bat for a short celebration, which is followed by a quick change for Angelo Mathews, as he wear the chest guard here.
A bouncer, on middle and leg. Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Angelo Mathews sways away this time.
Fullish, on the pads, Angelo Mathews flicks it to fine leg for one.
Back of a length, on middle.It flies off the deck. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under this one.
Length ball, on off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it watchfully.
Shorter, outside off. Angelo Mathews goes back and defends.
Floated, outside off, turning back in. Angelo Mathews pushes i to covers.
Angelo Mathews prods to this full ball and tucks it to short leg.
Full and outside off. Angelo Mathews blocks it to covers.
Another dot now! It is shorter, outside off. The ball grips and turns in sharply. It catches the gloves of Angelo Mathews as he tries to go back and punch it away. It lobs but lands safely.
Fuller, on fifth stump. Angelo Mathews shuffles and makes a solid block. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Daryl Mitchell starts from 'round the wicket. Short ball, down leg. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it down to fine leg for one.
BYE! It is a slower bumper, on leg. It nips in late.The ball goes past the keeper, but there is Scott Kuggeleijn right behind the keeper. One bye.

In the air...lands safely! The plan almost works here. It is a good-length ball, on middle and leg. It jumps off the surface. Dinesh Chandimal is taken aback. The ball catches the top half of the blade and chips in front of the keeper. Tom Blundell could not get this in time.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Once again the short one, Dinesh Chandimal gives it the same treatment, ducks under.
A sharp bumper, on leg. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under this one as well.
A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Angelo Mathews defends it watchfully.
It is full, angled into the pads. Angelo Mathews nudges it to the leg side.
Blair Tickner bends his back hard and serves a short one, on the bodyline. Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
Good length, outside off. Angelo Mathews punches it to cover off his back foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Angelo Mathews pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Blair Tickner hurls in a good-length ball, in the channel. Dinesh Chandimal gets it past backward point off the outer half. They take a single.
Daryl Mitchell continues with his ploy of short ball. He steam in 'round the wicket. It is a short ball, down leg. It carries well. Dinesh Chandimal offer no shot.
Good length, on leg. It takes off the deck. Dinesh Chandimal shoulders his arms at it. The ball goes to square leg off the thigh pads.
A sharp bumper, over the stumps. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Good length, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal hops and blocks.
Length, on leg. Dinesh Chandimal remains solid in his defense.
Short one, goes down leg. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone for the keeper. A maiden for Daryl Mitchell.
Good length, around off. It gets some extra bounce off the deck. Angelo Mathews hangs back and fends it out.
Length, outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Short one, outside off. Angelo Mathews lifts his front leg and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fuller, tailing into the pads. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to the left of mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Dinesh Chandimal pulls it to the on side for a single.
Shortish, around off. Angelo Mathews heaves it across the line to mid-wicket for another single.
OUCH! Daryl Mitchell serves it short, on off. Angelo Mathews pulls it straight down with an angled bat and hits Henry Nicholls right on top of his right foot.
Daryl Mitchell creates half-a-chance here. It is a short ball, angled down leg. Dinesh Chandimal goes for the pull shot, but does not middle it. The ball lobs off the gloves and lobs to the off side.
Short, down leg. Dinesh Chandimal pulls it down to fine leg for one.
Bouncer, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under.
Short, way down the leg side. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.

How has this missed the stumps? Daryl Mitchell working hard with the ball here. He almost gets rewarded for the same. Back of a length, on off. Angelo Mathews thinks about taking it out and goes for the pull shot. The ball takes the inside edge, sneaks past the stumps, towards fine leg. One taken.
Good length, on the bodyline. Angelo Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Blair Tickner now goes short, down the leg side. Dinesh Chandimal lets it be.
Short, on top of leg. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Back of a length, sliding down leg. Dinesh Chandimal does not go after it. The umpire signals two bouncers for the over.
Blair Tickner goes full, on the pads. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to square leg but Michael Bracewell makes a great stop.
Dinesh Chandimal is losing his patience here.It is a good-length ball, down leg. Dinesh Chandimal goes back and pulls it to deep square leg. One taken.
Back of a length, on off. Dinesh Chandimal hops and taps it to point.
Shortish, just outside leg. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it down to fine leg for a single.
Short ball, down leg. Angelo Mathews pulls it down to fine leg for another single.
Sharp bouncer, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal defends watchfully.
Short one, down the leg side. Left alone.
Back of a length, on the body. Angelo Mathews pulls it down to fine leg for one.
BYE! Blair Tickner now serves a short one, in the channel. Dinesh Chandimal shuffles but eventually sways away from the line. Tom Blundell parries it down to third man. They collect a bye.
Short, down leg. Left alone.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under it.

FOUR! A welcome boundary for Sri Lanka. Blair Tickner continues the short ball treatment, down leg. Angelo Mathews hooks it down to deep square leg. Daryl Mitchell puts in a valiant effort in the deep but touches the ropes while handling the ball.
Short one, down leg. Angelo Mathews whips it to fine leg for a single.
A sharp bumper, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
On a good length, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews makes a good leave.
A bit slower, down the leg side, on a length. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
Short ball, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews has no shot to offer.
Angelo Mathews pulls this short one, down to fine leg. One taken.
WIDE! Daryl Mitchell bends his back hard and dishes a bumper, on middle. This one flies above the batter's head. The umpire signals a wide, as Dinesh Chandimal lets it be.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal defends it out solidly.
Flights it up, outside off. Angelo Mathews gets it back to the bowler off the inner half.
It is tossed up, around off. Angelo Mathews tries to flick it away. It bounces off his pads.
Full and on off, defended back to the bowler.
Shorter, on off. Angelo Mathews shuffles across and tucks it to short leg.
Flatter, outside off. Angelo Mathews now flicks it through square leg for a single.
Dinesh Chandimal uses his feet and flicks this full ball down to wide long on for a brace.
Daryl Mitchell continues with the short ball ploy. Back of a length, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews pulls it down to fine leg for one.
Length, on the pads. Dinesh Chandimal clips it through square leg for one.
Daryl Mitchell steams in again serves a slower bumper, on the bodyline. Angelo Mathews does not pick it up early and whips it to the leg side.
FOUR! Just short of Tom Latham at short fine. Back of a length, on leg. Angelo Mathews swivels and pulls. It almost carries to Tom Latham at short fine leg. The ball sneaks through and races away.
WIDE! A sharp bumper, on middle. Angelo Mathews ducks under. The umpire signals a wide for height.
Fuller, on the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Length, down the leg side. Left alone.
Flatter and on off. Angelo Mathews defends it out watchfully.
Fuller, on off. Angelo Mathews leans forward and clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Michael Bracewell goes full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal tucks it to the on side.
Shorter, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal cuts it hard to deep point for one.
Flatter, outside off. Angelo Mathews stays back and punches it through the line to sweeper cover. One taken.
A single now as this played down to long on. The stand moves to 93 runs.
Back of a length,on leg. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it down to fine leg for a single.
Daryl Mitchell goes short, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
Slower one, short and down leg. Angelo Mathews lets it be.
Daryl Mitchell drags his length ball, down the leg side. Angelo Mathews heaves it across the line to deep square leg and collects a brace.
A single now as this short ball is pulled down to fine leg.
It is fuller this time, attacking the pads. Dinesh Chandimal clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and defends it out
A single now as this is flicked down to long on.
On the pads, tucked to square leg for one.
A single now as this is eased towards mid on.
Short one, outside off. Angelo Mathews chops it to point and gets a single.
It is full, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal clips it to the leg side.
Starts with a good-length delivery and swinging away outside off, Angelo Mathews leaves the ball alone.
Bowls it touch fuller and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews is happy to let this one go as well.
Angles it on a length and moving away around off, Angelo Mathews lets it be.
On a good length and swinging away outside off, Angelo Mathews does not reach out to the delivery and lets it go.
There comes the in dipper by Tim Southee, bowls it on a length and around off, Angelo Mathews reads it well and works it to mid on.
Goes back to the outswinger on a length outside off, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms.
Leg bye! Back of a length and slanting in on leg, Dinesh Chandimal looks to tuck this one but gets hit high on the front pad. The ball rolls behind square for a single.
On a good length around off, Angelo Mathews hangs back and defends it down the wicket.
Keeps it full and at the stumps, Angelo Mathews brings his wrists into play and flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs. 200 comes up for Sri Lanka.
Length delivery on off, Angelo Mathews gets behind the line and blocks this one out.
Bowls it on a length and angling down the leg side, Angelo Mathews gets inside the line and leaves the ball alone.
On a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews withdraws his bat and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Lands this one full and going away outside off, Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and sees the ball go through to the keeper.

OUT! TIMBER! The new ball does the trick for New Zealand! This is a peach of a delivery by Tim Southee. Bowls this one with a wobble seam and allows the ball to nip back in after pitching, Dinesh Chandimal plays for the away going delivery and pays the price. Gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball sneaks through the gap between the bat and pad to disturb the woodwork. A much-needed breakthrough for New Zealand.
Howout: b Tim Southee

Commentary: Serves this one a good length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva accounts for the away movement and shoulders arms.

FOUR! Edgy! Bowls this one full and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and defends this one with soft hands. The ball catches the outside edge and runs through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Another outswinger outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva watchfully lets it go.
Goes full this time around off and moving away, Dhananjaya de Silva gets on the front foot to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Banged in short and on middle by Matt Henry, Angelo Mathews quickly ducks under.
Lands it full and on middle, Angelo Mathews rolls his wrists and flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
On a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews reaches out to the delivery and dabs it to point.
Length delivery honing at the pads, Angelo Mathews tucks this one down to fine leg for a single.
Goes full and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets lured on the front foot, the ball nips away after pitching and beats him on the outside edge.
Another full delivery in the channel outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva takes a forward to defend but the away movement takes the ball past his outside edge.
FOUR! Tim Southee bowls this one full and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews defends this one late and with an angled bat. The ball takes the outside edge and rolls past point for a boundary.
Good-length delivery around off, Angelo Mathews taps it to point and takes a single.
On a good length outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva pushes at the away going delivery and plays it to gully.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on a good length around off, Dhananjaya de Silva is happy to let this one go.
Bowls it full and around off, a hint of away movement, Dhananjaya de Silva gets on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva shoulders arms. A probing over by Tim Southee.
Bowls this one full and outside off, Angelo Mathews takes a stride forward but the ball jags back in sharply. Beats Mathews on the inside edge.
Back of a length on middle by Matt Henry, Angelo Mathews gets cramped for room and looks to work it on the leg side. Fends this one a bit uppishly down the wicket.
On a good length and going away outside off, Angelo Mathews pokes at the delivery and luckily for him, he does not edge this one.
Serves it full and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews hangs out his bat to defend without much foot movement. The ball zips past the outside edge.

Testing times for Angelo Mathews. Matt Henry bowls it on a good length around off and allows the ball to nip back in. Angelo Mathews gets caught on the crease as he looks to defend and wears the ball on the gloves.
Continues to go on a good length and outside off, Angelo Mathews reads it well and shoulders arms.
Good-length delivery going away outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva lets it go.
Full and swinging away outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the drive but mishits back to the bowler.
Goes wide of the crease and keeps it on a good length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva watchfully leaves the ball alone.
FOUR! Length delivery around off by Tim Southee, Dhananjaya de Silva goes at the delivery with soft hands. Gets an outside edge that rolls through the slip cordon for a boundary.
On a good length but sliding down the leg side, Dhananjaya de Silva lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Touch fuller around off, Dhananjaya de Silva works it to point for a dot.
Sees the batter step out and bangs it short on off, Angelo Mathews ducks under.
On a good length and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews gets into an awkward positon but does not chase the delivery.
Length delivery on off and tailing back into the batter, Angelo Mathews gets hurried and gets hit high on the pads.
Bowls it fuller at the stumps, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and gets behind the line to keep this one out.
Keeps it full on off, Angelo Mathews takes a good stride forward and drops it on the leg side for a run.
Another full delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva flicks this one down to fine leg for a single.
Starts with a good-length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva nudges this one to square leg for a single.
Back of a length around off, Angelo Mathews hangs back and defends it on the off side.
Fuller and slanting at the pads, Angelo Mathews helps this one down to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Bowls this one a good length around off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes back to punch this one on the off side. The ball catches the inside edge of his bat and races away towards the fine leg fence.
Goes full this time and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and blocks this one out.
Shortish delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva picks the length early and pulls it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Matt Henry bowls it full and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva presents a full face of the bat and drives it a bit uppishly but to the left of the bowler for a boundary.
On a good length and shaping away outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva pokes at the away going delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short of a length at the batter, Dhananjaya de Silva uses his feet and nudges this one to square leg for a single.
WIDE! Bends his back and bangs it short on middle, Angelo Mathews ducks under and lets it go. The umpire signals a wide for height.
Another bumper around off, at 132.1 kph, Angelo Mathews sways away and leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length and angling in at the batter, Angelo Mathews takes his bottom hand off the bat and flicks it down to fine leg for a run.
On a good length and shaping in on middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva solidly keeps this one out.
FOUR! Blair Tickner goes short this time and outside off, the ball sits up nicely for the batter, Angelo Mathews shuffles across and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Moves to 99.

HUNDRED for Angelo Mathews! Back of a length and outside off, Angelo Mathews picks the length early and allows the ball to come to him. Punches this one through covers and collects a boundary. Roars in delight and raises his bat to his teammates. Brings up the 14th Test hundred of his career.
Short of a length on off, Angelo Mathews goes for the pull and gets it towards backward square leg for a single.
Fuller and moving away outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva leans forward and drives it to mid off for a single.
FOUR! Blair Tickner continues to go short and bowls it on leg, Angelo Mathews gets inside the line and pulls it towards the fine leg fence for the third boundary of the over.
Bowls it on a good length and shaping away outside off, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms and lets it go. An expensive over by Blair Tickner. 14 runs came off it.

Bowls it full and around off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the drive away from the body. Ends up chipping this one uppishly towards extra cover. Luckily for him, the ball falls short of Kane Williamson stationed there.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva defends this one to point.
On a good length and outside off, the ball nips away after pitching, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lands it full and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets tempted by the length and goes for a big booming drive but connects with thin air.
Full and at the stumps, Dhananjaya de Silva clips this one straight to mid-wicket.
Leg bye! Length delivery sliding down the leg side, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the flick but misses. The ball comes off his pads and rolls to fine leg for a single. Final over before Tea coming up.
Bowls it full and in the channel outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Keeps it full again and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva pushes hard at the ball and fails to control his drive along the ground. But, the ball falls just short of point.
Another full delivery on off by Tim Southee, Dhananjaya de Silva solidly gets behind the line.
FOUR! Glorious by Dhananjaya de Silva Angled in full around off, Dhananjaya de Silva picks the length early and drives it back past the bowler for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up.
On a good length outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva defends this one on the off side.
Full and honing in at the stumps, Dhananjaya de Silva keeps this one out on the off side. That will be TEA on Day 4!
Blair Tickner pitches it up, on fourth stump. Angelo Mathews leans forward and drives it down the ground. They take two before the fielder cuts it out.
Full length, on the pads. Angelo Mathews flicks it down to fine leg for a single.
Full length, tailing back in from outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it with a straight bat.
Length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva taps it to covers. There is an overthrow and the batters cross.
Another single now! Fuller, on middle. Angelo Mathews clips it to deep square leg and crosses.
Good length, sliding down leg. Dhananjaya de Silva does not go after this one.
Full length, on the pads. Angelo Mathews tucks it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and defends this good length ball to the off side.
Short ball, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Angelo Mathews swivels and heaves it across the line to deep square leg.Two taken.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matt Henry strikes and gets rid of Angelo Mathews here. New Zealand will be delighted to see the back of Mathews here. He veteran walks off the field to a standing ovation for his sensational knock of 115 runs. Matt Henry hurls in a length ball, that is angled in outside off. This one nips away a touch. Angelo Mathews tries to defend it away from his body and this time overcommits to his shot. The ball catches the outside edge and flies towards the keeper. Tom Blundell makes no mistake behind the sticks.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary: On a length, around off, defended out.
Blair Tickner serves it on a length, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it on his front foot.
It is a bit full, jagging back in from outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva remains solid in his defense here.
Full, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva dabs it towards the slip cordon.
FOUR! Nicely played. Blair Tickner dishes a full-length ball, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva drives it down the park for four runs.
Dhananjaya de Silva now pulls this short one to deep mid-wicket for just a single.
Short one, outside off. Left alone.
Good length, around leg. Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Much fuller, on fourth stump, angling across. Niroshan Dickwella gets behind the line to defend it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matt Henry has turned the game on its head. He takes two wickets in quick succession to put Sri Lanka in a spot of bother. It is a good-length ball, in the channel, slanting across. Niroshan Dickwella is caught inside the crease. He tries to feel for it but without moving his feet. The ball takes the outside edge and Tom Blundell takes a sharp catch behind the sticks.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary: Fuller, angled into the pads. Kasun Rajitha gets it to point off the outer half.
Shortish, in the channel. Kasun Rajitha defends it out solidly.
BEATEN! Matt Henry angles in a length ball, outside off and gets it to shape away just enough to beat the outside edge.
Short ball, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva taps it to point and crosses.
A sharp bouncer, over the stumps. Kasun Rajitha ducks under it.

FOUR! Positive from Kasun Rajitha. Blair Tickner serves a short one, down leg. Kasun Rajitha makes some room and throws the kitchen at it. The ball takes the top-edge and flies down to the fine leg fence for four runs.
Back of a length, outside off. Kasun Rajitha shuffles and lets it be.
Blair Tickner bends his back hard. A bouncer, on middle and leg. Kasun Rajitha sways away. He has a smile across his face seeing the short ball attack on him.
Length, on the pads, clipped to the on side.
Fuller around off, Dhananjaya de Silva take a stride forward to defend. The ball rolls off the inner part of the bat towards square leg. Kasun Rajitha wants a single but gets sent back.
On a good length and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the cut but misses.
Short of a length on off by Matt Henry, Dhananjaya de Silva rides on top of the bounce and pulls it wide of deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva dabs this one to point for a single.
Back of a length shaping away outside off, Kasun Rajitha hangs out his bat to defend and gets beaten.
Good-length delivery outside off, Kasun Rajitha shoulders arms and lets it go.
Lands it on a good length and on middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the clip but misses and gets hit high on the front pad.

A loud appeal for caught behind turned down! Bowls it full and in the channel outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva leans forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. There was a noise as the ball went past the bat but the UltraEdge shows no spike.
Fuller outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva pushes away from the body and luckily for him, he does not edge this one.
Back of a length outside off by Blair Tickner, Dhananjaya de Silva works it towards point and takes a single.
Short and on middle, Blair Tickner drops his wrists and leaves the ball alone.
Goes full and at the stumps, Kasun Rajitha was backing up for a short delivery but gets his bat down in time and plays it to mid on for a run.
Bowls it on a good length around off, Kasun Rajitha hangs back and pushes it to point for a single.
Tad short and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the cut but gets a bottom edge that goes on the bounce towards the slip cordon.
Switches to good length and outside off, the ball nips away and zips past the outside edge of Dhananjaya de Silva's bat.
Fuller and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva drives it firmly back to the bowler. Matt Henry does not mange to stop this in his follow-through and concedes a single.
Length delivery angling in on leg, Kasun Rajitha looks to nudge it on the leg side but gets an inside edge. The ball comes off his pads and rolls to square leg for a run.
On a good length and shaping away outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva chases the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length on off by Blair Tickner, Kasun Rajitha dabs this one off the back foot towards point.
Another back-of-a-length delivery sliding down the leg side, Kasun Rajitha nudges this one on the leg side but finds leg slip.
Switches to 'round the wicket and angles it in short and at the batter, Kasun Rajitha fends this one on the off side.
Short and outside off, Kasun Rajitha stays leg side of the ball and slaps it over extra cover. The ball plugs in the outfield and batters run three.
Short again and on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva swivels in his crease and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Banged in short and at the batter, Kasun Rajitha takes his bottom hand off the bat and awkwardly fends it on the off side.
On a good length around off by Matt Henry, Dhananjaya de Silva punches it along the ground to cover for a single.

FOUR! Streaky! Keeps it on a good length on off, Kasun Rajitha plants his foot forward and presents a straight bat to defend. The ball catches the outside edge of his bat and races through the slip cordon for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Matt Henry strikes and removes Kasun Rajitha!  Goes full and straight at the stumps. Kasun Rajitha plants his foot across and goes for the clip. He fails to get any bat on it and the ball catches him right in front of the stumps. New Zealand go up in unison and the umpire raises the finger. Kasun Rajitha goes for the review but the UltraEdge shows no bat and it is umpire's call on Ball Tracking. The onfield decision stands and Sri Lanka are now 8 wickets down.
Howout: lbw b Matt Henry

Commentary: On a good length and angling across outside off, Lahiru Kumara leaves the ball alone.

FOUR! Angled in full and on off, Lahiru Kumara clears his front leg and drills it back past the bowler. Matt Henry does not manage to get a hand on it in his follow through and the ball races away to the fence.
Good-length delivery on off, Lahiru Kumara swings his bat at it and misses.
A length ball, on top of off. Dhananjaya de Silva tries to be innovative now trying to scoop a fast bowler. He misses it completely.
Short ball, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva dabs it out to backward point.
Fuller, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets it to square leg off the inside edge. One taken.
Back of a length, outside off. Lahiru Kumara ducks under it.
FOUR! Top shot. It is a length ball, outside off. Lahiru Kumara picks it up nicely and lofts it over the bowler's head. A couple of bounces over the rope.
This is angled into the pads, on a length. Lahiru Kumara flicks it to the leg side.

OUT! RUN OUT! Matt Henry has done enough in the end to complete a run out with one hand. It is a short ball, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva comes down the track and lofts it down towards long off. Kane Williamson comes across. Dhananjaya de Silva calls for two runs. Kane Williamson is quick with his throw, but Matt Henry though does not collect the ball as he seems to be in some pain. Kane Williamson looks at it and is a bit frustrated. Although, luckily for Matt Henry, he is able to parry it on to the stumps. The third umpire goes through several times and eventually shows OUT on the big screen.
Howout: run out (Kane Williamson / Matt Henry)

Commentary: Shortish delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva stays on the back foot and pushes it to mid on and refuses the single.
On a length around off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for a big heave but gets an inside edge that rolls down the wicket.
Good-length delivery on off, Dhananjaya de Silva solidly keeps this one out on the off side.
Fuller around off, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to go over cover but miscues this one towards mid off. Luckily for him, the ball falls short of Tim Southee at mid off.
FOUR! Short again and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva hangs back and pulls it hard through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tim Southee starts with a full one, on off. Asitha Fernando blocks it out to covers.
Fuller, outside off. It flies off the deck. Asitha Fernando lets it be.

OUT! CAUGHT! Asitha Fernando gets in a real tangle here. Tim Southee bends his back hard now and serves a short ball, on off. It flies off the deck. Asitha Fernando bends his neck but keeps his bat way high. The ball catches the edge and flies towards Kane Williamson at gully, who takes a dolly there. Sri Lanka have been all out 302 runs.
Howout: c Kane Williamson b Tim Southee

Commentary: Kasun Rajitha starts with a full delivery, around the wicket. He gets it to swing in a touch. Tom Latham begins his innings with a solid defense.
Back of a length, in the channel. Tom Latham shuffles and leaves it alone.
Back of a length, wide of off, swinging in late. Tom Latham watches it sail past him.
Good length, angled in around off. Tom Latham blocks it watchfully.
Kasun Rajitha now drifts it in, around off and gets it to move away off the deck. Tom Latham tries to defend the wrong line here. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Length, outside off. Latham leaves it alone. A maiden for Kasun Rajitha.
Asitha Fernando dishes a good-length ball, angling across, in the channel. Devon Conway shoulders his arms at it.
Devon Conway and New Zealand are off the mark here. It is on a length, on the pads. Devon Conway tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Much fuller, sliding down leg. Tom Latham now opens his account as he clips this to deep square leg off his pads.

Asitha Fernando angles it in, full and on off. Devon Conway drives it nonchalantly back to the bowler. Asitha Fernando gets low to his left and thinks he has got a finger on it, as the ball goes on to hit the stumps at the non-striker's end. Tom Latham though is save inside the crease here.
Good length, outside off. Left alone.
Asitha Fernando now dishes a length ball, outside off. It nips away and beats the outside edge.
Good length, sliding down leg. Tom Latham fails to glance it around the corner. The ball brushes the thigh pads and goes to the left of the keeper.
Back of a length, on fourth stump. Tom Latham blocks it out solidly.

A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! Kasun Rajitha dishes a length ball, angled into middle. Tom Latham strides in and looks to block it away but gets pinged on his pads. An enquiry is made for lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
Fuller, on the pads. Tom Latham flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Kasun Rajitha fires it full, angled into the pads. Devon Conway takes a blow on his pads here.
It is a length ball, that jags back in from outside off. Devon Conway get forward to defend the one that swings away. He gets beaten on the inside edge to get hit near the groin area.
Shorter, wide of off. Left alone by Latham.
Fuller, wide of off. Tom Latham times his drive well to extra covers. The fielder makes a half-stop. One taken.
Back of a length, outside off. Devon Conway has no shot to offer.

Excellent fielding! It is a full-length ball, on fourth stump. Devon Conway crunches it to covers on his front foot. Dimuth Karunaratne makes a full-stretched dive to his right and makes a half-stop with one hand. Saves a certain boundary here.
On a length, outside off. Devon Conway hangs his blade away from his body and gets beaten in the process.
Full and on off. Conway bunts it towards mid on and crosses for a single.
A length ball, angling down leg. Devon Conway flicks it to short fine leg.
Full length, outside off. Devon Conway strides across and dabs it to point for a quick single.
It is full, straying on the pads. Latham clips it past square leg for one run.
It is full, angled into the pads. Devon Conway flicks it firmly to deep square leg and collects a brace this time.
Touch fuller, outsid off. Conway leaves it alone for the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Kasun Rajitha draws the first blood here. Sri Lanka are off to an ideal start here. They will be delighted to see the back of Devon Conway so early on. Kasun Rajitha comes from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, outside off. It just holds into the wicket a bit. Devon Conway ends up chipping it straight back towards the bowler. Kasun Rajitha jumps and takes a sharp catch above his head.
Howout: c & b Kasun Rajitha

Commentary: It is a length ball, in the channel, with some extra bounce. Tom Latham makes a good leave.
Fuller, on fifth stump. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
Three dots in a row now! On a length, wide of off, nips in late. Tom Latham is happy with yet another sighter here.
It is full, angled in on off. Tom Latham blocks it out watchfully.
Shorter, wide of off. Tom Latham watches it sail past him.
Asitha Fernando gets his first maiden of the innings. It is fuller, that lands outside off and nips in late. Tom Latham makes a solid leave.
Good-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Kane Williamson shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.
This is much fuller, outside off and nips away sharply off the deck. Kane Williamson leaves it alone for the keeper.
It is full, wide of off. Kane Williamson leans in and drives it toward extra cover but finds the fielder.
BEATEN! Kasun Rajitha angles in a length ball, on off. Kane Williamson tries to defend the main line here but gets beaten by the away swing here.
A length ball, in the channel. Kane Williamson tries to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.

EDGED! Three fielders go for it but the ball lands short. It is a full-length ball, angled in around off. It nips away after hitting the deck. The ball catches the outside edge, although it does not carry as Kane Williamson plays it with soft hands.
Angled in on off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham defends the line but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Full and sliding at the pads, Tom Latham goes for the clip but misses and wears it on the thigh.
Full and on off, Tom Latham pushes this one to mid on. A yes-no situation but Tom Latham sends Kane Williamson back in the nick of time.
A shout for LBW turned down! Full and slanting in on middle and leg, Tom Latham plants hs foot forward to defend and gets caught on the front pad.
FOUR! Asitha Fernando goes short this time and outside off, Tom Latham stands tall and cuts this one hard. Gets it past point for a boundary.
Back to the fuller length at the stumps, Tom Latham defends it with soft hands. Gets it from the outer part of the bat towards gully for a dot.

A big appeal for LBW but turned down! Kasun Rajitha bowls this one full and shaping away on off, Kane Williamson does not account for the away movement and defends down the wrong line. The ball catches him on the back leg and Sri Lanka go up in appeal. Dimuth Karunaratne has a word with the keeper and goes for the review with 2 seconds left on the timer. But, the UltraEdge shows no bat and it is missing the wickets on Ball Tracking. Kane Williamson survives and Sri Lanka lose their review.
Fuller again and on off, Kane Williamson gets behind the line and blocks it down the wicket.
Full and going away on middle, Kane Williamson does get squared up a bit but still manages to drive it to mid off.
Continues to go full around off, Kane Williamson gets on the front foot and defends this one along the ground to gully.
On a length and swinging away outside off, Kane Williamson covers his off stump and shoulders arms.

Full and drifting at the pads, it was there to be put away but Kane Williamson fails to get any bat on the flick. The ball rolls off his pads to the left of the keeper. Niroshan Dickwella moves quickly and makes a good stop.
On a good length around off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham goes back and defends it on the leg side.
Length delivery on the off stump, Tom Latham takes a good stride forward and keeps this one out.

Four Byes! Asitha Fernando loses his radar and sprays a fullish delivery way down the leg side, Niroshan Dickwella dives to his right but it was out of his reach. The ball races away to the fence for a boundary.
Fuller at the stumps, Tom Latham gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Length delivery on middle and leg, Tom Latham turns this one down to fine leg for a single.
Keeps it full and outside off, Kane Williamson is happy to shoulder arms to this delivery.
Full and swinging in on middle, Tom Latham clips this one straight to square leg.
Back of a length outside off by Kasun Rajitha, Tom Latham gets on his toes to punch it through the off side but gets a bottom edge and the ball drops at his feet.
Length delivery around the off stump, Tom Latham gets on the front foot and blocks this one out.
Full again and shaping away outside off, Tom Latham covers his off stump and lets it pass.
Length delivery going away outside off, Tom Latham leaves the ball alone.
Bowls it on a good length in the channel outside off, Tom Latham plants his foot forward and opts not to offer a shot.
On a good length around off, nips back in sharply, Kane Williamson accounts for the inward movement and shoulders arms.
This one goes the other way, good-length delivery on off, and the ball straightens after pitching. Kane Williamson gets squared up and the ball zips past his outside edge.
Continues to bowl a tight length around off, Kane Williamson does not push out hard to the delivery and lets it go.
Length delivery outside off, Kane Williamson withdraws his bat and sees the ball go through to the keeper.
Another delivery in the channel, Kane Williamson watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Good-length delivery outside off, the ball moves away and beats Kane Williamson on the outside edge.
Starts with a short delivery on off, Tom Latham whips off the back foot but does not manage to beat mid-wicket.
Short and quicker on off, Tom Latham goes back and punches it to backward point.
Fraction short and outside off, Tom Latham goes on the back foot and cuts it wide of backward point for a run.
Floats this one full at the stumps, Kane Williamson gets forward and works it to short leg.

FOUR! Kane Williamson is finally off the mark! Prabath Jayasuriya bowls it short and on off, Kane Williamson picks the length early and rocks back in his crease. Punches it past point and opens his account with a boundary.
Flighted, full on middle and leg, Kane Williamson presses forward and blocks it out.
Starts with a fullish delivery outside off, Tom Latham goes for the drive but does not manage to get it away. Gets it from the bottom part of the bat to mid off.
Bowls it back of a length just outside off, Tom Latham hangs back to defend and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good-length delivery in the channel outside off, Tom Latham watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Brave leave! This delivery jags back in sharply and goes over the stumps. Tom Latham left this trusting the bounce of the wicket.
Continues to bowl it on a good length and shaping away outside off, Tom Latham does go chasing the delivery and gets beaten again.
Another delivery on a good length around off, Tom Latham shoulders arms.
Fired in full and on middle and leg, Kane Williamson gets forward and keeps this one out.
No ball! Short and flatter at the stumps, Kane Williamson gets on the back foot and defends with a straight bat. Prabath Jayasuriya has overstepped and it is signalled as a no ball.
Flighted delivery on off, Kane Williamson keeps this one out down the wicket.
Tossed up, fuller on off, Kane Williamson leans forward and blocks it out.
Short and on middle, Kane Williamson goes back in his crease and defends it down the wicket.
Tossed up, full on middle and leg, Kane Williamson gets on the front foot to defend. Gets it from the inner part of the bat towards fine leg for a single.
Full ball, on off, blocked out.
A length ball, on off, defended out.
Fuller, on off. Kane Williamson bunts it out to the off side.
Full length, wide of off, nips in late. Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
On a good length and angling in around off, Kane Williamson shoulders arms.
Back of a length and outside off, Kane Williamson gets his gloves out of the way and lets it go.
Good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Kane Williamson stays back to defend and withdraws his bat at the last moment.
Tossed up, full on middle, Tom Latham knocks it down to long on for a single.
Full and on middle and leg, Kane Williamson presses forward and blocks it out.
Short and quicker at the stumps, Kane Williamson goes back in his crease and whips this one through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fullish delivery on off, Kane Williamson drives it to short cover where Kusal Mendis fumbles but it is backed up at mid off.
Flighted, full on middle, Kane Williamson gets forward and keeps this one out.
Short and on off by Prabath Jayasuriya, Kane Williamson cuts this one hard but finds backward point. That will be STUMPS on Day 4!
Starts from 'round the wicket and angles it in full and outside off, Tom Latham gets forward and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Keeps it full and around off, Tom Latham gets on the front foot and drives it along the ground to mid off.
Another full delivery in the channel outside off, Tom Latham accounts for the inward movement and blocks it out on the off side.
Tom Latham and New Zealand are underway on Day 5! Asitha Fernando bowls it full and angling at the pads, Tom Latham clips this one towards deep mid-wicket and collects a couple of runs.
Good-length delivery tailing in around off, Tom Latham covers his off stump and shoulders arms.
Back of a length around off, Tom Latham stays on the back foot and watchfully defends this one to point.
Starts with a full delivery drifting at the pads, Kane Williamson brings his wrists into play and works this one towards deep backward square leg. Opens his account on Day 5 with a couple of runs.
Bowls it full and just outside off, Kane Williamson presses forward and lets the ball pass.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Fullish delivery and down the leg side, Kane Williamson does not miss out as turns this one wide of fine leg for a boundary.
Good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Kane Williamson gets his gloves out of the way and leaves the ball alone.
Full and on middle and leg, Kane Williamson clips this one to mid on for a dot.
Serves it full again but outside off, Kane Williamson is happy to let this one go.
On a good length and slanting in around off, Tom Latham watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Banged in short on off by Asitha Fernando, Tom Latham hangs back and pulls it towards mid on but without any timing.
Back of a length outside off, Tom Latham dabs this one off the back foot to backward point.
Good-length and around off, the ball jags back in and bounces sharply as well. Tom Latham looks to defend but wears it on his gloves.
Another on a good length and outside off, Tom Latham shoulders arms.
Back of a length and outside off by Asitha Fernando, Tom Latham stays back and punches it on the off side but finds point.
Full and swinging away outside off, Kane Williamson does not reach out to the delivery and lets it pass.
Much straighter this time and in the channel outside off on a full length, Kane Williamson gets on the front foot and leaves the ball alone.
Lands it full and straying at the pads, Kane Williamson clips this one straight to mid-wicket.

A loud shout for LBW but turned down! Kasun Rajitha bowls it on a good length and tailing in on leg, Kane Williamson goes on the back foot and hops to whip this one on the leg side. The ball keeps a bit low and beats Williamson on the inside edge. Dimuth Karunaratne has a word with the keeper and the bowler and sends it upstairs for a review. The UltraEdge shows no bat but wickets is umpire's call on Ball Tracking. Kane Williamson survives and Sri Lanka keep their review.
Good-length delivery on off, Kane Williamson stays back and defends it on the off side.
Another delivery on a good length and shaping away outside off, Kane Williamson watchfully leaves the ball alone.
Continues to bowl from 'round the wicket and angles it on a good length and outside off, Tom Latham is happy to let this one pass.
Back of a length around off by Asitha Fernando, Tom Latham stays back and guides it along the ground to gully.
Touch fuller and honing in at the stumps, Tom Latham goes back to a full delivery but still manages to push it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length and outside off, the ball rises sharply after pitching, Kane Williamson watches it closely and leaves the ball alone.
A bit too wide outside off, Kane Williamson does not bother to play at the delivery and shoulders arms.
Bowls it on a good length in the channel outside off, the ball keeps low this time, Kane Williamson hangs back to defend and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller around off by Kasun Rajitha, Tom Latham takes a good stride forward and keeps this one out.
Serves it on a good length and seaming away outside off, Tom Latham covers his off stump and leaves the ball alone.
FOUR! Kasun Rajitha bowls this one on a length and outside off, Tom Latham gets the width he needs and frees his arms. Drives it past point and collects a boundary.
Fuller this time and outside off, Tom Latham goes for the drive but mishits this one back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, Tom Latham hangs back and defends it on the off side.
Switches to over the wicket and bowls it full and angling across outside off, Tom Latham shoulders arms.
Lands it on a good length on off, Kane Williamson gets behind the line and defends it towards mid off.
Fuller and at the stumps, Kane Williamson gets on the front foot and eases it to square leg for a single.
On a good length and angling in just outside off, Tom Latham stays back and blocks this one out.

Serves this one full and outside off, it was there to be put away but Tom Latham does not go fully forward. But, he still goes for the drive and gets an inside edge that goes on the bounce to Niroshan Dickwella behind the wicket.
Full and slanting in on leg, Tom Latham clips this one to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson drives it firmly but does not manage to beat mid off.
LEG BYE! Full and angling down the leg side from over the wicket, Tom Latham works this one behind square on the leg side, as it goes off his pads. They cross for a leg bye.
Serves it full and shaping away outside off, Kane Williamson goes for the drive away from his body and luckily for him, he does not edge this one.
Full and around off by Kasun Rajitha, a hint of away movement, Kane Williamson presses forward to defend with soft hands. Gets an outside edge that rolls past second slip for a single.
Full but down the leg side, Tom Latham goes for the flick but misses.
Continues to go full and at the stumps, Tom Latham clips it nicely but does not manage to beat Dimuth Karunaratne at mid-wicket.
Keeps it full and around off, Tom Latham gets on the front foot and defends it on the off side.
Starts with a good-length delivery angling in at the stumps, Kane Williamson gets behind the line and keeps this one out.
On a good length and just outside off, Kane Williamson defends this one solidly on the off side.
Length delivery on off by Lahiru Kumara, Kane Williamson blocks it down the wicket.
Back of a length around off, Kane Williamson stays on the back foot and punches it to short cover.
Keeps it on a good length on off, Kane Williamson gets on the front foot and defends it down the wicket.
Back of a length around off, the ball jags back in sharply and cramps Kane Williamson for room but he still manages to defend it to point.
FOUR! Glorious by Tom Latham! Kasun Rajitha serves this one full and outside off, Tom Latham picks the length early and leans into the drive. Gets it past extra cover and collects a boundary.
On a length and at the pads, Tom Latham turns this one down to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length around off, Kane Williamson stays on the back foot and keeps it out.
Good-length delivery just outside off, Kane Williamson looks to punch it on the off side but does not manage to time this one well.
Bowls this one on a back of a length and on off, Kane Williamson solidly gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Another delivery on a good length, Kane Williamson defends this one down the wicket.
Floats it up, outside off. It grips and turns in with some extra bounce. Tom Latham goes back and nudges it in front of leg slip.

OUT! CHOPPED! Dimuth Karunaratne's decision to bring Prabath Jayasuriya on has paid dividends here. Sri Lanka get the early wicket they were after. Prabath Jayasuriya serves it short, outside off. It grips and turns in a long way. Tom Latham rocks back and tries to go for the expansive shot. Latham looks to cut it away, but inside-edges it onto the stumps instead. Pressure on the hosts straightaway.
Howout: b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Flatter and on off, blocked out.
Fuller, outside off. Henry Nicholls gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg for a brace. Henry Nicholls is off the mark.
Henry Nicholls stays back to the flat ball and defends it out late.
Tossed up, full and on off. Henry Nicholls gets it past the slip fielder. Two runs taken. A wicket-taking over by Prabath Jayasuriya comes to an end. Sri Lanka need 8 more wickets to win.
It is a length ball, angled into the pads. Kane Williamson clips it towards mid-wicket.
Good length, on fifth stump. Kane Williamson punches it to cover off the back foot.
Kane Williamson strides in to this length ball, coming back in from outside off. Kane Williamson firmly wrists it to the on side.
Full length, on fourth stump. Kane Williamson presses forward and defends it solidly.
Lahiru Kumara now angles in a length ball, outside off. It nips away off the deck. Kane Williamson has a poke at it but misses.
FOUR! Incredible shot! It is full, wide of off. Kane Williamson waits for it and crunches it past point. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence. This shot should certainly boost his confidence.
Looped up, full and on off. Henry Nicholls comes long way across and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Kane Williamson lunges and defends this full one into the deck.
Flatter, on the pads. Kane Williamson nudges it through the gap at mid-wicket. Two taken.
It is a bit short, on middle and leg. Kane Williamson clips it to the leg side. The ball chips in the air off the knee of the short leg fielder. It lands safely though and they take a single.
A single now as this is worked towards mid on.
Kane Williamson now uses his feet and bunts this full ball towards mid off. New Zealand need 222 runs to win in 40 overs.
Length ball, on top of off. Henry Nicholls blocks it with a straight bat.
Outside off, left alone by Henry Nicholls.
Swing and a miss! A bit short, wide of off. Henry Nicholls slashes hard at it but gets no bat on ball.
Lahiru Kumara hurls in a good-length delivery, wide of off. Henry Nicholls shoulders his arms at it.
Full, angled into the pads. Henry Nicholls flicks it to deep mid-wicket. The batters take two comfortably.
A sharp bumper, outside off. Henry Nicholls goes chasing after it but makes no connection. One thing is sure that Henry Nicholls is not here to sit back at all.
Back of a length, around off. Kane Williamson knocks it through the gap at covers for one.
Henry Nicholls prods to this full ball and blocks it watchfully.
Full and outside off. Henry Nicholls shuffles across and goes for the sweep. He bumps it towards short leg. The fielder gets a hand on it. One taken.
On leg, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Full, on fourth stump, blocked out solidly.
It is full, coming in with the arm. Kane Williamson charges down the wicket and blocks it into the deck.
Lahiru Kumara serves it on a good-length, angling across, in the channel. Henry Nicholls stays back and punches it through the line towards cover for one.

Oh lucky! A short ball, on middle. Kane Williamson swivels and tries to pull it away. The ball dies off the inside edge. It almost sneaks inside his pad flaps. Fortunately, it does not deflect on to the sticks.
Length, on leg. Kane Williamson clips it to mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is a short ball, on off. Henry Nicholls rides the bounce and heaves it across the line for a boundary at deep mid-wicket.
A length ball, that comes back in from outside off. Henry Nicholls fails to flick it away and takes a blow on his pads.
Fuller, outside off. Henry Nicholls drives it toward mid off. Angelo Mathews rushes to his right and makes a sharp stop with a dive. One taken.
Full, on off. Henry Nicholls fends it to covers and scampers across for a quick single.
Pushed through quicker, on off. Kane Williamson defends it under his eyes.
Kane Williamson now wrists this full ball towards long on for an easy single.
Floated and full, outside off. Henry Nicholls gets low and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for one.
FOUR! Great use of the feet. It is tossed up, on off. Kane Williamson dances down the track and smacks it down the ground for four runs.

FOUR! Consecutive boundaries to end the over. Kane Williamson now getting into the act here. It is a short ball, on middle and leg. Kane Williamson whips it powerfully through mid-wicket. It races away for four more.

Misfield! It is a full-length ball, outside off. Henry Nicholls drives it to the right of mid off. Angelo Mathews hurries to his right but the ball sneaks through him. The batters take three with ease.
Much fuller, angled into the pads. Kane Williamson dabs it back to the bowler.
A bit straight this time, on a length, around off. Kane Williamson stays back and defends.
Full length, on off. Kane Williamson fends it to the off side.

DROPPED! A huge let off for Kane Williamson. Lahiru Kumara angles in a length ball and gets it to shape away. It catches the outside edge of Kane Williamson's blade. The ball flies low and to the right of the keeper. Niroshan Dickwella dives to that side, gets a hand on it but it does not stick in. The batters sneak a single.
Length, on off, defended to covers.
It is full, down leg. Kane Williamson pads it out.
Darted on the pads, Kane Williamson clips it to square leg for a single.
Floated and full, outside off. Some extra bounce this time. Henry Nicholls hangs his blade away from his body and gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! Prabath Jayasuriya is turning the game on its head here. He has picked up his second wicket of the innings and a crucial one. Henry Nicholls' struggles with the bat continue. It is tossed up, full and outside off. Henry Nicholls gets low and goes for the sweep. The ball takes the top-edge and lobs towards backward square leg. Kusal Mendis takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Kusal Mendis b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: SIX! ALL THE WAY! An ideal start for Daryl Mitchell. It is full, on leg. Daryl Mitchell comes down the track, makes some room and launches it over the bowler's head for a biggie.
Fuller, outside leg. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out off his pads. A successful over from Prabath Jayasuriya comes to an end.
Length, outside off. Kane Williamson lets it be.
Kane Williamson stays back and taps this length ball towards point.
BEATEN! Asitha Fernando drifts in a length ball, on fourth stump. It shapes away late and beats the outside edge.
Short one, wide of off. Left alone.
Asitha Fernando hurls in a length ball, outside off. It nips away just enough to beat the outside edge once again in this over.
