Shorter, on top of off. Kane Williamson hops and blocks.
Flighted, full on leg, Daryl Mitchell blocks this one out off his pads.
Short and way down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell leaves the ball alone. The umpire warns Prabath Jayasuriya for bowling this too far down the leg side.
WIDE! Short and down the leg side again, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms and the umpire signals a wide.
WIDE! Another delivery down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell lets it go and it is signalled as a wide.
Floated, full at the pads, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and defends it down the wicket.
WIDE! Short again and on leg, Daryl Mitchell gets inside the line of the ball and leaves the ball alone. It is wided once again.
Short and on middle, Daryl Mitchell pushes this one off the back foot to short cover.
Short and on off, Daryl Mitchell works this one towards point and takes a single.
Flatter at the stumps, Kane Williamson pushes this one back to the bowler.
Short of a length outside off, Daryl Mitchell advances and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Edgy! On a good length in the channel outside off, Kane Williamson goes for the drive away from his body and gets a thickish outside edge. The ball travels through the vacant third slip area for a boundary.
Back of a length on middle, Kane Williamson picks the length early and pulls it wide of deep square leg. Kasun Rajitha runs to his right and puts in the dive to save a run for his side.
On a good length outside off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet to defend this one but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length delivery around off, Daryl Mitchell steps out and lofts it over mid off. The ball plugs in the outfield and batters run two.
Fuller on off by Asitha Fernando, Daryl Mitchell drives it down to long off and retains the strike with a single.
Flighted, full on middle, Daryl Mitchell looks to push this one back to the bowler but gets an inside edge. The ball comes off his pads and drops to the left of short leg.
Floated, full at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell gets forward and keeps this one out.
Loopy delivery, full on leg, Daryl Mitchell paddles this one down to fine leg for a single.
Short and at the stumps, Kane Williamson stays back and whips it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Short and flatter on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell solidly gets behind the line.
Tossed up, full on off, Daryl Mitchell knocks it down to long off for a run.
Back of a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell withdraws his bat and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
On a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell takes a big stride forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off by Asitha Fernando, Daryl Mitchell punches this one off the back foot to cover for a single.
Bowls it back of a length and angling in off, Kane Williamson stays back and dabs this one to point for a run.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it firmly but finds extra cover.

Lands it full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell goes for the drive but gets it from the outer part of the bat. The ball goes on the bounce towards gully where the fielder makes a sharp stop to his right.
Short and at the pads by Prabath Jayasuriya, Kane Williamson goes back and works it to short leg.
Flighted delivery on leg, Kane Williamson blocks this one off his pads.
Touch fuller this time on middle and leg, Kane Williamson watchfully keeps this one out.
Continues to bowl it at the pads and on a fuller length, Kane Williamson gets behind the line and defends.
Fuller around off, Kane Williamson gets forward and keeps it out.
Floated, full on leg, Kane Williamson presses forward and defends.
Full and shaping away outside off, Daryl Mitchell slices this one towards deep point for a single.
On a good length in the channel outside off, Kane Williamson gets squared up a bit but still manages to defend this one towards gully.
Length delivery and going away outside off, Kane Williamson gets on top of the bounce and cuts it to deep point for a run.
Fuller and swinging away outside off, Daryl Mitchell steps out and shoulders arms.
FOUR! Goes with the inswinger this time but drifts at the pads, Daryl Mitchell brings his wrists into play and clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Keeps it full and just outside off, Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
Tossed up nicely, full on leg, the ball turns away from the rough and beats Kane Williamson on the outside edge.
Flighted delivery, full on leg, Kane Williamson gets down and sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Full and quicker at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell knocks it down to long off for a single.
Floated, full on middle and leg, Kane Williamson pushes it back to the bowler.
Another tossed up delivery on leg, Kane Williamson presses forward and keeps it out on the off side.

Short and down the leg side, Kane Williamson goes back to work it on the leg side but misses. Niroshan Dickwella behind the wicket misses as well but batters decide not to run as the ball rolls behind the keeper.

FOUR! Kasun Rajitha keeps it full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell plants his foot forward and goes for the drive away from his body. The ball catches the inside edge and races away towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Good-length delivery shaping away outside off, Daryl Mitchell is happy to let this one go.
Fuller and at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and drives it down to long on for a single.

FIFTY for Kane Williamson! On a good length and outside off, Kane Williamson allows the ball to come to him and plays this one under his eyes. Taps this one past backward point and collects a boundary to bring up his fifty.
Lands it on a length and angling in just outside off, Kane Williamson gets his gloves out of the way and lets it go.
Much wider this time and outside off, Kane Williamson shoulders arms.
Floated, full and turning away on middle, Daryl Mitchell gets forward to defend but gets an outside edge that goes agonizingly wide of first slip. The ball rolls to third man for a couple of runs.
Full and on leg, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet to defend but gets it from the inner part of the bat towards short leg.
Flighted, full at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell pulls out the reverse sweep but gets it off his gloves. Luckily for him, the ball does not lob up in the air.
Tossed up, full outside off, Daryl Mitchell leans forward and keeps this one out.
Fuller again and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it down the wicket.
Short and on leg by Prabath Jayasuriya, Daryl Mitchell goes back and works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Starts with a good-length delivery shaping away near the tramline on the off side, Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
Back of a length this time and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms.
Goes full and around off, Daryl Mitchell gets to the pitch of the delivery and drives it down to long off for a single.
Length delivery outside off, Kane Williamson dabs this to deep point for a single.
Full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shuffles across and knocks it down to long on for a single.
On a length around off, Kane Williamson guides this one along the ground to gully. New Zealand need more 146 runs to win.
Full and on off. Daryl Mitchell drives it down to the left of the bowler.
It is fuller, on leg. Daryl Mitchell prods and gets a thick inside edge on it. The ball falls short of short leg.
Daryl Mitchell now gets the reverse sweep out and gets it past the slip fielder. One taken.
Shorter, on middle and leg. Kane Williamson goes back and knocks it down to long off for a single.
Another single now as Daryl Mitchell pushes this full ball firmly down the ground.
Tossed up, around leg. It turns away sharply. Kane Williamson plays it late and dabs it into the wicket. This stand is looking really solid now for the hosts.
A length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell charges down the wicket and clips it in front of long on. The batters take a single.
Swing and a miss! Good length, outside off. shaping further away. Kane Williamson goes after it but misses.
Much fuller, in the channel. Kane Williamson shuffles and lets it be.
Full length, around off. Kane Williamson drives it uppishly through point. Fortunately, it goes through the gap. One taken.
On a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell comes across and fends it into covers.
Fraction short, on off. Daryl Mitchell stands tall and taps it back to the bowler.
Floated and full, on middle. Kane Williamson presses forward and smothers it into the deck.
Fuller, on off. Kane Williamson lofts it inside out over extra covers. Two taken.
A bit slower, full and on off. Kane Williamson knocks it down the park for a single this time.
Daryl Mitchell prods to this full one and defends it solidly.
SIX! BANG! 150 is up for the Kiwis. Prabath Jayasuriya gives it some air this time, full and on off. Daryl Mitchell dances down the track and launches it over the long on fence for a biggie.

Very full, on off. Daryl Mitchell pushes it gently down the ground. Prabath Jayasuriya hurries to his left but is unable to make the stop. One taken. 10 runs come off this over then. New Zealand are making their intentions pretty clear here.
Good length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell taps it to covers.
On a length, outside off once again. Daryl Mitchell takes a step across and clips it towards mid on for an easy single.
Kane Williamson rocks back to this length ball and punches it towards deep point. The call is for two and they get it.
A length ball, that jags back in from outside off. Kane Williamson remains solid in his defense this time.
Kasun Rajitha hurls in a length ball, in the channel. Kane Williamson plays it late and dabs it down to gully.

FOUR! Wonderful shot! Pleasing to the eyes. It is pitched up, outside off. Kane Williamson leans in and carves it through the gap between mid off and extra cover. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence. This boundary surely spoils the over for Kasun Rajitha.
Fuller, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell clips it to the leg side.
Prabath Jayasuriya tosses it up, outside leg. It turns way across the batter. Daryl Mitchell goes deep inside the crease but does well to drop his hands.
Full and on leg. Daryl Mitchell reverse sweeps it down to third man and collects a brace.
A single now as Daryl Mitchell hits it down to long on.
Darted on the pads, tucked into mid-wicket.

Good running! It is tossed up, full and outside off. Kane Williamson drives it uppishly over covers. The batters take three runs before the fielder cuts it out. Daryl Mitchell is doing really well to push for these extra runs here and Kane Williamson is obliging.
Lahiru Kumara starts with an inswinger, full and on off. Kane Williamson blocks it on his front foot.
Great fielding! It is a length ball, outside off. Kane Williamson punches it through the line off his back foot. Dimuth Karunaratne makes a sharp stop with a dive to his right in covers. One taken.

In the air...safe! Some rub of green for Daryl Mitchell. It is a short ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell stands tall and throws his blade at it. The ball goes high in the air off the outside edge but lands safely at mid off. They take a single.
Full length, on off, Kane Williamson blocks it late.
SIX! All the way! Kane Williamson stays back to this short ball and pulls it over the fine leg fence for a maximum.
Lahiru Kumara goes full, on leg. Kane Williamson tucks it through mid-wicket for a single. 109 runs needed to win now.
Full, outside leg. Kane Williamson gets low and sweeps it to backward square leg for a single.
Straying on the pads, clipped to the leg side.
It is pushed through quicker, on leg stump. Daryl Mitchell prods and gets it past short leg off the inside edge. It is in the air but briefly. They take a single.
On middle and leg, blocked solidly.
Tosses it up, full and on leg. Kane Williamson goes for the sweep shot. It catches the bottom edge and runs down to fine leg. Two taken.
Fuller, on middle. Kane Williamson works it to the on side off the inner half.
Fuller, on off, tailing back in. Daryl Mitchell gets an inside edge on his pads. It rolls out to the off side and the batters cross.

LEG BYE! A huge appeal for lbw but turned down. It is a full-length ball, around middle. It swings down leg. Kane Williamson tries to flick it away but misses and gets pinged on his pads. Lahiru Kumara appeals but the finger stays down. Dimuth Karunaratne takes the review. The Ball Tracking though confirms that the ball is missing the wickets. The batters get a leg bye in the end. Sri Lanka though lose a review here.
Good-length, on fifth stump. It jags back in sharply off the deck. Daryl Mitchell stands tall and tries to heave it across the line but misses.
Length and on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, on top of off. Kane Williamson defends it with full face.
Shorter, in the channel. Kane Williamson steers it through backward point and crosses.
Flatter and on the pads. Kane Williamson flicks it to square leg for one.
WIDE! Prabath Jayasuriya spills this one down the leg side. Daryl Mitchell fails to clip it away. Wide called.
On leg stump, defended solidly.
Floated and full, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it on his front foot.
A bit short, on the stumps. Daryl Mitchell goes back and taps it out.

It is full, on leg. Daryl Mitchell gets low of the reverse sweep and gets it past point. Niroshan Dickwella puts his hands up in the air and appeals for lbw. Prabath Jayasuriya sees his wicket keeper's interest and joins in late. The umpire though is unmoved. The batters cross for one. The replays later confirm that it comes off his gloves.
Full and on leg, blocked solidly.

Full-length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell flicks it down to long on and gets back for two runs quite comfortably. FIFTY FOR MITCHELL! He has certainly picked things up from where he left off. He backs his ton with a half-century here. Incredible run-scorer Daryl Mitchell has turned into.
It is full, around off. Daryl Mitchell knocks it down to long on and collects a brace once again. This is really good running.
Lahiru Kumara dishes it full, around off. Daryl Mitchell pushes it back to the bowler.
It is full, sliding down leg. Daryl Mitchell flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Lahiru Kumara hurls in a length ball, outside off. It jags back in. Kane Williamson looks to hit it through the line but gets beaten on the inside edge.

BEATEN! A bit fuller this time, outside off. It nips back in off the deck. Kane Williamson hangs his blade away from his body but misses it completely. He gets beaten on the inside edge once again but no luck going Sri Lanka's way.
SIX! Daryl Mitchell goes huge! Prabath Jayasuriya gives this one air and bowls it full on middle, Daryl Mitchell shimmies down the track and thumps it well over long off for a maximum.
Another flighted delivery on leg, Daryl Mitchell hoicks across the line and gets it from the inner part of the bat towards deep square leg for a single.
Keeps it full and on off, Kane Williamson gets forward and works it to point for a single.
Full on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and defends.

SIX! Another tossed up delivery, full on leg, Daryl Mitchell gets down the track in a flash and swings his bat at it. Gets it from the bottom part of the bat but the power of Mitchell sends the ball over the long on fence for yet another maximum.
Fullish delivery at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell knocks it down to long on and retains the strike with a single. New Zealand now need 78 more runs to win.
Goes full and on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell clips this one off his toes to deep square leg for a run.
Length delivery angling in on off, Kane Williamson allows the ball to come to him and blocks this one out.
On a good length just outside off, Kane Williamson steers this one on the off side but finds gully.
FOUR! Lahiru Kumara serves this one fuller in length and on middle, Kane Williamson picks the length early and rolls his wrists. Clips it wide of mid on and collects a boundary.
Leg bye! Back of a length and tailing back into the batter, Kane Williamson misses the flick and gets hit on the thigh. The ball drops at his feet and batters sneak in a quick single.
Short of a length on off, Daryl Mitchell pulls it hard to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Sloppy stuff! Asitha Fernando starts with a low full toss on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks this one wide of mid on where Chamika Karunaratne runs across to his right. He does not bend down low enough and ends up conceding a boundary.
Short of a length on middle, Daryl Mitchell pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket and collects a couple of runs more.
Another low full toss outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it to deep cover and settles for a single.

FOUR! Immaculate placement! Asitha Fernando keeps this one full and outside off, Kane Williamson gets the width he needs and frees his arms. Creams the drive and gets it wide of deep cover for a boundary.
Full and drifting onto the pads, Kane Williamson turns this one down to fine leg for a single.
Low full toss at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell goes for a big heave but gets an inside edge back onto his pads. The ball rolls to point for a single. Another good over for New Zealand.
Sharp bumper! Banged in short and at the batter, Daryl Mitchell goes for the hook but the ball climbs on him and he fails to connect.
Short of a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell taps this one off the back foot to deep backward point for a single.
Goes short again and on middle, Kane Williamson ducks under and lets it be.
Persists with short length and outside off, Kane Williamson gets on his toes and steers it wide of third man for a run.

Another bumper directed at the batter, Daryl Mitchell goes for the pull but gets it from the upper of the bat. The lobs way in front of Angelo Mathews at mid-wicket and the batters cross for a single.
Low full toss at the pads, Kane Williamson clips this one nicely but finds mid-wicket.
Length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell plays this one back to the bowler.
Serves it full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drills it down to long off and takes a single.
Slower and into the wicket on middle, Kane Williamson ducks under and lets it go.
Fullish delivery around off by Asitha Fernando, Kane Williamson squeezes this one to deep cover for a single.

OUT! CHOPPED IT ON! Asitha Fernando nails the yorker outside off, Daryl Mitchell reaches out to the delivery and looks to dig this one on the off side. The ball catches the inside edge and trickles back onto the stumps. End of a brilliant knock by Daryl Mitchell. Do Sri Lanka sense an opening here?
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Tries to go full again but ends up bowling a full toss on off, Tom Blundell pushes this one back to the bowler.
Serves it full and outside off, Kane Williamson pushes this one back to the left of the bowler. Lahiru Kumara fumbles a bit in his follow through but batters decide not to run on the misfield.
Back of a length on middle, Kane Williamson hangs back and turns this one in front of deep square leg which allows him to come back for the second.
Short of a length at the batter, Kane Williamson ducks under and lets it be.
Full and slanting in on leg, Kane Williamson clips this one off his toes to deep square leg and settles for a single.

Banged in short and on off by Lahiru Kumara, Tom Blundell goes for the pull but plays it a bit early. Gets an inside edge onto his right elbow. The ball rolls behind square on the leg side for a single.
Another well-directed bouncer, Kane Williamson ducks under and lets it be.
Bowls this one on a length and wide outside off, Tom Blundell goes for the drive away from his body and is lucky not to edge this one.
Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell reaches out to the delivery again and drives it to deep point. Dhananjaya de Silva in the deep does not pick the ball which allows batters to run two.

OUT! TIMBER! This is a brutal delivery by Asitha Fernando! Bowls a searing yorker at the stumps, a hint of inward movement in the air, Tom Blundell gets hurried and fails to get his bat down in time to dig this one out. Sees his middle stump pegged back and New Zealand are all of a sudden 5 wickets down. Do we have a late twist in this game?
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Full and straight, on the pads. Michael Bracewell flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, Kane Williamson leans into the drive and plays it to deep cover for a single.
Low full toss outside off, Michael Bracewell drives it to deep cover and takes a single.

Banged in short and at the batter by Lahiru Kumara, Michael Bracewell swivels in his crease and pulls it hard to deep square leg. Kasun Rajitha stationed there moves quickly to his left and puts in the dive. Saves three runs for his side with an acrobatic effort.
Short again and on off, Kane Williamson stands tall and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tries to go full this time but ends up bowling a low full toss down the leg side, Michael Bracewell flicks this one down to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length and tailing in on middle, Kane Williamson gets on the back foot and places this one gently between deep mid-wicket and deep square leg which allows him to come back for the second.
Switches to short length and on off, Kane Williamson pulls it to deep square leg and takes a single.
Full and tailing in on leg, Michael Bracewell works this one to deep square leg for a single. New Zealand need 37 runs now.
WIDE! Asitha Fernando goes full, well outside off, even outside the tramline. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone. Wide called by the umpire.
LEG BYE! It is full, sliding down leg. Michael Bracewell fails to clip it away. The ball rolls to the left of the keeper off the pads. They cross for a leg bye.
Asitha Fernando fires it full, tailing into the pads. Kane Williamson gets it through covers off the leading edge. One taken. Kane Williamson is on 99 now.
A short ball, outside off, swings in late. Michael Bracewell thinks about riding the bounce here but misses it completely.
Very full, wide of off. Michael Bracewell carves it towards deep point. They take a single.

TEST HUNDRED NUMBER 27! Kane Williamson continues his domination in the fourth innings of Test cricket. A crucial innings, right when his side needed it the most. It is full, wide of off. Kane Williamson reaches out and taps it to covers for a single. Kane Williamson raises his bat and soaks in the applause of his team-mates and the crowd.
Banged in short and at the batter, Michael Bracewell goes for the pull but does not connect.
WIDE! Bend his back and bowls it short outside off, Kane Williamson looks to ramp this one over the keeper's head but the ball sails over his head. The umpire signals wide for height.
Full this time and outside off, Kane Williamson carves this one wide of deep point and collects a couple of runs.
Nails the yorker at the stumps, Kane Williamson digs this one out back to the bowler.
Low full toss on middle by Kasun Rajitha, Kane Williamson places this one to the left of Lahiru Kumara at long off and comes back for the second.

On a length and outside off, Kane Williamson frees his arms and slaps this one wide of long off. Lahiru Kumara runs across to his left and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The third umpire is called for but the replays show that Michael Bracewell is safely in.
Full and angling into the batter, Kane Williamson flicks this one to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Brute force by Michael Bracewell! Kasun Rajitha bowls a cutter and on off, Michael Bracewell picks the change of pace and waits for the ball to arrive. Thumps it back over the bowler's head for a boundary. New Zealand now need 20 more runs to win.
Full length, outside off. Kane Williamson whips it to long on and takes a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Asitha Fernando picks his third wicket of the innings. Asitha Fernando serves a short ball, outside off. Michael Bracewell goes hunting for another boundary. He pulls it powerfully to deep mid-wicket but hits it straight down the throat of Chamika Karunaratne, the substitute fielder who takes a sharp catch in the deep. Is there a twist in the tale?
Howout: c sub Chamika Karunaratne b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Goes full again and outside off, Tim Southee drives away from the body and gets a thickish outside edge that flies down to third man for a single.
Full and tailing at the stumps by Asitha Fernando, Kane Williamson accounts for the inward movement and flicks this one to the right of long on for a brace.
Bowls a low full toss near the tramline on the off side, Kane Williamson leaves the ball alone.
Another low full toss angling in on off, Kane Williamson knocks it down to long on and retains the strike with a single. New Zealand need 15 from the last two overs.

Nails the yorker at the stumps, Kane Williamson gets his bat down in time and digs this one out in front of deep mid-wicket. Chamika Karunaratne gets to the ball quickly and fires an accurate throw at the striker's end but Williamson is just too quick and safely makes his ground.
Fullish delivery on leg, Kane Williamson flicks this one off his toes to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Lahiru Kumara shortens his length and bowls it on middle, Tim Southee backs away and goes for the pull shot. Does not get it from the middle part of the bat and skies this one high in the air towards deep mid-wicket. Dhananjaya de Silva and Chamika Karunaratne run across from their respective positions for the catch. Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the catch at the last moment and hangs onto it.
Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary: Full and straight at the stumps, Matt Henry drives this one uppishly towards long off for a single.
Back of a length outside off, Kane Williamson runs this one down to third man and takes a single.

Short of a length on middle by Lahiru Kumara, Matt Henry backs away and creates room. Flat bats this one back over the bowler's head. Ramesh Mendis runs around from long on and makes a good diving stop to save two runs for his side. A bit luck for Sri Lanka as Ramesh Mendis could've touched the toblerone for sure but there were just ropes at the long off region. It will be Kane Williamson on strike at the start of the next over with New Zealand needing 8 from the final 6 balls.

Starts with a fullish delivery outside off, Kane Williamson swings his bat at it and gets it from the toe end of the bat. The ball rolls towards long on and he wants to come back for the second. But, he slips while turning and has to settle for a single.
Low full toss outside off, Matt Henry reaches out to the delivery and hits it down to long off for a run.

OUT! RUN OUT! Another low full toss outside off, Kane Williamson gets across to the off side and whips this one towards deep mid-wicket. The batters complete a single but Williamson wants to retain the strike and calls Matt Henry for the second. Kasun Rajitha gets to the ball quickly and fires an accurate throw to Asitha Fernando at the non-striker's end. He takes the bails off and catches Henry short of the crease despite the dive.
Howout: run out (Kasun Rajitha / Asitha Fernando)

Commentary: FOUR! BEAUTIFUL SHOT! The scores are level now. Asitha Fernando bowls it full and outside off, Kane Williamson picks the length early and leans into the drive. Creams the drive between deep backward point and deep cover for a boundary.

Banged in short and around off, Kane Williamson goes for the pull but does not get any bat on it. He has a look a the square leg umpire who deems the ball to be below the batter's head. New Zealand need 1 off the last ball.

THAT'S IT! New Zealand win by 2 wickets! Unreal scenes at the Hagley Oval. Asitha Fernando goes short again and bowls it at the batter, Kane Williamson shuffles across to pull this one on the leg side but misses again. Niroshan Dickwella behind the wicket pouches it safely and fires a throw at the striker's end as the batters look to sneak in a bye. He does not hit and his throw is collected by Asitha Fernando in the middle of the pitch. Fernando picks the ball, turns around and hits at the non-strikers' end. Sri Lanka think they have got their man but the replays show that the dive by Kane Williamson helped him make his ground by the barest of margins. Sri Lanka are dejected but you gotta stand up and applaud Kane Williamson for his outstanding knock.
